45 return nullptr;

48bool TargetLowering::isPositionIndependent() const {
49 return getTargetMachine().isPositionIndependent();

52/// Check whether a given call node is in tail position within its function. If
53/// so, it sets Chain to the input chain of the tail call.
54bool TargetLowering::isInTailCallPosition(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDNode *Node,
55 SDValue &Chain) const {
56 const Function &F = DAG.getMachineFunction().getFunction();
57
58 // Conservatively require the attributes of the call to match those of
59 // the return. Ignore NoAlias and NonNull because they don't affect the
60 // call sequence.
61 AttributeList CallerAttrs = F.getAttributes();
62 if (AttrBuilder(CallerAttrs, AttributeList::ReturnIndex)
63 .removeAttribute(Attribute::NoAlias)
64 .removeAttribute(Attribute::NonNull)
65 .hasAttributes())
66 return false;
67
68 // It's not safe to eliminate the sign / zero extension of the return value.
69 if (CallerAttrs.hasAttribute(AttributeList::ReturnIndex, Attribute::ZExt) ||
70 CallerAttrs.hasAttribute(AttributeList::ReturnIndex, Attribute::SExt))
71 return false;
72
73 // Check if the only use is a function return node.
74 return isUsedByReturnOnly(Node, Chain);
75}
76
77bool TargetLowering::parametersInCSRMatch(const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI,
78 const uint32_t *CallerPreservedMask,
79 const SmallVectorImpl<CCValAssign> &ArgLocs,
80 const SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &OutVals) const {
81 for (unsigned I = 0, E = ArgLocs.size(); I != E; ++I) {
82 const CCValAssign &ArgLoc = ArgLocs[I];
83 if (!ArgLoc.isRegLoc())
84 continue;
85 unsigned Reg = ArgLoc.getLocReg();
86 // Only look at callee saved registers.
87 if (MachineOperand::clobbersPhysReg(CallerPreservedMask, Reg))
88 continue;
89 // Check that we pass the value used for the caller.
90 // (We look for a CopyFromReg reading a virtual register that is used
91 // for the function live-in value of register Reg)
92 SDValue Value = OutVals[I];
93 if (Value->getOpcode() != ISD::CopyFromReg)
94 return false;
95 unsigned ArgReg = cast<RegisterSDNode>(Value->getOperand(1))->getReg();
96 if (MRI.getLiveInPhysReg(ArgReg) != Reg)
97 return false;
98 }
99 return true;
100}

102/// Set CallLoweringInfo attribute flags based on a call instruction
103/// and called function attributes.
104void TargetLoweringBase::ArgListEntry::setAttributes(const CallBase *Call,
105 unsigned ArgIdx) {
106 IsSExt = Call->paramHasAttr(ArgIdx, Attribute::SExt);
107 IsZExt = Call->paramHasAttr(ArgIdx, Attribute::ZExt);
108 IsInReg = Call->paramHasAttr(ArgIdx, Attribute::InReg);
109 IsSRet = Call->paramHasAttr(ArgIdx, Attribute::StructRet);
110 IsNest = Call->paramHasAttr(ArgIdx, Attribute::Nest);
111 IsByVal = Call->paramHasAttr(ArgIdx, Attribute::ByVal);
112 IsInAlloca = Call->paramHasAttr(ArgIdx, Attribute::InAlloca);
113 IsReturned = Call->paramHasAttr(ArgIdx, Attribute::Returned);
114 IsSwiftSelf = Call->paramHasAttr(ArgIdx, Attribute::SwiftSelf);
115 IsSwiftError = Call->paramHasAttr(ArgIdx, Attribute::SwiftError);
116 Alignment = Call->getParamAlignment(ArgIdx);
117 ByValType = nullptr;
118 if (Call->paramHasAttr(ArgIdx, Attribute::ByVal))
119 ByValType = Call->getParamByValType(ArgIdx);
120}

122/// Generate a libcall taking the given operands as arguments and returning a
123/// result of type RetVT.
124std::pair<SDValue, SDValue>
125TargetLowering::makeLibCall(SelectionDAG &DAG, RTLIB::Libcall LC, EVT RetVT,
126 ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops, bool isSigned,
127 const SDLoc &dl, bool doesNotReturn,
128 bool isReturnValueUsed,
129 bool isPostTypeLegalization) const {
130 TargetLowering::ArgListTy Args;
131 Args.reserve(Ops.size());
132
133 TargetLowering::ArgListEntry Entry;
134 for (SDValue Op : Ops) {
135 Entry.Node = Op;
136 Entry.Ty = Entry.Node.getValueType().getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext());
137 Entry.IsSExt = shouldSignExtendTypeInLibCall(Op.getValueType(), isSigned);
138 Entry.IsZExt = !shouldSignExtendTypeInLibCall(Op.getValueType(), isSigned);
139 Args.push_back(Entry);
140 }
141
142 if (LC == RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL)
143 report_fatal_error("Unsupported library call operation!");
144 SDValue Callee = DAG.getExternalFunctionSymbol(getLibcallName(LC));
145
146 Type *RetTy = RetVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext());
147 TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo CLI(DAG);
148 bool signExtend = shouldSignExtendTypeInLibCall(RetVT, isSigned);
149 CLI.setDebugLoc(dl)
150 .setChain(DAG.getEntryNode())
151 .setLibCallee(getLibcallCallingConv(LC), RetTy, Callee, std::move(Args))
152 .setNoReturn(doesNotReturn)
153 .setDiscardResult(!isReturnValueUsed)
154 .setIsPostTypeLegalization(isPostTypeLegalization)
155 .setSExtResult(signExtend)
156 .setZExtResult(!signExtend);
157 return LowerCallTo(CLI);
158}

160bool
161TargetLowering::findOptimalMemOpLowering(std::vector<EVT> &MemOps,
162 unsigned Limit, uint64_t Size,
163 unsigned DstAlign, unsigned SrcAlign,
164 bool IsMemset,
165 bool ZeroMemset,
166 bool MemcpyStrSrc,
167 bool AllowOverlap,
168 bool MustPreserveCheriCapabilities,
169 unsigned DstAS, unsigned SrcAS,
170 const AttributeList &FuncAttributes) const {
171 // If 'SrcAlign' is zero, that means the memory operation does not need to
172 // load the value, i.e. memset or memcpy from constant string. Otherwise,
173 // it's the inferred alignment of the source. 'DstAlign', on the other hand,
174 // is the specified alignment of the memory operation. If it is zero, that
175 // means it's possible to change the alignment of the destination.
176 // 'MemcpyStrSrc' indicates whether the memcpy source is constant so it does
177 // not need to be loaded.
178 if (!(SrcAlign == 0 || SrcAlign >= DstAlign))
179 return false;
180
181 EVT VT = getOptimalMemOpType(Size, DstAlign, SrcAlign,
182 IsMemset, ZeroMemset, MemcpyStrSrc,
183 FuncAttributes);
184 // XXXAR: (ab)use MVT::isVoid to indicate that a memcpy call must be made
185 if (VT == MVT::isVoid) {
186 return false; // cannot lower as memops
187 }
188 // If the type is a fat pointer, then forcibly disable overlap.
189 // XXXAR: Note this is not the same as TLI.allowsMisalignedMemoryAccesses().
190 // Even if we support unaligned access for 8-byte values, we must never
191 // perform an overlapping store if the previous store was a capability store
192 // since the 8-byte store will clear the the tag bit if it overlaps with the
193 // prior capability store!
194 if (VT.isFatPointer()) {
195 AllowOverlap = false;
196 }
197
198 if (VT == MVT::Other) {
199 // Use the largest integer type whose alignment constraints are satisfied.
200 // We only need to check DstAlign here as SrcAlign is always greater or
201 // equal to DstAlign (or zero).
202 VT = MVT::i64;
203 while (DstAlign && DstAlign < VT.getSizeInBits() / 8 &&
204 !allowsMisalignedMemoryAccesses(VT, DstAS, DstAlign))
205 VT = (MVT::SimpleValueType)(VT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy - 1);
206 assert(VT.isInteger());
207
208 // Find the largest legal integer type.
209 MVT LVT = MVT::i64;
210 while (!isTypeLegal(LVT))
211 LVT = (MVT::SimpleValueType)(LVT.SimpleTy - 1);
212 assert(LVT.isInteger());
213
214 // If the type we've chosen is larger than the largest legal integer type
215 // then use that instead.
216 if (VT.bitsGT(LVT))
217 VT = LVT;
218 }
219
220 unsigned NumMemOps = 0;
221 while (Size != 0) {
222 unsigned VTSize = VT.getSizeInBits() / 8;
223 while (VTSize > Size) {
224 // For now, only use non-vector load / store's for the left-over pieces.
225 EVT NewVT = VT;
226 unsigned NewVTSize;
227
228 bool Found = false;
229 if (VT.isVector() || VT.isFloatingPoint()) {
230 NewVT = (VT.getSizeInBits() > 64) ? MVT::i64 : MVT::i32;
231 if (isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::STORE, NewVT) &&
232 isSafeMemOpType(NewVT.getSimpleVT()))
233 Found = true;
234 else if (NewVT == MVT::i64 &&
235 isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::STORE, MVT::f64) &&
236 isSafeMemOpType(MVT::f64)) {
237 // i64 is usually not legal on 32-bit targets, but f64 may be.
238 NewVT = MVT::f64;
239 Found = true;
240 }
241 }
242 if (VT.isFatPointer()) {
243 NewVT = MVT::i64;
244 Found = isSafeMemOpType(NewVT.getSimpleVT());
245 }
246
247 if (!Found) {
248 do {
249 NewVT = (MVT::SimpleValueType)(NewVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy - 1);
250 if (NewVT == MVT::i8)
251 break;
252 } while (!isSafeMemOpType(NewVT.getSimpleVT()));
253 }
254 NewVTSize = NewVT.getSizeInBits() / 8;
255
256 // If the new VT cannot cover all of the remaining bits, then consider
257 // issuing a (or a pair of) unaligned and overlapping load / store.
258 bool Fast;
259 if (NumMemOps && AllowOverlap && NewVTSize < Size &&
260 allowsMisalignedMemoryAccesses(VT, DstAS, DstAlign,
261 MachineMemOperand::MONone, &Fast) &&
262 Fast)
263 VTSize = Size;
264 else {
265 VT = NewVT;
266 VTSize = NewVTSize;
267 }
268 }
269
270 if (++NumMemOps > Limit)
271 return false;
272
273 // If we are preserving capabilities, the first VT must be a capability
274 if (MustPreserveCheriCapabilities && MemOps.empty() && !VT.isFatPointer()) {
275 return false;
276 }
277
278 MemOps.push_back(VT);
279 Size -= VTSize;
280 }
281
282 return true;
283}

285/// Soften the operands of a comparison. This code is shared among BR_CC,
286/// SELECT_CC, and SETCC handlers.
287void TargetLowering::softenSetCCOperands(SelectionDAG &DAG, EVT VT,
288 SDValue &NewLHS, SDValue &NewRHS,
289 ISD::CondCode &CCCode,
290 const SDLoc &dl) const {
291 assert((VT == MVT::f32 || VT == MVT::f64 || VT == MVT::f128 || VT == MVT::ppcf128)
292 && "Unsupported setcc type!");
293
294 // Expand into one or more soft-fp libcall(s).
295 RTLIB::Libcall LC1 = RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL, LC2 = RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL;
296 bool ShouldInvertCC = false;
297 switch (CCCode) {
298 case ISD::SETEQ:
299 case ISD::SETOEQ:
300 LC1 = (VT == MVT::f32) ? RTLIB::OEQ_F32 :
301 (VT == MVT::f64) ? RTLIB::OEQ_F64 :
302 (VT == MVT::f128) ? RTLIB::OEQ_F128 : RTLIB::OEQ_PPCF128;
303 break;
304 case ISD::SETNE:
305 case ISD::SETUNE:
306 LC1 = (VT == MVT::f32) ? RTLIB::UNE_F32 :
307 (VT == MVT::f64) ? RTLIB::UNE_F64 :
308 (VT == MVT::f128) ? RTLIB::UNE_F128 : RTLIB::UNE_PPCF128;
309 break;
310 case ISD::SETGE:
311 case ISD::SETOGE:
312 LC1 = (VT == MVT::f32) ? RTLIB::OGE_F32 :
313 (VT == MVT::f64) ? RTLIB::OGE_F64 :
314 (VT == MVT::f128) ? RTLIB::OGE_F128 : RTLIB::OGE_PPCF128;
315 break;
316 case ISD::SETLT:
317 case ISD::SETOLT:
318 LC1 = (VT == MVT::f32) ? RTLIB::OLT_F32 :
319 (VT == MVT::f64) ? RTLIB::OLT_F64 :
320 (VT == MVT::f128) ? RTLIB::OLT_F128 : RTLIB::OLT_PPCF128;
321 break;
322 case ISD::SETLE:
323 case ISD::SETOLE:
324 LC1 = (VT == MVT::f32) ? RTLIB::OLE_F32 :
325 (VT == MVT::f64) ? RTLIB::OLE_F64 :
326 (VT == MVT::f128) ? RTLIB::OLE_F128 : RTLIB::OLE_PPCF128;
327 break;
328 case ISD::SETGT:
329 case ISD::SETOGT:
330 LC1 = (VT == MVT::f32) ? RTLIB::OGT_F32 :
331 (VT == MVT::f64) ? RTLIB::OGT_F64 :
332 (VT == MVT::f128) ? RTLIB::OGT_F128 : RTLIB::OGT_PPCF128;
333 break;
334 case ISD::SETUO:
335 LC1 = (VT == MVT::f32) ? RTLIB::UO_F32 :
336 (VT == MVT::f64) ? RTLIB::UO_F64 :
337 (VT == MVT::f128) ? RTLIB::UO_F128 : RTLIB::UO_PPCF128;
338 break;
339 case ISD::SETO:
340 LC1 = (VT == MVT::f32) ? RTLIB::O_F32 :
341 (VT == MVT::f64) ? RTLIB::O_F64 :
342 (VT == MVT::f128) ? RTLIB::O_F128 : RTLIB::O_PPCF128;
343 break;
344 case ISD::SETONE:
345 // SETONE = SETOLT | SETOGT
346 LC1 = (VT == MVT::f32) ? RTLIB::OLT_F32 :
347 (VT == MVT::f64) ? RTLIB::OLT_F64 :
348 (VT == MVT::f128) ? RTLIB::OLT_F128 : RTLIB::OLT_PPCF128;
349 LC2 = (VT == MVT::f32) ? RTLIB::OGT_F32 :
350 (VT == MVT::f64) ? RTLIB::OGT_F64 :
351 (VT == MVT::f128) ? RTLIB::OGT_F128 : RTLIB::OGT_PPCF128;
352 break;
353 case ISD::SETUEQ:
354 LC1 = (VT == MVT::f32) ? RTLIB::UO_F32 :
355 (VT == MVT::f64) ? RTLIB::UO_F64 :
356 (VT == MVT::f128) ? RTLIB::UO_F128 : RTLIB::UO_PPCF128;
357 LC2 = (VT == MVT::f32) ? RTLIB::OEQ_F32 :
358 (VT == MVT::f64) ? RTLIB::OEQ_F64 :
359 (VT == MVT::f128) ? RTLIB::OEQ_F128 : RTLIB::OEQ_PPCF128;
360 break;
361 default:
362 // Invert CC for unordered comparisons
363 ShouldInvertCC = true;
364 switch (CCCode) {
365 case ISD::SETULT:
366 LC1 = (VT == MVT::f32) ? RTLIB::OGE_F32 :
367 (VT == MVT::f64) ? RTLIB::OGE_F64 :
368 (VT == MVT::f128) ? RTLIB::OGE_F128 : RTLIB::OGE_PPCF128;
369 break;
370 case ISD::SETULE:
371 LC1 = (VT == MVT::f32) ? RTLIB::OGT_F32 :
372 (VT == MVT::f64) ? RTLIB::OGT_F64 :
373 (VT == MVT::f128) ? RTLIB::OGT_F128 : RTLIB::OGT_PPCF128;
374 break;
375 case ISD::SETUGT:
376 LC1 = (VT == MVT::f32) ? RTLIB::OLE_F32 :
377 (VT == MVT::f64) ? RTLIB::OLE_F64 :
378 (VT == MVT::f128) ? RTLIB::OLE_F128 : RTLIB::OLE_PPCF128;
379 break;
380 case ISD::SETUGE:
381 LC1 = (VT == MVT::f32) ? RTLIB::OLT_F32 :
382 (VT == MVT::f64) ? RTLIB::OLT_F64 :
383 (VT == MVT::f128) ? RTLIB::OLT_F128 : RTLIB::OLT_PPCF128;
384 break;
385 default: llvm_unreachable("Do not know how to soften this setcc!");
386 }
387 }
388
389 // Use the target specific return value for comparions lib calls.
390 EVT RetVT = getCmpLibcallReturnType();
391 SDValue Ops[2] = {NewLHS, NewRHS};
392 NewLHS = makeLibCall(DAG, LC1, RetVT, Ops, false /*sign irrelevant*/,
393 dl).first;
394 NewRHS = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, RetVT);
395
396 CCCode = getCmpLibcallCC(LC1);
397 // XXXAR: FIXME: why use isInteger=true here?
398 if (ShouldInvertCC)
399 // CCCode = getSetCCInverse(CCCode, /*isInteger=*/true);
400 CCCode = getSetCCInverse(CCCode, MVT::i32);
401
402 if (LC2 != RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL) {
403 SDValue Tmp = DAG.getNode(
404 ISD::SETCC, dl,
405 getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), RetVT),
406 NewLHS, NewRHS, DAG.getCondCode(CCCode));
407 NewLHS = makeLibCall(DAG, LC2, RetVT, Ops, false/*sign irrelevant*/,
408 dl).first;
409 NewLHS = DAG.getNode(
410 ISD::SETCC, dl,
411 getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), RetVT),
412 NewLHS, NewRHS, DAG.getCondCode(getCmpLibcallCC(LC2)));
413 NewLHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, Tmp.getValueType(), Tmp, NewLHS);
414 NewRHS = SDValue();
415 }
416}
417
418/// Return the entry encoding for a jump table in the current function. The
419/// returned value is a member of the MachineJumpTableInfo::JTEntryKind enum.
420unsigned TargetLowering::getJumpTableEncoding() const {
421 // In non-pic modes, just use the address of a block.
422 if (!isPositionIndependent())
423 return MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_BlockAddress;
424
425 // In PIC mode, if the target supports a GPRel32 directive, use it.
426 if (getTargetMachine().getMCAsmInfo()->getGPRel32Directive() != nullptr)
427 return MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_GPRel32BlockAddress;
428
429 // Otherwise, use a label difference.
430 return MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_LabelDifference32;
431}
432
433SDValue TargetLowering::getPICJumpTableRelocBase(SDValue Table,
434 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
435 // If our PIC model is GP relative, use the global offset table as the base.
436 unsigned JTEncoding = getJumpTableEncoding();
437
438 if ((JTEncoding == MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_GPRel64BlockAddress) ||
439 (JTEncoding == MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_GPRel32BlockAddress))
440 return DAG.getGLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE(getPointerTy(
441 DAG.getDataLayout(), DAG.getDataLayout().getGlobalsAddressSpace()));
442
443 return Table;
444}
445
446/// This returns the relocation base for the given PIC jumptable, the same as
447/// getPICJumpTableRelocBase, but as an MCExpr.
448const MCExpr *
449TargetLowering::getPICJumpTableRelocBaseExpr(const MachineFunction *MF,
450 unsigned JTI,MCContext &Ctx) const{
451 // The normal PIC reloc base is the label at the start of the jump table.
452 return MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MF->getJTISymbol(JTI, Ctx), Ctx);
453}
454
455bool
456TargetLowering::isOffsetFoldingLegal(const GlobalAddressSDNode *GA) const {
457 const TargetMachine &TM = getTargetMachine();
458 const GlobalValue *GV = GA->getGlobal();
459
460 // If the address is not even local to this DSO we will have to load it from
461 // a got and then add the offset.
462 if (!TM.shouldAssumeDSOLocal(*GV->getParent(), GV))
463 return false;
464
465 // If the code is position independent we will have to add a base register.
466 if (isPositionIndependent())
467 return false;
468
469 // Otherwise we can do it.
470 return true;
471}
