473//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
474// Optimization Methods
475//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
476
477/// If the specified instruction has a constant integer operand and there are
478/// bits set in that constant that are not demanded, then clear those bits and
479/// return true.
480bool TargetLowering::ShrinkDemandedConstant(SDValue Op, const APInt &Demanded,
481 TargetLoweringOpt &TLO) const {
482 SDLoc DL(Op);
483 unsigned Opcode = Op.getOpcode();
484
485 // Do target-specific constant optimization.
486 if (targetShrinkDemandedConstant(Op, Demanded, TLO))
487 return TLO.New.getNode();
488
489 // FIXME: ISD::SELECT, ISD::SELECT_CC
490 switch (Opcode) {
491 default:
492 break;
493 case ISD::XOR:
494 case ISD::AND:
495 case ISD::OR: {
496 auto *Op1C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1));
497 if (!Op1C)
498 return false;
499
500 // If this is a 'not' op, don't touch it because that's a canonical form.
501 const APInt &C = Op1C->getAPIntValue();
502 if (Opcode == ISD::XOR && Demanded.isSubsetOf(C))
503 return false;
504
505 if (!C.isSubsetOf(Demanded)) {
506 EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
507 SDValue NewC = TLO.DAG.getConstant(Demanded & C, DL, VT);
508 SDValue NewOp = TLO.DAG.getNode(Opcode, DL, VT, Op.getOperand(0), NewC);
509 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, NewOp);
510 }
511
512 break;
513 }
514 }
515
516 return false;
517}
518
519/// Convert x+y to (VT)((SmallVT)x+(SmallVT)y) if the casts are free.
520/// This uses isZExtFree and ZERO_EXTEND for the widening cast, but it could be
521/// generalized for targets with other types of implicit widening casts.
522bool TargetLowering::ShrinkDemandedOp(SDValue Op, unsigned BitWidth,
523 const APInt &Demanded,
524 TargetLoweringOpt &TLO) const {
525 assert(Op.getNumOperands() == 2 &&
526 "ShrinkDemandedOp only supports binary operators!");
527 assert(Op.getNode()->getNumValues() == 1 &&
528 "ShrinkDemandedOp only supports nodes with one result!");
529
530 SelectionDAG &DAG = TLO.DAG;
531 SDLoc dl(Op);
532
533 // Early return, as this function cannot handle vector types.
534 if (Op.getValueType().isVector())
535 return false;
536
537 // Don't do this if the node has another user, which may require the
538 // full value.
539 if (!Op.getNode()->hasOneUse())
540 return false;
541
542 // Search for the smallest integer type with free casts to and from
543 // Op's type. For expedience, just check power-of-2 integer types.
544 const TargetLowering &TLI = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo();
545 unsigned DemandedSize = Demanded.getActiveBits();
546 unsigned SmallVTBits = DemandedSize;
547 if (!isPowerOf2_32(SmallVTBits))
548 SmallVTBits = NextPowerOf2(SmallVTBits);
549 for (; SmallVTBits < BitWidth; SmallVTBits = NextPowerOf2(SmallVTBits)) {
550 EVT SmallVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), SmallVTBits);
551 if (TLI.isTruncateFree(Op.getValueType(), SmallVT) &&
552 TLI.isZExtFree(SmallVT, Op.getValueType())) {
553 // We found a type with free casts.
554 SDValue X = DAG.getNode(
555 Op.getOpcode(), dl, SmallVT,
556 DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, SmallVT, Op.getOperand(0)),
557 DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, SmallVT, Op.getOperand(1)));
558 assert(DemandedSize <= SmallVTBits && "Narrowed below demanded bits?");
559 SDValue Z = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, Op.getValueType(), X);
560 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, Z);
561 }
562 }
563 return false;
564}
565
566bool TargetLowering::SimplifyDemandedBits(SDValue Op, const APInt &DemandedBits,
567 DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
568 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
569 TargetLoweringOpt TLO(DAG, !DCI.isBeforeLegalize(),
570 !DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps());
571 KnownBits Known;
572
573 bool Simplified = SimplifyDemandedBits(Op, DemandedBits, Known, TLO);
574 if (Simplified) {
575 DCI.AddToWorklist(Op.getNode());
576 DCI.CommitTargetLoweringOpt(TLO);
577 }
578 return Simplified;
579}
580
581bool TargetLowering::SimplifyDemandedBits(SDValue Op, const APInt &DemandedBits,
582 KnownBits &Known,
583 TargetLoweringOpt &TLO,
584 unsigned Depth,
585 bool AssumeSingleUse) const {
586 EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
587 APInt DemandedElts = VT.isVector()
588 ? APInt::getAllOnesValue(VT.getVectorNumElements())
589 : APInt(1, 1);
590 return SimplifyDemandedBits(Op, DemandedBits, DemandedElts, Known, TLO, Depth,
591 AssumeSingleUse);
592}
593
594/// Look at Op. At this point, we know that only the OriginalDemandedBits of the
595/// result of Op are ever used downstream. If we can use this information to
596/// simplify Op, create a new simplified DAG node and return true, returning the
597/// original and new nodes in Old and New. Otherwise, analyze the expression and
598/// return a mask of Known bits for the expression (used to simplify the
599/// caller). The Known bits may only be accurate for those bits in the
600/// OriginalDemandedBits and OriginalDemandedElts.
601bool TargetLowering::SimplifyDemandedBits(
602 SDValue Op, const APInt &OriginalDemandedBits,
603 const APInt &OriginalDemandedElts, KnownBits &Known, TargetLoweringOpt &TLO,
604 unsigned Depth, bool AssumeSingleUse) const {
605 unsigned BitWidth = OriginalDemandedBits.getBitWidth();
606 assert(Op.getScalarValueSizeInBits() == BitWidth &&
607 "Mask size mismatches value type size!");
608
609 unsigned NumElts = OriginalDemandedElts.getBitWidth();
610 assert((!Op.getValueType().isVector() ||
611 NumElts == Op.getValueType().getVectorNumElements()) &&
612 "Unexpected vector size");
613
614 APInt DemandedBits = OriginalDemandedBits;
615 APInt DemandedElts = OriginalDemandedElts;
616 SDLoc dl(Op);
617 auto &DL = TLO.DAG.getDataLayout();
618
619 // Don't know anything.
620 Known = KnownBits(BitWidth);
621
622 // Undef operand.
623 if (Op.isUndef())
624 return false;
625
626 if (Op.getOpcode() == ISD::Constant) {
627 // We know all of the bits for a constant!
628 Known.One = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op)->getAPIntValue();
629 Known.Zero = ~Known.One;
630 return false;
631 }
632
633 // Other users may use these bits.
634 EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
635 if (!Op.getNode()->hasOneUse() && !AssumeSingleUse) {
636 if (Depth != 0) {
637 // If not at the root, Just compute the Known bits to
638 // simplify things downstream.
639 Known = TLO.DAG.computeKnownBits(Op, DemandedElts, Depth);
640 return false;
641 }
642 // If this is the root being simplified, allow it to have multiple uses,
643 // just set the DemandedBits/Elts to all bits.
644 DemandedBits = APInt::getAllOnesValue(BitWidth);
645 DemandedElts = APInt::getAllOnesValue(NumElts);
646 } else if (OriginalDemandedBits == 0 || OriginalDemandedElts == 0) {
647 // Not demanding any bits/elts from Op.
648 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, TLO.DAG.getUNDEF(VT));
649 } else if (Depth == 6) { // Limit search depth.
650 return false;
651 }
652
653 KnownBits Known2, KnownOut;
654 switch (Op.getOpcode()) {
655 case ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR: {
656 if (!DemandedElts[0])
657 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, TLO.DAG.getUNDEF(VT));
658
659 KnownBits SrcKnown;
660 SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
661 unsigned SrcBitWidth = Src.getScalarValueSizeInBits();
662 APInt SrcDemandedBits = DemandedBits.zextOrSelf(SrcBitWidth);
663 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Src, SrcDemandedBits, SrcKnown, TLO, Depth + 1))
664 return true;
665 Known = SrcKnown.zextOrTrunc(BitWidth, false);
666 break;
667 }
668 case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR:
669 // Collect the known bits that are shared by every constant vector element.
670 Known.Zero.setAllBits(); Known.One.setAllBits();
671 for (SDValue SrcOp : Op->ops()) {
672 if (!isa<ConstantSDNode>(SrcOp)) {
673 // We can only handle all constant values - bail out with no known bits.
674 Known = KnownBits(BitWidth);
675 return false;
676 }
677 Known2.One = cast<ConstantSDNode>(SrcOp)->getAPIntValue();
678 Known2.Zero = ~Known2.One;
679
680 // BUILD_VECTOR can implicitly truncate sources, we must handle this.
681 if (Known2.One.getBitWidth() != BitWidth) {
682 assert(Known2.getBitWidth() > BitWidth &&
683 "Expected BUILD_VECTOR implicit truncation");
684 Known2 = Known2.trunc(BitWidth);
685 }
686
687 // Known bits are the values that are shared by every element.
688 // TODO: support per-element known bits.
689 Known.One &= Known2.One;
690 Known.Zero &= Known2.Zero;
691 }
692 return false; // Don't fall through, will infinitely loop.
693 case ISD::LOAD: {
694 LoadSDNode *LD = cast<LoadSDNode>(Op);
695 if (getTargetConstantFromLoad(LD)) {
696 Known = TLO.DAG.computeKnownBits(Op, DemandedElts, Depth);
697 return false; // Don't fall through, will infinitely loop.
698 }
699 break;
700 }
701 case ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT: {
702 SDValue Vec = Op.getOperand(0);
703 SDValue Scl = Op.getOperand(1);
704 auto *CIdx = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(2));
705 EVT VecVT = Vec.getValueType();
706
707 // If index isn't constant, assume we need all vector elements AND the
708 // inserted element.
709 APInt DemandedVecElts(DemandedElts);
710 if (CIdx && CIdx->getAPIntValue().ult(VecVT.getVectorNumElements())) {
711 unsigned Idx = CIdx->getZExtValue();
712 DemandedVecElts.clearBit(Idx);
713
714 // Inserted element is not required.
715 if (!DemandedElts[Idx])
716 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, Vec);
717 }
718
719 KnownBits KnownScl;
720 unsigned NumSclBits = Scl.getScalarValueSizeInBits();
721 APInt DemandedSclBits = DemandedBits.zextOrTrunc(NumSclBits);
722 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Scl, DemandedSclBits, KnownScl, TLO, Depth + 1))
723 return true;
724
725 Known = KnownScl.zextOrTrunc(BitWidth, false);
726
727 KnownBits KnownVec;
728 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Vec, DemandedBits, DemandedVecElts, KnownVec, TLO,
729 Depth + 1))
730 return true;
731
732 if (!!DemandedVecElts) {
733 Known.One &= KnownVec.One;
734 Known.Zero &= KnownVec.Zero;
735 }
736
737 return false;
738 }
739 case ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR: {
740 SDValue Base = Op.getOperand(0);
741 SDValue Sub = Op.getOperand(1);
742 EVT SubVT = Sub.getValueType();
743 unsigned NumSubElts = SubVT.getVectorNumElements();
744
745 // If index isn't constant, assume we need the original demanded base
746 // elements and ALL the inserted subvector elements.
747 APInt BaseElts = DemandedElts;
748 APInt SubElts = APInt::getAllOnesValue(NumSubElts);
749 if (isa<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(2))) {
750 const APInt &Idx = Op.getConstantOperandAPInt(2);
751 if (Idx.ule(NumElts - NumSubElts)) {
752 unsigned SubIdx = Idx.getZExtValue();
753 SubElts = DemandedElts.extractBits(NumSubElts, SubIdx);
754 BaseElts.insertBits(APInt::getNullValue(NumSubElts), SubIdx);
755 }
756 }
757
758 KnownBits KnownSub, KnownBase;
759 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Sub, DemandedBits, SubElts, KnownSub, TLO,
760 Depth + 1))
761 return true;
762 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Base, DemandedBits, BaseElts, KnownBase, TLO,
763 Depth + 1))
764 return true;
765
766 Known.Zero.setAllBits();
767 Known.One.setAllBits();
768 if (!!SubElts) {
769 Known.One &= KnownSub.One;
770 Known.Zero &= KnownSub.Zero;
771 }
772 if (!!BaseElts) {
773 Known.One &= KnownBase.One;
774 Known.Zero &= KnownBase.Zero;
775 }
776 break;
777 }
778 case ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS: {
779 Known.Zero.setAllBits();
780 Known.One.setAllBits();
781 EVT SubVT = Op.getOperand(0).getValueType();
782 unsigned NumSubVecs = Op.getNumOperands();
783 unsigned NumSubElts = SubVT.getVectorNumElements();
784 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumSubVecs; ++i) {
785 APInt DemandedSubElts =
786 DemandedElts.extractBits(NumSubElts, i * NumSubElts);
787 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Op.getOperand(i), DemandedBits, DemandedSubElts,
788 Known2, TLO, Depth + 1))
789 return true;
790 // Known bits are shared by every demanded subvector element.
791 if (!!DemandedSubElts) {
792 Known.One &= Known2.One;
793 Known.Zero &= Known2.Zero;
794 }
795 }
796 break;
797 }
798 case ISD::VECTOR_SHUFFLE: {
799 ArrayRef<int> ShuffleMask = cast<ShuffleVectorSDNode>(Op)->getMask();
800
801 // Collect demanded elements from shuffle operands..
802 APInt DemandedLHS(NumElts, 0);
803 APInt DemandedRHS(NumElts, 0);
804 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) {
805 if (!DemandedElts[i])
806 continue;
807 int M = ShuffleMask[i];
808 if (M < 0) {
809 // For UNDEF elements, we don't know anything about the common state of
810 // the shuffle result.
811 DemandedLHS.clearAllBits();
812 DemandedRHS.clearAllBits();
813 break;
814 }
815 assert(0 <= M && M < (int)(2 * NumElts) && "Shuffle index out of range");
816 if (M < (int)NumElts)
817 DemandedLHS.setBit(M);
818 else
819 DemandedRHS.setBit(M - NumElts);
820 }
821
822 if (!!DemandedLHS || !!DemandedRHS) {
823 Known.Zero.setAllBits();
824 Known.One.setAllBits();
825 if (!!DemandedLHS) {
826 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedBits, DemandedLHS,
827 Known2, TLO, Depth + 1))
828 return true;
829 Known.One &= Known2.One;
830 Known.Zero &= Known2.Zero;
831 }
832 if (!!DemandedRHS) {
833 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedBits, DemandedRHS,
834 Known2, TLO, Depth + 1))
835 return true;
836 Known.One &= Known2.One;
837 Known.Zero &= Known2.Zero;
838 }
839 }
840 break;
841 }
842 case ISD::AND: {
843 SDValue Op0 = Op.getOperand(0);
844 SDValue Op1 = Op.getOperand(1);
845
846 // If the RHS is a constant, check to see if the LHS would be zero without
847 // using the bits from the RHS. Below, we use knowledge about the RHS to
848 // simplify the LHS, here we're using information from the LHS to simplify
849 // the RHS.
850 if (ConstantSDNode *RHSC = isConstOrConstSplat(Op1)) {
851 // Do not increment Depth here; that can cause an infinite loop.
852 KnownBits LHSKnown = TLO.DAG.computeKnownBits(Op0, DemandedElts, Depth);
853 // If the LHS already has zeros where RHSC does, this 'and' is dead.
854 if ((LHSKnown.Zero & DemandedBits) ==
855 (~RHSC->getAPIntValue() & DemandedBits))
856 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, Op0);
857
858 // If any of the set bits in the RHS are known zero on the LHS, shrink
859 // the constant.
860 if (ShrinkDemandedConstant(Op, ~LHSKnown.Zero & DemandedBits, TLO))
861 return true;
862
863 // Bitwise-not (xor X, -1) is a special case: we don't usually shrink its
864 // constant, but if this 'and' is only clearing bits that were just set by
865 // the xor, then this 'and' can be eliminated by shrinking the mask of
866 // the xor. For example, for a 32-bit X:
867 // and (xor (srl X, 31), -1), 1 --> xor (srl X, 31), 1
868 if (isBitwiseNot(Op0) && Op0.hasOneUse() &&
869 LHSKnown.One == ~RHSC->getAPIntValue()) {
870 SDValue Xor = TLO.DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, dl, VT, Op0.getOperand(0), Op1);
871 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, Xor);
872 }
873 }
874
875 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Op1, DemandedBits, DemandedElts, Known, TLO,
876 Depth + 1))
877 return true;
878 assert(!Known.hasConflict() && "Bits known to be one AND zero?");
879 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Op0, ~Known.Zero & DemandedBits, DemandedElts,
880 Known2, TLO, Depth + 1))
881 return true;
882 assert(!Known2.hasConflict() && "Bits known to be one AND zero?");
883
884 // If all of the demanded bits are known one on one side, return the other.
885 // These bits cannot contribute to the result of the 'and'.
886 if (DemandedBits.isSubsetOf(Known2.Zero | Known.One))
887 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, Op0);
888 if (DemandedBits.isSubsetOf(Known.Zero | Known2.One))
889 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, Op1);
890 // If all of the demanded bits in the inputs are known zeros, return zero.
891 if (DemandedBits.isSubsetOf(Known.Zero | Known2.Zero))
892 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, TLO.DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT));
893 // If the RHS is a constant, see if we can simplify it.
894 if (ShrinkDemandedConstant(Op, ~Known2.Zero & DemandedBits, TLO))
895 return true;
896 // If the operation can be done in a smaller type, do so.
897 if (ShrinkDemandedOp(Op, BitWidth, DemandedBits, TLO))
898 return true;
899
900 // Output known-1 bits are only known if set in both the LHS & RHS.
901 Known.One &= Known2.One;
902 // Output known-0 are known to be clear if zero in either the LHS | RHS.
903 Known.Zero |= Known2.Zero;
904 break;
905 }
906 case ISD::OR: {
907 SDValue Op0 = Op.getOperand(0);
908 SDValue Op1 = Op.getOperand(1);
909
910 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Op1, DemandedBits, DemandedElts, Known, TLO,
911 Depth + 1))
912 return true;
913 assert(!Known.hasConflict() && "Bits known to be one AND zero?");
914 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Op0, ~Known.One & DemandedBits, DemandedElts,
915 Known2, TLO, Depth + 1))
916 return true;
917 assert(!Known2.hasConflict() && "Bits known to be one AND zero?");
918
919 // If all of the demanded bits are known zero on one side, return the other.
920 // These bits cannot contribute to the result of the 'or'.
921 if (DemandedBits.isSubsetOf(Known2.One | Known.Zero))
922 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, Op0);
923 if (DemandedBits.isSubsetOf(Known.One | Known2.Zero))
924 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, Op1);
925 // If the RHS is a constant, see if we can simplify it.
926 if (ShrinkDemandedConstant(Op, DemandedBits, TLO))
927 return true;
928 // If the operation can be done in a smaller type, do so.
929 if (ShrinkDemandedOp(Op, BitWidth, DemandedBits, TLO))
930 return true;
931
932 // Output known-0 bits are only known if clear in both the LHS & RHS.
933 Known.Zero &= Known2.Zero;
934 // Output known-1 are known to be set if set in either the LHS | RHS.
935 Known.One |= Known2.One;
936 break;
937 }
938 case ISD::XOR: {
939 SDValue Op0 = Op.getOperand(0);
940 SDValue Op1 = Op.getOperand(1);
941
942 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Op1, DemandedBits, DemandedElts, Known, TLO,
943 Depth + 1))
944 return true;
945 assert(!Known.hasConflict() && "Bits known to be one AND zero?");
946 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Op0, DemandedBits, DemandedElts, Known2, TLO,
947 Depth + 1))
948 return true;
949 assert(!Known2.hasConflict() && "Bits known to be one AND zero?");
950
951 // If all of the demanded bits are known zero on one side, return the other.
952 // These bits cannot contribute to the result of the 'xor'.
953 if (DemandedBits.isSubsetOf(Known.Zero))
954 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, Op0);
955 if (DemandedBits.isSubsetOf(Known2.Zero))
956 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, Op1);
957 // If the operation can be done in a smaller type, do so.
958 if (ShrinkDemandedOp(Op, BitWidth, DemandedBits, TLO))
959 return true;
960
961 // If all of the unknown bits are known to be zero on one side or the other
962 // (but not both) turn this into an *inclusive* or.
963 // e.g. (A & C1)^(B & C2) -> (A & C1)|(B & C2) iff C1&C2 == 0
964 if (DemandedBits.isSubsetOf(Known.Zero | Known2.Zero))
965 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, TLO.DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Op0, Op1));
966
967 // Output known-0 bits are known if clear or set in both the LHS & RHS.
968 KnownOut.Zero = (Known.Zero & Known2.Zero) | (Known.One & Known2.One);
969 // Output known-1 are known to be set if set in only one of the LHS, RHS.
970 KnownOut.One = (Known.Zero & Known2.One) | (Known.One & Known2.Zero);
971
972 if (ConstantSDNode *C = isConstOrConstSplat(Op1)) {
973 // If one side is a constant, and all of the known set bits on the other
974 // side are also set in the constant, turn this into an AND, as we know
975 // the bits will be cleared.
976 // e.g. (X | C1) ^ C2 --> (X | C1) & ~C2 iff (C1&C2) == C2
977 // NB: it is okay if more bits are known than are requested
978 if (C->getAPIntValue() == Known2.One) {
979 SDValue ANDC =
980 TLO.DAG.getConstant(~C->getAPIntValue() & DemandedBits, dl, VT);
981 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, TLO.DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Op0, ANDC));
982 }
983
984 // If the RHS is a constant, see if we can change it. Don't alter a -1
985 // constant because that's a 'not' op, and that is better for combining
986 // and codegen.
987 if (!C->isAllOnesValue()) {
988 if (DemandedBits.isSubsetOf(C->getAPIntValue())) {
989 // We're flipping all demanded bits. Flip the undemanded bits too.
990 SDValue New = TLO.DAG.getNOT(dl, Op0, VT);
991 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, New);
992 }
993 // If we can't turn this into a 'not', try to shrink the constant.
994 if (ShrinkDemandedConstant(Op, DemandedBits, TLO))
995 return true;
996 }
997 }
998
999 Known = std::move(KnownOut);
1000 break;
1001 }
1002 case ISD::SELECT:
1003 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Op.getOperand(2), DemandedBits, Known, TLO,
1004 Depth + 1))
1005 return true;
1006 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedBits, Known2, TLO,
1007 Depth + 1))
1008 return true;
1009 assert(!Known.hasConflict() && "Bits known to be one AND zero?");
1010 assert(!Known2.hasConflict() && "Bits known to be one AND zero?");
1011
1012 // If the operands are constants, see if we can simplify them.
1013 if (ShrinkDemandedConstant(Op, DemandedBits, TLO))
1014 return true;
1015
1016 // Only known if known in both the LHS and RHS.
1017 Known.One &= Known2.One;
1018 Known.Zero &= Known2.Zero;
1019 break;
1020 case ISD::SELECT_CC:
1021 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Op.getOperand(3), DemandedBits, Known, TLO,
1022 Depth + 1))
1023 return true;
1024 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Op.getOperand(2), DemandedBits, Known2, TLO,
1025 Depth + 1))
1026 return true;
1027 assert(!Known.hasConflict() && "Bits known to be one AND zero?");
1028 assert(!Known2.hasConflict() && "Bits known to be one AND zero?");
1029
1030 // If the operands are constants, see if we can simplify them.
1031 if (ShrinkDemandedConstant(Op, DemandedBits, TLO))
1032 return true;
1033
1034 // Only known if known in both the LHS and RHS.
1035 Known.One &= Known2.One;
1036 Known.Zero &= Known2.Zero;
1037 break;
1038 case ISD::SETCC: {
1039 SDValue Op0 = Op.getOperand(0);
1040 SDValue Op1 = Op.getOperand(1);
1041 ISD::CondCode CC = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(Op.getOperand(2))->get();
1042 // If (1) we only need the sign-bit, (2) the setcc operands are the same
1043 // width as the setcc result, and (3) the result of a setcc conforms to 0 or
1044 // -1, we may be able to bypass the setcc.
1045 if (DemandedBits.isSignMask() &&
1046 Op0.getScalarValueSizeInBits() == BitWidth &&
1047 getBooleanContents(VT) ==
1048 BooleanContent::ZeroOrNegativeOneBooleanContent) {
1049 // If we're testing X < 0, then this compare isn't needed - just use X!
1050 // FIXME: We're limiting to integer types here, but this should also work
1051 // if we don't care about FP signed-zero. The use of SETLT with FP means
1052 // that we don't care about NaNs.
1053 if (CC == ISD::SETLT && Op1.getValueType().isInteger() &&
1054 (isNullConstant(Op1) || ISD::isBuildVectorAllZeros(Op1.getNode())))
1055 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, Op0);
1056
1057 // TODO: Should we check for other forms of sign-bit comparisons?
1058 // Examples: X <= -1, X >= 0
1059 }
1060 if (getBooleanContents(Op0.getValueType()) ==
1061 TargetLowering::ZeroOrOneBooleanContent &&
1062 BitWidth > 1)
1063 Known.Zero.setBitsFrom(1);
1064 break;
1065 }
1066 case ISD::SHL: {
1067 SDValue Op0 = Op.getOperand(0);
1068 SDValue Op1 = Op.getOperand(1);
1069
1070 if (ConstantSDNode *SA = isConstOrConstSplat(Op1)) {
1071 // If the shift count is an invalid immediate, don't do anything.
1072 if (SA->getAPIntValue().uge(BitWidth))
1073 break;
1074
1075 unsigned ShAmt = SA->getZExtValue();
1076
1077 // If this is ((X >>u C1) << ShAmt), see if we can simplify this into a
1078 // single shift. We can do this if the bottom bits (which are shifted
1079 // out) are never demanded.
1080 if (Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::SRL) {
1081 if (ShAmt &&
1082 (DemandedBits & APInt::getLowBitsSet(BitWidth, ShAmt)) == 0) {
1083 if (ConstantSDNode *SA2 = isConstOrConstSplat(Op0.getOperand(1))) {
1084 if (SA2->getAPIntValue().ult(BitWidth)) {
1085 unsigned C1 = SA2->getZExtValue();
1086 unsigned Opc = ISD::SHL;
1087 int Diff = ShAmt - C1;
1088 if (Diff < 0) {
1089 Diff = -Diff;
1090 Opc = ISD::SRL;
1091 }
1092
1093 SDValue NewSA = TLO.DAG.getConstant(Diff, dl, Op1.getValueType());
1094 return TLO.CombineTo(
1095 Op, TLO.DAG.getNode(Opc, dl, VT, Op0.getOperand(0), NewSA));
1096 }
1097 }
1098 }
1099 }
1100
1101 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Op0, DemandedBits.lshr(ShAmt), DemandedElts,
1102 Known, TLO, Depth + 1))
1103 return true;
1104
1105 // Try shrinking the operation as long as the shift amount will still be
1106 // in range.
1107 if ((ShAmt < DemandedBits.getActiveBits()) &&
1108 ShrinkDemandedOp(Op, BitWidth, DemandedBits, TLO))
1109 return true;
1110
1111 // Convert (shl (anyext x, c)) to (anyext (shl x, c)) if the high bits
1112 // are not demanded. This will likely allow the anyext to be folded away.
1113 if (Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::ANY_EXTEND) {
1114 SDValue InnerOp = Op0.getOperand(0);
1115 EVT InnerVT = InnerOp.getValueType();
1116 unsigned InnerBits = InnerVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
1117 if (ShAmt < InnerBits && DemandedBits.getActiveBits() <= InnerBits &&
1118 isTypeDesirableForOp(ISD::SHL, InnerVT)) {
1119 EVT ShTy = getShiftAmountTy(InnerVT, DL);
1120 if (!APInt(BitWidth, ShAmt).isIntN(ShTy.getSizeInBits()))
1121 ShTy = InnerVT;
1122 SDValue NarrowShl =
1123 TLO.DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, InnerVT, InnerOp,
1124 TLO.DAG.getConstant(ShAmt, dl, ShTy));
1125 return TLO.CombineTo(
1126 Op, TLO.DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, VT, NarrowShl));
1127 }
1128 // Repeat the SHL optimization above in cases where an extension
1129 // intervenes: (shl (anyext (shr x, c1)), c2) to
1130 // (shl (anyext x), c2-c1). This requires that the bottom c1 bits
1131 // aren't demanded (as above) and that the shifted upper c1 bits of
1132 // x aren't demanded.
1133 if (Op0.hasOneUse() && InnerOp.getOpcode() == ISD::SRL &&
1134 InnerOp.hasOneUse()) {
1135 if (ConstantSDNode *SA2 =
1136 isConstOrConstSplat(InnerOp.getOperand(1))) {
1137 unsigned InnerShAmt = SA2->getLimitedValue(InnerBits);
1138 if (InnerShAmt < ShAmt && InnerShAmt < InnerBits &&
1139 DemandedBits.getActiveBits() <=
1140 (InnerBits - InnerShAmt + ShAmt) &&
1141 DemandedBits.countTrailingZeros() >= ShAmt) {
1142 SDValue NewSA = TLO.DAG.getConstant(ShAmt - InnerShAmt, dl,
1143 Op1.getValueType());
1144 SDValue NewExt = TLO.DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, VT,
1145 InnerOp.getOperand(0));
1146 return TLO.CombineTo(
1147 Op, TLO.DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, NewExt, NewSA));
1148 }
1149 }
1150 }
1151 }
1152
1153 Known.Zero <<= ShAmt;
1154 Known.One <<= ShAmt;
1155 // low bits known zero.
1156 Known.Zero.setLowBits(ShAmt);
1157 }
1158 break;
1159 }
1160 case ISD::SRL: {
1161 SDValue Op0 = Op.getOperand(0);
1162 SDValue Op1 = Op.getOperand(1);
1163
1164 if (ConstantSDNode *SA = isConstOrConstSplat(Op1)) {
1165 // If the shift count is an invalid immediate, don't do anything.
1166 if (SA->getAPIntValue().uge(BitWidth))
1167 break;
1168
1169 EVT ShiftVT = Op1.getValueType();
1170 unsigned ShAmt = SA->getZExtValue();
1171 APInt InDemandedMask = (DemandedBits << ShAmt);
1172
1173 // If the shift is exact, then it does demand the low bits (and knows that
1174 // they are zero).
1175 if (Op->getFlags().hasExact())
1176 InDemandedMask.setLowBits(ShAmt);
1177
1178 // If this is ((X << C1) >>u ShAmt), see if we can simplify this into a
1179 // single shift. We can do this if the top bits (which are shifted out)
1180 // are never demanded.
1181 if (Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL) {
1182 if (ConstantSDNode *SA2 = isConstOrConstSplat(Op0.getOperand(1))) {
1183 if (ShAmt &&
1184 (DemandedBits & APInt::getHighBitsSet(BitWidth, ShAmt)) == 0) {
1185 if (SA2->getAPIntValue().ult(BitWidth)) {
1186 unsigned C1 = SA2->getZExtValue();
1187 unsigned Opc = ISD::SRL;
1188 int Diff = ShAmt - C1;
1189 if (Diff < 0) {
1190 Diff = -Diff;
1191 Opc = ISD::SHL;
1192 }
1193
1194 SDValue NewSA = TLO.DAG.getConstant(Diff, dl, ShiftVT);
1195 return TLO.CombineTo(
1196 Op, TLO.DAG.getNode(Opc, dl, VT, Op0.getOperand(0), NewSA));
1197 }
1198 }
1199 }
1200 }
1201
1202 // Compute the new bits that are at the top now.
1203 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Op0, InDemandedMask, DemandedElts, Known, TLO,
1204 Depth + 1))
1205 return true;
1206 assert(!Known.hasConflict() && "Bits known to be one AND zero?");
1207 Known.Zero.lshrInPlace(ShAmt);
1208 Known.One.lshrInPlace(ShAmt);
1209
1210 Known.Zero.setHighBits(ShAmt); // High bits known zero.
1211 }
1212 break;
1213 }
1214 case ISD::SRA: {
1215 SDValue Op0 = Op.getOperand(0);
1216 SDValue Op1 = Op.getOperand(1);
1217
1218 // If this is an arithmetic shift right and only the low-bit is set, we can
1219 // always convert this into a logical shr, even if the shift amount is
1220 // variable. The low bit of the shift cannot be an input sign bit unless
1221 // the shift amount is >= the size of the datatype, which is undefined.
1222 if (DemandedBits.isOneValue())
1223 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, TLO.DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op0, Op1));
1224
1225 if (ConstantSDNode *SA = isConstOrConstSplat(Op1)) {
1226 // If the shift count is an invalid immediate, don't do anything.
1227 if (SA->getAPIntValue().uge(BitWidth))
1228 break;
1229
1230 unsigned ShAmt = SA->getZExtValue();
1231 APInt InDemandedMask = (DemandedBits << ShAmt);
1232
1233 // If the shift is exact, then it does demand the low bits (and knows that
1234 // they are zero).
1235 if (Op->getFlags().hasExact())
1236 InDemandedMask.setLowBits(ShAmt);
1237
1238 // If any of the demanded bits are produced by the sign extension, we also
1239 // demand the input sign bit.
1240 if (DemandedBits.countLeadingZeros() < ShAmt)
1241 InDemandedMask.setSignBit();
1242
1243 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Op0, InDemandedMask, DemandedElts, Known, TLO,
1244 Depth + 1))
1245 return true;
1246 assert(!Known.hasConflict() && "Bits known to be one AND zero?");
1247 Known.Zero.lshrInPlace(ShAmt);
1248 Known.One.lshrInPlace(ShAmt);
1249
1250 // If the input sign bit is known to be zero, or if none of the top bits
1251 // are demanded, turn this into an unsigned shift right.
1252 if (Known.Zero[BitWidth - ShAmt - 1] ||
1253 DemandedBits.countLeadingZeros() >= ShAmt) {
1254 SDNodeFlags Flags;
1255 Flags.setExact(Op->getFlags().hasExact());
1256 return TLO.CombineTo(
1257 Op, TLO.DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op0, Op1, Flags));
1258 }
1259
1260 int Log2 = DemandedBits.exactLogBase2();
1261 if (Log2 >= 0) {
1262 // The bit must come from the sign.
1263 SDValue NewSA =
1264 TLO.DAG.getConstant(BitWidth - 1 - Log2, dl, Op1.getValueType());
1265 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, TLO.DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op0, NewSA));
1266 }
1267
1268 if (Known.One[BitWidth - ShAmt - 1])
1269 // New bits are known one.
1270 Known.One.setHighBits(ShAmt);
1271 }
1272 break;
1273 }
1274 case ISD::FSHL:
1275 case ISD::FSHR: {
1276 SDValue Op0 = Op.getOperand(0);
1277 SDValue Op1 = Op.getOperand(1);
1278 SDValue Op2 = Op.getOperand(2);
1279 bool IsFSHL = (Op.getOpcode() == ISD::FSHL);
1280
1281 if (ConstantSDNode *SA = isConstOrConstSplat(Op2)) {
1282 unsigned Amt = SA->getAPIntValue().urem(BitWidth);
1283
1284 // For fshl, 0-shift returns the 1st arg.
1285 // For fshr, 0-shift returns the 2nd arg.
1286 if (Amt == 0) {
1287 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(IsFSHL ? Op0 : Op1, DemandedBits, DemandedElts,
1288 Known, TLO, Depth + 1))
1289 return true;
1290 break;
1291 }
1292
1293 // fshl: (Op0 << Amt) | (Op1 >> (BW - Amt))
1294 // fshr: (Op0 << (BW - Amt)) | (Op1 >> Amt)
1295 APInt Demanded0 = DemandedBits.lshr(IsFSHL ? Amt : (BitWidth - Amt));
1296 APInt Demanded1 = DemandedBits << (IsFSHL ? (BitWidth - Amt) : Amt);
1297 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Op0, Demanded0, DemandedElts, Known2, TLO,
1298 Depth + 1))
1299 return true;
1300 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Op1, Demanded1, DemandedElts, Known, TLO,
1301 Depth + 1))
1302 return true;
1303
1304 Known2.One <<= (IsFSHL ? Amt : (BitWidth - Amt));
1305 Known2.Zero <<= (IsFSHL ? Amt : (BitWidth - Amt));
1306 Known.One.lshrInPlace(IsFSHL ? (BitWidth - Amt) : Amt);
1307 Known.Zero.lshrInPlace(IsFSHL ? (BitWidth - Amt) : Amt);
1308 Known.One |= Known2.One;
1309 Known.Zero |= Known2.Zero;
1310 }
1311 break;
1312 }
1313 case ISD::BITREVERSE: {
1314 SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
1315 APInt DemandedSrcBits = DemandedBits.reverseBits();
1316 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Src, DemandedSrcBits, DemandedElts, Known2, TLO,
1317 Depth + 1))
1318 return true;
1319 Known.One = Known2.One.reverseBits();
1320 Known.Zero = Known2.Zero.reverseBits();
1321 break;
1322 }
1323 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG: {
1324 SDValue Op0 = Op.getOperand(0);
1325 EVT ExVT = cast<VTSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))->getVT();
1326 unsigned ExVTBits = ExVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
1327
1328 // If we only care about the highest bit, don't bother shifting right.
1329 if (DemandedBits.isSignMask()) {
1330 unsigned NumSignBits = TLO.DAG.ComputeNumSignBits(Op0);
1331 bool AlreadySignExtended = NumSignBits >= BitWidth - ExVTBits + 1;
1332 // However if the input is already sign extended we expect the sign
1333 // extension to be dropped altogether later and do not simplify.
1334 if (!AlreadySignExtended) {
1335 // Compute the correct shift amount type, which must be getShiftAmountTy
1336 // for scalar types after legalization.
1337 EVT ShiftAmtTy = VT;
1338 if (TLO.LegalTypes() && !ShiftAmtTy.isVector())
1339 ShiftAmtTy = getShiftAmountTy(ShiftAmtTy, DL);
1340
1341 SDValue ShiftAmt =
1342 TLO.DAG.getConstant(BitWidth - ExVTBits, dl, ShiftAmtTy);
1343 return TLO.CombineTo(Op,
1344 TLO.DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Op0, ShiftAmt));
1345 }
1346 }
1347
1348 // If none of the extended bits are demanded, eliminate the sextinreg.
1349 if (DemandedBits.getActiveBits() <= ExVTBits)
1350 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, Op0);
1351
1352 APInt InputDemandedBits = DemandedBits.getLoBits(ExVTBits);
1353
1354 // Since the sign extended bits are demanded, we know that the sign
1355 // bit is demanded.
1356 InputDemandedBits.setBit(ExVTBits - 1);
1357
1358 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Op0, InputDemandedBits, Known, TLO, Depth + 1))
1359 return true;
1360 assert(!Known.hasConflict() && "Bits known to be one AND zero?");
1361
1362 // If the sign bit of the input is known set or clear, then we know the
1363 // top bits of the result.
1364
1365 // If the input sign bit is known zero, convert this into a zero extension.
1366 if (Known.Zero[ExVTBits - 1])
1367 return TLO.CombineTo(
1368 Op, TLO.DAG.getZeroExtendInReg(Op0, dl, ExVT.getScalarType()));
1369
1370 APInt Mask = APInt::getLowBitsSet(BitWidth, ExVTBits);
1371 if (Known.One[ExVTBits - 1]) { // Input sign bit known set
1372 Known.One.setBitsFrom(ExVTBits);
1373 Known.Zero &= Mask;
1374 } else { // Input sign bit unknown
1375 Known.Zero &= Mask;
1376 Known.One &= Mask;
1377 }
1378 break;
1379 }
1380 case ISD::BUILD_PAIR: {
1381 EVT HalfVT = Op.getOperand(0).getValueType();
1382 unsigned HalfBitWidth = HalfVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
1383
1384 APInt MaskLo = DemandedBits.getLoBits(HalfBitWidth).trunc(HalfBitWidth);
1385 APInt MaskHi = DemandedBits.getHiBits(HalfBitWidth).trunc(HalfBitWidth);
1386
1387 KnownBits KnownLo, KnownHi;
1388
1389 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Op.getOperand(0), MaskLo, KnownLo, TLO, Depth + 1))
1390 return true;
1391
1392 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Op.getOperand(1), MaskHi, KnownHi, TLO, Depth + 1))
1393 return true;
1394
1395 Known.Zero = KnownLo.Zero.zext(BitWidth) |
1396 KnownHi.Zero.zext(BitWidth).shl(HalfBitWidth);
1397
1398 Known.One = KnownLo.One.zext(BitWidth) |
1399 KnownHi.One.zext(BitWidth).shl(HalfBitWidth);
1400 break;
1401 }
1402 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND: {
1403 SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
1404 unsigned InBits = Src.getScalarValueSizeInBits();
1405
1406 // If none of the top bits are demanded, convert this into an any_extend.
1407 if (DemandedBits.getActiveBits() <= InBits)
1408 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, TLO.DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, VT, Src));
1409
1410 APInt InDemandedBits = DemandedBits.trunc(InBits);
1411 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Src, InDemandedBits, Known, TLO, Depth + 1))
1412 return true;
1413 assert(!Known.hasConflict() && "Bits known to be one AND zero?");
1414 assert(Known.getBitWidth() == InBits && "Src width has changed?");
1415 Known = Known.zext(BitWidth, true /* ExtendedBitsAreKnownZero */);
1416 break;
1417 }
1418 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG: {
1419 // TODO - merge this with ZERO_EXTEND above?
1420 SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
1421 EVT SrcVT = Src.getValueType();
1422 unsigned InBits = SrcVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
1423 unsigned InElts = SrcVT.getVectorNumElements();
1424
1425 // If we only need the non-extended bits of the bottom element
1426 // then we can just bitcast to the result.
1427 if (DemandedBits.getActiveBits() <= InBits && DemandedElts == 1 &&
1428 VT.getSizeInBits() == SrcVT.getSizeInBits() &&
1429 TLO.DAG.getDataLayout().isLittleEndian())
1430 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, TLO.DAG.getBitcast(VT, Src));
1431
1432 APInt InDemandedBits = DemandedBits.trunc(InBits);
1433 APInt InDemandedElts = DemandedElts.zextOrSelf(InElts);
1434 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Src, InDemandedBits, InDemandedElts, Known, TLO,
1435 Depth + 1))
1436 return true;
1437 assert(!Known.hasConflict() && "Bits known to be one AND zero?");
1438 assert(Known.getBitWidth() == InBits && "Src width has changed?");
1439 Known = Known.zext(BitWidth, true /* ExtendedBitsAreKnownZero */);
1440 break;
1441 }
1442 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND: {
1443 SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
1444 unsigned InBits = Src.getScalarValueSizeInBits();
1445
1446 // If none of the top bits are demanded, convert this into an any_extend.
1447 if (DemandedBits.getActiveBits() <= InBits)
1448 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, TLO.DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, VT, Src));
1449
1450 // Since some of the sign extended bits are demanded, we know that the sign
1451 // bit is demanded.
1452 APInt InDemandedBits = DemandedBits.trunc(InBits);
1453 InDemandedBits.setBit(InBits - 1);
1454
1455 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Src, InDemandedBits, Known, TLO, Depth + 1))
1456 return true;
1457 assert(!Known.hasConflict() && "Bits known to be one AND zero?");
1458 // If the sign bit is known one, the top bits match.
1459 Known = Known.sext(BitWidth);
1460
1461 // If the sign bit is known zero, convert this to a zero extend.
1462 if (Known.isNonNegative())
1463 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, TLO.DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, dl, VT, Src));
1464 break;
1465 }
1466 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG: {
1467 // TODO - merge this with SIGN_EXTEND above?
1468 SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
1469 unsigned InBits = Src.getScalarValueSizeInBits();
1470
1471 APInt InDemandedBits = DemandedBits.trunc(InBits);
1472
1473 // If some of the sign extended bits are demanded, we know that the sign
1474 // bit is demanded.
1475 if (InBits < DemandedBits.getActiveBits())
1476 InDemandedBits.setBit(InBits - 1);
1477
1478 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Src, InDemandedBits, Known, TLO, Depth + 1))
1479 return true;
1480 assert(!Known.hasConflict() && "Bits known to be one AND zero?");
1481 // If the sign bit is known one, the top bits match.
1482 Known = Known.sext(BitWidth);
1483 break;
1484 }
1485 case ISD::ANY_EXTEND: {
1486 SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
1487 unsigned InBits = Src.getScalarValueSizeInBits();
1488 APInt InDemandedBits = DemandedBits.trunc(InBits);
1489 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Src, InDemandedBits, Known, TLO, Depth + 1))
1490 return true;
1491 assert(!Known.hasConflict() && "Bits known to be one AND zero?");
1492 Known = Known.zext(BitWidth, false /* => any extend */);
1493 break;
1494 }
1495 case ISD::TRUNCATE: {
1496 SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
1497
1498 // Simplify the input, using demanded bit information, and compute the known
1499 // zero/one bits live out.
1500 unsigned OperandBitWidth = Src.getScalarValueSizeInBits();
1501 APInt TruncMask = DemandedBits.zext(OperandBitWidth);
1502 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Src, TruncMask, Known, TLO, Depth + 1))
1503 return true;
1504 Known = Known.trunc(BitWidth);
1505
1506 // If the input is only used by this truncate, see if we can shrink it based
1507 // on the known demanded bits.
1508 if (Src.getNode()->hasOneUse()) {
1509 switch (Src.getOpcode()) {
1510 default:
1511 break;
1512 case ISD::SRL:
1513 // Shrink SRL by a constant if none of the high bits shifted in are
1514 // demanded.
1515 if (TLO.LegalTypes() && !isTypeDesirableForOp(ISD::SRL, VT))
1516 // Do not turn (vt1 truncate (vt2 srl)) into (vt1 srl) if vt1 is
1517 // undesirable.
1518 break;
1519
1520 auto *ShAmt = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Src.getOperand(1));
1521 if (!ShAmt || ShAmt->getAPIntValue().uge(BitWidth))
1522 break;
1523
1524 SDValue Shift = Src.getOperand(1);
1525 uint64_t ShVal = ShAmt->getZExtValue();
1526
1527 if (TLO.LegalTypes())
1528 Shift = TLO.DAG.getConstant(ShVal, dl, getShiftAmountTy(VT, DL));
1529
1530 APInt HighBits =
1531 APInt::getHighBitsSet(OperandBitWidth, OperandBitWidth - BitWidth);
1532 HighBits.lshrInPlace(ShVal);
1533 HighBits = HighBits.trunc(BitWidth);
1534
1535 if (!(HighBits & DemandedBits)) {
1536 // None of the shifted in bits are needed. Add a truncate of the
1537 // shift input, then shift it.
1538 SDValue NewTrunc =
1539 TLO.DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, VT, Src.getOperand(0));
1540 return TLO.CombineTo(
1541 Op, TLO.DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, NewTrunc, Shift));
1542 }
1543 break;
1544 }
1545 }
1546
1547 assert(!Known.hasConflict() && "Bits known to be one AND zero?");
1548 break;
1549 }
1550 case ISD::AssertZext: {
1551 // AssertZext demands all of the high bits, plus any of the low bits
1552 // demanded by its users.
1553 EVT ZVT = cast<VTSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))->getVT();
1554 APInt InMask = APInt::getLowBitsSet(BitWidth, ZVT.getSizeInBits());
1555 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Op.getOperand(0), ~InMask | DemandedBits, Known,
1556 TLO, Depth + 1))
1557 return true;
1558 assert(!Known.hasConflict() && "Bits known to be one AND zero?");
1559
1560 Known.Zero |= ~InMask;
1561 break;
1562 }
1563 case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT: {
1564 SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
1565 SDValue Idx = Op.getOperand(1);
1566 unsigned NumSrcElts = Src.getValueType().getVectorNumElements();
1567 unsigned EltBitWidth = Src.getScalarValueSizeInBits();
1568
1569 // Demand the bits from every vector element without a constant index.
1570 APInt DemandedSrcElts = APInt::getAllOnesValue(NumSrcElts);
1571 if (auto *CIdx = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Idx))
1572 if (CIdx->getAPIntValue().ult(NumSrcElts))
1573 DemandedSrcElts = APInt::getOneBitSet(NumSrcElts, CIdx->getZExtValue());
1574
1575 // If BitWidth > EltBitWidth the value is anyext:ed. So we do not know
1576 // anything about the extended bits.
1577 APInt DemandedSrcBits = DemandedBits;
1578 if (BitWidth > EltBitWidth)
1579 DemandedSrcBits = DemandedSrcBits.trunc(EltBitWidth);
1580
1581 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Src, DemandedSrcBits, DemandedSrcElts, Known2, TLO,
1582 Depth + 1))
1583 return true;
1584
1585 Known = Known2;
1586 if (BitWidth > EltBitWidth)
1587 Known = Known.zext(BitWidth, false /* => any extend */);
1588 break;
1589 }
1590 case ISD::BITCAST: {
1591 SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
1592 EVT SrcVT = Src.getValueType();
1593 unsigned NumSrcEltBits = SrcVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
1594
1595 // If this is an FP->Int bitcast and if the sign bit is the only
1596 // thing demanded, turn this into a FGETSIGN.
1597 if (!TLO.LegalOperations() && !VT.isVector() && !SrcVT.isVector() &&
1598 DemandedBits == APInt::getSignMask(Op.getValueSizeInBits()) &&
1599 SrcVT.isFloatingPoint()) {
1600 bool OpVTLegal = isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::FGETSIGN, VT);
1601 bool i32Legal = isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::FGETSIGN, MVT::i32);
1602 if ((OpVTLegal || i32Legal) && VT.isSimple() && SrcVT != MVT::f16 &&
1603 SrcVT != MVT::f128) {
1604 // Cannot eliminate/lower SHL for f128 yet.
1605 EVT Ty = OpVTLegal ? VT : MVT::i32;
1606 // Make a FGETSIGN + SHL to move the sign bit into the appropriate
1607 // place. We expect the SHL to be eliminated by other optimizations.
1608 SDValue Sign = TLO.DAG.getNode(ISD::FGETSIGN, dl, Ty, Src);
1609 unsigned OpVTSizeInBits = Op.getValueSizeInBits();
1610 if (!OpVTLegal && OpVTSizeInBits > 32)
1611 Sign = TLO.DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, dl, VT, Sign);
1612 unsigned ShVal = Op.getValueSizeInBits() - 1;
1613 SDValue ShAmt = TLO.DAG.getConstant(ShVal, dl, VT);
1614 return TLO.CombineTo(Op,
1615 TLO.DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Sign, ShAmt));
1616 }
1617 }
1618
1619 // Bitcast from a vector using SimplifyDemanded Bits/VectorElts.
1620 // Demand the elt/bit if any of the original elts/bits are demanded.
1621 // TODO - bigendian once we have test coverage.
1622 // TODO - bool vectors once SimplifyDemandedVectorElts has SETCC support.
1623 if (SrcVT.isVector() && NumSrcEltBits > 1 &&
1624 (BitWidth % NumSrcEltBits) == 0 &&
1625 TLO.DAG.getDataLayout().isLittleEndian()) {
1626 unsigned Scale = BitWidth / NumSrcEltBits;
1627 unsigned NumSrcElts = SrcVT.getVectorNumElements();
1628 APInt DemandedSrcBits = APInt::getNullValue(NumSrcEltBits);
1629 APInt DemandedSrcElts = APInt::getNullValue(NumSrcElts);
1630 for (unsigned i = 0; i != Scale; ++i) {
1631 unsigned Offset = i * NumSrcEltBits;
1632 APInt Sub = DemandedBits.extractBits(NumSrcEltBits, Offset);
1633 if (!Sub.isNullValue()) {
1634 DemandedSrcBits |= Sub;
1635 for (unsigned j = 0; j != NumElts; ++j)
1636 if (DemandedElts[j])
1637 DemandedSrcElts.setBit((j * Scale) + i);
1638 }
1639 }
1640
1641 APInt KnownSrcUndef, KnownSrcZero;
1642 if (SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(Src, DemandedSrcElts, KnownSrcUndef,
1643 KnownSrcZero, TLO, Depth + 1))
1644 return true;
1645
1646 KnownBits KnownSrcBits;
1647 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Src, DemandedSrcBits, DemandedSrcElts,
1648 KnownSrcBits, TLO, Depth + 1))
1649 return true;
1650 } else if ((NumSrcEltBits % BitWidth) == 0 &&
1651 TLO.DAG.getDataLayout().isLittleEndian()) {
1652 unsigned Scale = NumSrcEltBits / BitWidth;
1653 unsigned NumSrcElts = SrcVT.isVector() ? SrcVT.getVectorNumElements() : 1;
1654 APInt DemandedSrcBits = APInt::getNullValue(NumSrcEltBits);
1655 APInt DemandedSrcElts = APInt::getNullValue(NumSrcElts);
1656 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i)
1657 if (DemandedElts[i]) {
1658 unsigned Offset = (i % Scale) * BitWidth;
1659 DemandedSrcBits.insertBits(DemandedBits, Offset);
1660 DemandedSrcElts.setBit(i / Scale);
1661 }
1662
1663 if (SrcVT.isVector()) {
1664 APInt KnownSrcUndef, KnownSrcZero;
1665 if (SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(Src, DemandedSrcElts, KnownSrcUndef,
1666 KnownSrcZero, TLO, Depth + 1))
1667 return true;
1668 }
1669
1670 KnownBits KnownSrcBits;
1671 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Src, DemandedSrcBits, DemandedSrcElts,
1672 KnownSrcBits, TLO, Depth + 1))
1673 return true;
1674 }
1675
1676 // If this is a bitcast, let computeKnownBits handle it. Only do this on a
1677 // recursive call where Known may be useful to the caller.
1678 if (Depth > 0) {
1679 Known = TLO.DAG.computeKnownBits(Op, DemandedElts, Depth);
1680 return false;
1681 }
1682 break;
1683 }
1684 case ISD::ADD:
1685 case ISD::MUL:
1686 case ISD::SUB: {
1687 // Add, Sub, and Mul don't demand any bits in positions beyond that
1688 // of the highest bit demanded of them.
1689 SDValue Op0 = Op.getOperand(0), Op1 = Op.getOperand(1);
1690 unsigned DemandedBitsLZ = DemandedBits.countLeadingZeros();
1691 APInt LoMask = APInt::getLowBitsSet(BitWidth, BitWidth - DemandedBitsLZ);
1692 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Op0, LoMask, DemandedElts, Known2, TLO,
1693 Depth + 1) ||
1694 SimplifyDemandedBits(Op1, LoMask, DemandedElts, Known2, TLO,
1695 Depth + 1) ||
1696 // See if the operation should be performed at a smaller bit width.
1697 ShrinkDemandedOp(Op, BitWidth, DemandedBits, TLO)) {
1698 SDNodeFlags Flags = Op.getNode()->getFlags();
1699 if (Flags.hasNoSignedWrap() || Flags.hasNoUnsignedWrap()) {
1700 // Disable the nsw and nuw flags. We can no longer guarantee that we
1701 // won't wrap after simplification.
1702 Flags.setNoSignedWrap(false);
1703 Flags.setNoUnsignedWrap(false);
1704 SDValue NewOp =
1705 TLO.DAG.getNode(Op.getOpcode(), dl, VT, Op0, Op1, Flags);
1706 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, NewOp);
1707 }
1708 return true;
1709 }
1710
1711 // If we have a constant operand, we may be able to turn it into -1 if we
1712 // do not demand the high bits. This can make the constant smaller to
1713 // encode, allow more general folding, or match specialized instruction
1714 // patterns (eg, 'blsr' on x86). Don't bother changing 1 to -1 because that
1715 // is probably not useful (and could be detrimental).
1716 ConstantSDNode *C = isConstOrConstSplat(Op1);
1717 APInt HighMask = APInt::getHighBitsSet(BitWidth, DemandedBitsLZ);
1718 if (C && !C->isAllOnesValue() && !C->isOne() &&
1719 (C->getAPIntValue() | HighMask).isAllOnesValue()) {
1720 SDValue Neg1 = TLO.DAG.getAllOnesConstant(dl, VT);
1721 // We can't guarantee that the new math op doesn't wrap, so explicitly
1722 // clear those flags to prevent folding with a potential existing node
1723 // that has those flags set.
1724 SDNodeFlags Flags;
1725 Flags.setNoSignedWrap(false);
1726 Flags.setNoUnsignedWrap(false);
1727 SDValue NewOp = TLO.DAG.getNode(Op.getOpcode(), dl, VT, Op0, Neg1, Flags);
1728 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, NewOp);
1729 }
1730
1731 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
1732 }
1733 default:
1734 if (Op.getOpcode() >= ISD::BUILTIN_OP_END) {
1735 if (SimplifyDemandedBitsForTargetNode(Op, DemandedBits, DemandedElts,
1736 Known, TLO, Depth))
1737 return true;
1738 break;
1739 }
1740
1741 // Just use computeKnownBits to compute output bits.
1742 Known = TLO.DAG.computeKnownBits(Op, DemandedElts, Depth);
1743 break;
1744 }
1745
1746 // If we know the value of all of the demanded bits, return this as a
1747 // constant.
1748 if (DemandedBits.isSubsetOf(Known.Zero | Known.One)) {
1749 // Avoid folding to a constant if any OpaqueConstant is involved.
1750 const SDNode *N = Op.getNode();
1751 for (SDNodeIterator I = SDNodeIterator::begin(N),
1752 E = SDNodeIterator::end(N);
1753 I != E; ++I) {
1754 SDNode *Op = *I;
1755 if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op))
1756 if (C->isOpaque())
1757 return false;
1758 }
1759 // TODO: Handle float bits as well.
1760 if (VT.isInteger())
1761 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, TLO.DAG.getConstant(Known.One, dl, VT));
1762 }
1763
1764 return false;
1765}
1766
1767bool TargetLowering::SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(SDValue Op,
1768 const APInt &DemandedElts,
1769 APInt &KnownUndef,
1770 APInt &KnownZero,
1771 DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
1772 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
1773 TargetLoweringOpt TLO(DAG, !DCI.isBeforeLegalize(),
1774 !DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps());
1775
1776 bool Simplified =
1777 SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(Op, DemandedElts, KnownUndef, KnownZero, TLO);
1778 if (Simplified) {
1779 DCI.AddToWorklist(Op.getNode());
1780 DCI.CommitTargetLoweringOpt(TLO);
1781 }
1782
1783 return Simplified;
1784}
1785
1786/// Given a vector binary operation and known undefined elements for each input
1787/// operand, compute whether each element of the output is undefined.
1788static APInt getKnownUndefForVectorBinop(SDValue BO, SelectionDAG &DAG,
1789 const APInt &UndefOp0,
1790 const APInt &UndefOp1) {
1791 EVT VT = BO.getValueType();
1792 assert(DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo().isBinOp(BO.getOpcode()) && VT.isVector() &&
1793 "Vector binop only");
1794
1795 EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
1796 unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
1797 assert(UndefOp0.getBitWidth() == NumElts &&
1798 UndefOp1.getBitWidth() == NumElts && "Bad type for undef analysis");
1799
1800 auto getUndefOrConstantElt = [&](SDValue V, unsigned Index,
1801 const APInt &UndefVals) {
1802 if (UndefVals[Index])
1803 return DAG.getUNDEF(EltVT);
1804
1805 if (auto *BV = dyn_cast<BuildVectorSDNode>(V)) {
1806 // Try hard to make sure that the getNode() call is not creating temporary
1807 // nodes. Ignore opaque integers because they do not constant fold.
1808 SDValue Elt = BV->getOperand(Index);
1809 auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Elt);
1810 if (isa<ConstantFPSDNode>(Elt) || Elt.isUndef() || (C && !C->isOpaque()))
1811 return Elt;
1812 }
1813
1814 return SDValue();
1815 };
1816
1817 APInt KnownUndef = APInt::getNullValue(NumElts);
1818 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) {
1819 // If both inputs for this element are either constant or undef and match
1820 // the element type, compute the constant/undef result for this element of
1821 // the vector.
1822 // TODO: Ideally we would use FoldConstantArithmetic() here, but that does
1823 // not handle FP constants. The code within getNode() should be refactored
1824 // to avoid the danger of creating a bogus temporary node here.
1825 SDValue C0 = getUndefOrConstantElt(BO.getOperand(0), i, UndefOp0);
1826 SDValue C1 = getUndefOrConstantElt(BO.getOperand(1), i, UndefOp1);
1827 if (C0 && C1 && C0.getValueType() == EltVT && C1.getValueType() == EltVT)
1828 if (DAG.getNode(BO.getOpcode(), SDLoc(BO), EltVT, C0, C1).isUndef())
1829 KnownUndef.setBit(i);
1830 }
1831 return KnownUndef;
1832}
1833
1834bool TargetLowering::SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(
1835 SDValue Op, const APInt &OriginalDemandedElts, APInt &KnownUndef,
1836 APInt &KnownZero, TargetLoweringOpt &TLO, unsigned Depth,
1837 bool AssumeSingleUse) const {
1838 EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
1839 APInt DemandedElts = OriginalDemandedElts;
1840 unsigned NumElts = DemandedElts.getBitWidth();
1841 assert(VT.isVector() && "Expected vector op");
1842 assert(VT.getVectorNumElements() == NumElts &&
1843 "Mask size mismatches value type element count!");
1844
1845 KnownUndef = KnownZero = APInt::getNullValue(NumElts);
1846
1847 // Undef operand.
1848 if (Op.isUndef()) {
1849 KnownUndef.setAllBits();
1850 return false;
1851 }
1852
1853 // If Op has other users, assume that all elements are needed.
1854 if (!Op.getNode()->hasOneUse() && !AssumeSingleUse)
1855 DemandedElts.setAllBits();
1856
1857 // Not demanding any elements from Op.
1858 if (DemandedElts == 0) {
1859 KnownUndef.setAllBits();
1860 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, TLO.DAG.getUNDEF(VT));
1861 }
1862
1863 // Limit search depth.
1864 if (Depth >= 6)
1865 return false;
1866
1867 SDLoc DL(Op);
1868 unsigned EltSizeInBits = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
1869
1870 switch (Op.getOpcode()) {
1871 case ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR: {
1872 if (!DemandedElts[0]) {
1873 KnownUndef.setAllBits();
1874 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, TLO.DAG.getUNDEF(VT));
1875 }
1876 KnownUndef.setHighBits(NumElts - 1);
1877 break;
1878 }
1879 case ISD::BITCAST: {
1880 SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
1881 EVT SrcVT = Src.getValueType();
1882
1883 // We only handle vectors here.
1884 // TODO - investigate calling SimplifyDemandedBits/ComputeKnownBits?
1885 if (!SrcVT.isVector())
1886 break;
1887
1888 // Fast handling of 'identity' bitcasts.
1889 unsigned NumSrcElts = SrcVT.getVectorNumElements();
1890 if (NumSrcElts == NumElts)
1891 return SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(Src, DemandedElts, KnownUndef,
1892 KnownZero, TLO, Depth + 1);
1893
1894 APInt SrcZero, SrcUndef;
1895 APInt SrcDemandedElts = APInt::getNullValue(NumSrcElts);
1896
1897 // Bitcast from 'large element' src vector to 'small element' vector, we
1898 // must demand a source element if any DemandedElt maps to it.
1899 if ((NumElts % NumSrcElts) == 0) {
1900 unsigned Scale = NumElts / NumSrcElts;
1901 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i)
1902 if (DemandedElts[i])
1903 SrcDemandedElts.setBit(i / Scale);
1904
1905 if (SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(Src, SrcDemandedElts, SrcUndef, SrcZero,
1906 TLO, Depth + 1))
1907 return true;
1908
1909 // Try calling SimplifyDemandedBits, converting demanded elts to the bits
1910 // of the large element.
1911 // TODO - bigendian once we have test coverage.
1912 if (TLO.DAG.getDataLayout().isLittleEndian()) {
1913 unsigned SrcEltSizeInBits = SrcVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
1914 APInt SrcDemandedBits = APInt::getNullValue(SrcEltSizeInBits);
1915 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i)
1916 if (DemandedElts[i]) {
1917 unsigned Ofs = (i % Scale) * EltSizeInBits;
1918 SrcDemandedBits.setBits(Ofs, Ofs + EltSizeInBits);
1919 }
1920
1921 KnownBits Known;
1922 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Src, SrcDemandedBits, Known, TLO, Depth + 1))
1923 return true;
1924 }
1925
1926 // If the src element is zero/undef then all the output elements will be -
1927 // only demanded elements are guaranteed to be correct.
1928 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumSrcElts; ++i) {
1929 if (SrcDemandedElts[i]) {
1930 if (SrcZero[i])
1931 KnownZero.setBits(i * Scale, (i + 1) * Scale);
1932 if (SrcUndef[i])
1933 KnownUndef.setBits(i * Scale, (i + 1) * Scale);
1934 }
1935 }
1936 }
1937
1938 // Bitcast from 'small element' src vector to 'large element' vector, we
1939 // demand all smaller source elements covered by the larger demanded element
1940 // of this vector.
1941 if ((NumSrcElts % NumElts) == 0) {
1942 unsigned Scale = NumSrcElts / NumElts;
1943 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i)
1944 if (DemandedElts[i])
1945 SrcDemandedElts.setBits(i * Scale, (i + 1) * Scale);
1946
1947 if (SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(Src, SrcDemandedElts, SrcUndef, SrcZero,
1948 TLO, Depth + 1))
1949 return true;
1950
1951 // If all the src elements covering an output element are zero/undef, then
1952 // the output element will be as well, assuming it was demanded.
1953 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) {
1954 if (DemandedElts[i]) {
1955 if (SrcZero.extractBits(Scale, i * Scale).isAllOnesValue())
1956 KnownZero.setBit(i);
1957 if (SrcUndef.extractBits(Scale, i * Scale).isAllOnesValue())
1958 KnownUndef.setBit(i);
1959 }
1960 }
1961 }
1962 break;
1963 }
1964 case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR: {
1965 // Check all elements and simplify any unused elements with UNDEF.
1966 if (!DemandedElts.isAllOnesValue()) {
1967 // Don't simplify BROADCASTS.
1968 if (llvm::any_of(Op->op_values(),
1969 [&](SDValue Elt) { return Op.getOperand(0) != Elt; })) {
1970 SmallVector<SDValue, 32> Ops(Op->op_begin(), Op->op_end());
1971 bool Updated = false;
1972 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) {
1973 if (!DemandedElts[i] && !Ops[i].isUndef()) {
1974 Ops[i] = TLO.DAG.getUNDEF(Ops[0].getValueType());
1975 KnownUndef.setBit(i);
1976 Updated = true;
1977 }
1978 }
1979 if (Updated)
1980 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, TLO.DAG.getBuildVector(VT, DL, Ops));
1981 }
1982 }
1983 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) {
1984 SDValue SrcOp = Op.getOperand(i);
1985 if (SrcOp.isUndef()) {
1986 KnownUndef.setBit(i);
1987 } else if (EltSizeInBits == SrcOp.getScalarValueSizeInBits() &&
1988 (isNullConstant(SrcOp) || isNullFPConstant(SrcOp))) {
1989 KnownZero.setBit(i);
1990 }
1991 }
1992 break;
1993 }
1994 case ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS: {
1995 EVT SubVT = Op.getOperand(0).getValueType();
1996 unsigned NumSubVecs = Op.getNumOperands();
1997 unsigned NumSubElts = SubVT.getVectorNumElements();
1998 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumSubVecs; ++i) {
1999 SDValue SubOp = Op.getOperand(i);
2000 APInt SubElts = DemandedElts.extractBits(NumSubElts, i * NumSubElts);
2001 APInt SubUndef, SubZero;
2002 if (SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(SubOp, SubElts, SubUndef, SubZero, TLO,
2003 Depth + 1))
2004 return true;
2005 KnownUndef.insertBits(SubUndef, i * NumSubElts);
2006 KnownZero.insertBits(SubZero, i * NumSubElts);
2007 }
2008 break;
2009 }
2010 case ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR: {
2011 if (!isa<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(2)))
2012 break;
2013 SDValue Base = Op.getOperand(0);
2014 SDValue Sub = Op.getOperand(1);
2015 EVT SubVT = Sub.getValueType();
2016 unsigned NumSubElts = SubVT.getVectorNumElements();
2017 const APInt &Idx = Op.getConstantOperandAPInt(2);
2018 if (Idx.ugt(NumElts - NumSubElts))
2019 break;
2020 unsigned SubIdx = Idx.getZExtValue();
2021 APInt SubElts = DemandedElts.extractBits(NumSubElts, SubIdx);
2022 APInt SubUndef, SubZero;
2023 if (SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(Sub, SubElts, SubUndef, SubZero, TLO,
2024 Depth + 1))
2025 return true;
2026 APInt BaseElts = DemandedElts;
2027 BaseElts.insertBits(APInt::getNullValue(NumSubElts), SubIdx);
2028 if (SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(Base, BaseElts, KnownUndef, KnownZero, TLO,
2029 Depth + 1))
2030 return true;
2031 KnownUndef.insertBits(SubUndef, SubIdx);
2032 KnownZero.insertBits(SubZero, SubIdx);
2033 break;
2034 }
2035 case ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR: {
2036 SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
2037 ConstantSDNode *SubIdx = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1));
2038 unsigned NumSrcElts = Src.getValueType().getVectorNumElements();
2039 if (SubIdx && SubIdx->getAPIntValue().ule(NumSrcElts - NumElts)) {
2040 // Offset the demanded elts by the subvector index.
2041 uint64_t Idx = SubIdx->getZExtValue();
2042 APInt SrcElts = DemandedElts.zextOrSelf(NumSrcElts).shl(Idx);
2043 APInt SrcUndef, SrcZero;
2044 if (SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(Src, SrcElts, SrcUndef, SrcZero, TLO,
2045 Depth + 1))
2046 return true;
2047 KnownUndef = SrcUndef.extractBits(NumElts, Idx);
2048 KnownZero = SrcZero.extractBits(NumElts, Idx);
2049 }
2050 break;
2051 }
2052 case ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT: {
2053 SDValue Vec = Op.getOperand(0);
2054 SDValue Scl = Op.getOperand(1);
2055 auto *CIdx = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(2));
2056
2057 // For a legal, constant insertion index, if we don't need this insertion
2058 // then strip it, else remove it from the demanded elts.
2059 if (CIdx && CIdx->getAPIntValue().ult(NumElts)) {
2060 unsigned Idx = CIdx->getZExtValue();
2061 if (!DemandedElts[Idx])
2062 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, Vec);
2063
2064 APInt DemandedVecElts(DemandedElts);
2065 DemandedVecElts.clearBit(Idx);
2066 if (SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(Vec, DemandedVecElts, KnownUndef,
2067 KnownZero, TLO, Depth + 1))
2068 return true;
2069
2070 KnownUndef.clearBit(Idx);
2071 if (Scl.isUndef())
2072 KnownUndef.setBit(Idx);
2073
2074 KnownZero.clearBit(Idx);
2075 if (isNullConstant(Scl) || isNullFPConstant(Scl))
2076 KnownZero.setBit(Idx);
2077 break;
2078 }
2079
2080 APInt VecUndef, VecZero;
2081 if (SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(Vec, DemandedElts, VecUndef, VecZero, TLO,
2082 Depth + 1))
2083 return true;
2084 // Without knowing the insertion index we can't set KnownUndef/KnownZero.
2085 break;
2086 }
2087 case ISD::VSELECT: {
2088 // Try to transform the select condition based on the current demanded
2089 // elements.
2090 // TODO: If a condition element is undef, we can choose from one arm of the
2091 // select (and if one arm is undef, then we can propagate that to the
2092 // result).
2093 // TODO - add support for constant vselect masks (see IR version of this).
2094 APInt UnusedUndef, UnusedZero;
2095 if (SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, UnusedUndef,
2096 UnusedZero, TLO, Depth + 1))
2097 return true;
2098
2099 // See if we can simplify either vselect operand.
2100 APInt DemandedLHS(DemandedElts);
2101 APInt DemandedRHS(DemandedElts);
2102 APInt UndefLHS, ZeroLHS;
2103 APInt UndefRHS, ZeroRHS;
2104 if (SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedLHS, UndefLHS,
2105 ZeroLHS, TLO, Depth + 1))
2106 return true;
2107 if (SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(Op.getOperand(2), DemandedRHS, UndefRHS,
2108 ZeroRHS, TLO, Depth + 1))
2109 return true;
2110
2111 KnownUndef = UndefLHS & UndefRHS;
2112 KnownZero = ZeroLHS & ZeroRHS;
2113 break;
2114 }
2115 case ISD::VECTOR_SHUFFLE: {
2116 ArrayRef<int> ShuffleMask = cast<ShuffleVectorSDNode>(Op)->getMask();
2117
2118 // Collect demanded elements from shuffle operands..
2119 APInt DemandedLHS(NumElts, 0);
2120 APInt DemandedRHS(NumElts, 0);
2121 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) {
2122 int M = ShuffleMask[i];
2123 if (M < 0 || !DemandedElts[i])
2124 continue;
2125 assert(0 <= M && M < (int)(2 * NumElts) && "Shuffle index out of range");
2126 if (M < (int)NumElts)
2127 DemandedLHS.setBit(M);
2128 else
2129 DemandedRHS.setBit(M - NumElts);
2130 }
2131
2132 // See if we can simplify either shuffle operand.
2133 APInt UndefLHS, ZeroLHS;
2134 APInt UndefRHS, ZeroRHS;
2135 if (SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedLHS, UndefLHS,
2136 ZeroLHS, TLO, Depth + 1))
2137 return true;
2138 if (SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedRHS, UndefRHS,
2139 ZeroRHS, TLO, Depth + 1))
2140 return true;
2141
2142 // Simplify mask using undef elements from LHS/RHS.
2143 bool Updated = false;
2144 bool IdentityLHS = true, IdentityRHS = true;
2145 SmallVector<int, 32> NewMask(ShuffleMask.begin(), ShuffleMask.end());
2146 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) {
2147 int &M = NewMask[i];
2148 if (M < 0)
2149 continue;
2150 if (!DemandedElts[i] || (M < (int)NumElts && UndefLHS[M]) ||
2151 (M >= (int)NumElts && UndefRHS[M - NumElts])) {
2152 Updated = true;
2153 M = -1;
2154 }
2155 IdentityLHS &= (M < 0) || (M == (int)i);
2156 IdentityRHS &= (M < 0) || ((M - NumElts) == i);
2157 }
2158
2159 // Update legal shuffle masks based on demanded elements if it won't reduce
2160 // to Identity which can cause premature removal of the shuffle mask.
2161 if (Updated && !IdentityLHS && !IdentityRHS && !TLO.LegalOps &&
2162 isShuffleMaskLegal(NewMask, VT))
2163 return TLO.CombineTo(Op,
2164 TLO.DAG.getVectorShuffle(VT, DL, Op.getOperand(0),
2165 Op.getOperand(1), NewMask));
2166
2167 // Propagate undef/zero elements from LHS/RHS.
2168 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) {
2169 int M = ShuffleMask[i];
2170 if (M < 0) {
2171 KnownUndef.setBit(i);
2172 } else if (M < (int)NumElts) {
2173 if (UndefLHS[M])
2174 KnownUndef.setBit(i);
2175 if (ZeroLHS[M])
2176 KnownZero.setBit(i);
2177 } else {
2178 if (UndefRHS[M - NumElts])
2179 KnownUndef.setBit(i);
2180 if (ZeroRHS[M - NumElts])
2181 KnownZero.setBit(i);
2182 }
2183 }
2184 break;
2185 }
2186 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
2187 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG: {
2188 APInt SrcUndef, SrcZero;
2189 SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
2190 unsigned NumSrcElts = Src.getValueType().getVectorNumElements();
2191 APInt DemandedSrcElts = DemandedElts.zextOrSelf(NumSrcElts);
2192 if (SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(Src, DemandedSrcElts, SrcUndef, SrcZero, TLO,
2193 Depth + 1))
2194 return true;
2195 KnownZero = SrcZero.zextOrTrunc(NumElts);
2196 KnownUndef = SrcUndef.zextOrTrunc(NumElts);
2197
2198 if (Op.getOpcode() == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG) {
2199 // zext(undef) upper bits are guaranteed to be zero.
2200 if (DemandedElts.isSubsetOf(KnownUndef))
2201 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, TLO.DAG.getConstant(0, SDLoc(Op), VT));
2202 KnownUndef.clearAllBits();
2203 }
2204 break;
2205 }
2206
2207 // TODO: There are more binop opcodes that could be handled here - MUL, MIN,
2208 // MAX, saturated math, etc.
2209 case ISD::OR:
2210 case ISD::XOR:
2211 case ISD::ADD:
2212 case ISD::SUB:
2213 case ISD::FADD:
2214 case ISD::FSUB:
2215 case ISD::FMUL:
2216 case ISD::FDIV:
2217 case ISD::FREM: {
2218 APInt UndefRHS, ZeroRHS;
2219 if (SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, UndefRHS,
2220 ZeroRHS, TLO, Depth + 1))
2221 return true;
2222 APInt UndefLHS, ZeroLHS;
2223 if (SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, UndefLHS,
2224 ZeroLHS, TLO, Depth + 1))
2225 return true;
2226
2227 KnownZero = ZeroLHS & ZeroRHS;
2228 KnownUndef = getKnownUndefForVectorBinop(Op, TLO.DAG, UndefLHS, UndefRHS);
2229 break;
2230 }
2231 case ISD::AND: {
2232 APInt SrcUndef, SrcZero;
2233 if (SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, SrcUndef,
2234 SrcZero, TLO, Depth + 1))
2235 return true;
2236 if (SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, KnownUndef,
2237 KnownZero, TLO, Depth + 1))
2238 return true;
2239
2240 // If either side has a zero element, then the result element is zero, even
2241 // if the other is an UNDEF.
2242 // TODO: Extend getKnownUndefForVectorBinop to also deal with known zeros
2243 // and then handle 'and' nodes with the rest of the binop opcodes.
2244 KnownZero |= SrcZero;
2245 KnownUndef &= SrcUndef;
2246 KnownUndef &= ~KnownZero;
2247 break;
2248 }
2249 case ISD::TRUNCATE:
2250 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND:
2251 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
2252 if (SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, KnownUndef,
2253 KnownZero, TLO, Depth + 1))
2254 return true;
2255
2256 if (Op.getOpcode() == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND) {
2257 // zext(undef) upper bits are guaranteed to be zero.
2258 if (DemandedElts.isSubsetOf(KnownUndef))
2259 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, TLO.DAG.getConstant(0, SDLoc(Op), VT));
2260 KnownUndef.clearAllBits();
2261 }
2262 break;
2263 default: {
2264 if (Op.getOpcode() >= ISD::BUILTIN_OP_END) {
2265 if (SimplifyDemandedVectorEltsForTargetNode(Op, DemandedElts, KnownUndef,
2266 KnownZero, TLO, Depth))
2267 return true;
2268 } else {
2269 KnownBits Known;
2270 APInt DemandedBits = APInt::getAllOnesValue(EltSizeInBits);
2271 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(Op, DemandedBits, OriginalDemandedElts, Known,
2272 TLO, Depth, AssumeSingleUse))
2273 return true;
2274 }
2275 break;
2276 }
2277 }
2278 assert((KnownUndef & KnownZero) == 0 && "Elements flagged as undef AND zero");
2279
2280 // Constant fold all undef cases.
2281 // TODO: Handle zero cases as well.
2282 if (DemandedElts.isSubsetOf(KnownUndef))
2283 return TLO.CombineTo(Op, TLO.DAG.getUNDEF(VT));
2284
2285 return false;
2286}
2287
2288/// Determine which of the bits specified in Mask are known to be either zero or
2289/// one and return them in the Known.
2290void TargetLowering::computeKnownBitsForTargetNode(const SDValue Op,
2291 KnownBits &Known,
2292 const APInt &DemandedElts,
2293 const SelectionDAG &DAG,
2294 unsigned Depth) const {
2295 assert((Op.getOpcode() >= ISD::BUILTIN_OP_END ||
2296 Op.getOpcode() == ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN ||
2297 Op.getOpcode() == ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN ||
2298 Op.getOpcode() == ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID) &&
2299 "Should use MaskedValueIsZero if you don't know whether Op"
2300 " is a target node!");
2301 Known.resetAll();
2302}
2303
2304void TargetLowering::computeKnownBitsForFrameIndex(const SDValue Op,
2305 KnownBits &Known,
2306 const APInt &DemandedElts,
2307 const SelectionDAG &DAG,
2308 unsigned Depth) const {
2309 assert(isa<FrameIndexSDNode>(Op) && "expected FrameIndex");
2310
2311 if (unsigned Align = DAG.InferPtrAlignment(Op)) {
2312 // The low bits are known zero if the pointer is aligned.
2313 Known.Zero.setLowBits(Log2_32(Align));
2314 }
2315}

2317/// This method can be implemented by targets that want to expose additional
2318/// information about sign bits to the DAG Combiner.
2319unsigned TargetLowering::ComputeNumSignBitsForTargetNode(SDValue Op,
2320 const APInt &,
2321 const SelectionDAG &,
2322 unsigned Depth) const {
2323 assert((Op.getOpcode() >= ISD::BUILTIN_OP_END ||
2324 Op.getOpcode() == ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN ||
2325 Op.getOpcode() == ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN ||
2326 Op.getOpcode() == ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID) &&
2327 "Should use ComputeNumSignBits if you don't know whether Op"
2328 " is a target node!");
2329 return 1;
2330}

2339 "Should use SimplifyDemandedVectorElts if you don't know whether Op"

2344bool TargetLowering::SimplifyDemandedBitsForTargetNode(

2349 Op.getOpcode() == ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN ||
2350 Op.getOpcode() == ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID) &&

2364 unsigned Depth) const {
