2374// FIXME: Ideally, this would use ISD::isConstantSplatVector(), but that must
2375// work with truncating build vectors and vectors with elements of less than
2376// 8 bits.
2377bool TargetLowering::isConstTrueVal(const SDNode *N) const {
2378 if (!N)
2379 return false;
2380
2381 APInt CVal;
2382 if (auto *CN = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N)) {
2383 CVal = CN->getAPIntValue();
2384 } else if (auto *BV = dyn_cast<BuildVectorSDNode>(N)) {
2385 auto *CN = BV->getConstantSplatNode();
2386 if (!CN)
2387 return false;
2388
2389 // If this is a truncating build vector, truncate the splat value.
2390 // Otherwise, we may fail to match the expected values below.
2391 unsigned BVEltWidth = BV->getValueType(0).getScalarSizeInBits();
2392 CVal = CN->getAPIntValue();
2393 if (BVEltWidth < CVal.getBitWidth())
2394 CVal = CVal.trunc(BVEltWidth);
2395 } else {
2396 return false;
2397 }
2398
2399 switch (getBooleanContents(N->getValueType(0))) {
2400 case UndefinedBooleanContent:
2401 return CVal[0];
2402 case ZeroOrOneBooleanContent:
2403 return CVal.isOneValue();
2404 case ZeroOrNegativeOneBooleanContent:
2405 return CVal.isAllOnesValue();
2406 }
2407
2408 llvm_unreachable("Invalid boolean contents");
2409}
2410
2411bool TargetLowering::isConstFalseVal(const SDNode *N) const {
2412 if (!N)
2413 return false;
2414
2415 const ConstantSDNode *CN = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N);
2416 if (!CN) {
2417 const BuildVectorSDNode *BV = dyn_cast<BuildVectorSDNode>(N);
2418 if (!BV)
2419 return false;
2420
2421 // Only interested in constant splats, we don't care about undef
2422 // elements in identifying boolean constants and getConstantSplatNode
2423 // returns NULL if all ops are undef;
2424 CN = BV->getConstantSplatNode();
2425 if (!CN)
2426 return false;
2427 }
2428
2429 if (getBooleanContents(N->getValueType(0)) == UndefinedBooleanContent)
2430 return !CN->getAPIntValue()[0];
2431
2432 return CN->isNullValue();
2433}
2434
2435bool TargetLowering::isExtendedTrueVal(const ConstantSDNode *N, EVT VT,
2436 bool SExt) const {
2437 if (VT == MVT::i1)
2438 return N->isOne();
2439
2440 TargetLowering::BooleanContent Cnt = getBooleanContents(VT);
2441 switch (Cnt) {
2442 case TargetLowering::ZeroOrOneBooleanContent:
2443 // An extended value of 1 is always true, unless its original type is i1,
2444 // in which case it will be sign extended to -1.
2445 return (N->isOne() && !SExt) || (SExt && (N->getValueType(0) != MVT::i1));
2446 case TargetLowering::UndefinedBooleanContent:
2447 case TargetLowering::ZeroOrNegativeOneBooleanContent:
2448 return N->isAllOnesValue() && SExt;
2449 }
2450 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected enumeration.");
2451}
2452
2453/// This helper function of SimplifySetCC tries to optimize the comparison when
2454/// either operand of the SetCC node is a bitwise-and instruction.
2455SDValue TargetLowering::foldSetCCWithAnd(EVT VT, SDValue N0, SDValue N1,
2456 ISD::CondCode Cond, const SDLoc &DL,
2457 DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
2458 // Match these patterns in any of their permutations:
2459 // (X & Y) == Y
2460 // (X & Y) != Y
2461 if (N1.getOpcode() == ISD::AND && N0.getOpcode() != ISD::AND)
2462 std::swap(N0, N1);
2463
2464 EVT OpVT = N0.getValueType();
2465 if (N0.getOpcode() != ISD::AND || !OpVT.isInteger() ||
2466 (Cond != ISD::SETEQ && Cond != ISD::SETNE))
2467 return SDValue();
2468
2469 SDValue X, Y;
2470 if (N0.getOperand(0) == N1) {
2471 X = N0.getOperand(1);
2472 Y = N0.getOperand(0);
2473 } else if (N0.getOperand(1) == N1) {
2474 X = N0.getOperand(0);
2475 Y = N0.getOperand(1);
2476 } else {
2477 return SDValue();
2478 }
2479
2480 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
2481 SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, OpVT);
2482 if (DAG.isKnownToBeAPowerOfTwo(Y)) {
2483 // Simplify X & Y == Y to X & Y != 0 if Y has exactly one bit set.
2484 // Note that where Y is variable and is known to have at most one bit set
2485 // (for example, if it is Z & 1) we cannot do this; the expressions are not
2486 // equivalent when Y == 0.
2487 assert(VT.isInteger());
2488 Cond = ISD::getSetCCInverse(Cond, VT);
2489 if (DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps() ||
2490 isCondCodeLegal(Cond, N0.getSimpleValueType()))
2491 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, VT, N0, Zero, Cond);
2492 } else if (N0.hasOneUse() && hasAndNotCompare(Y)) {
2493 // If the target supports an 'and-not' or 'and-complement' logic operation,
2494 // try to use that to make a comparison operation more efficient.
2495 // But don't do this transform if the mask is a single bit because there are
2496 // more efficient ways to deal with that case (for example, 'bt' on x86 or
2497 // 'rlwinm' on PPC).
2498
2499 // Bail out if the compare operand that we want to turn into a zero is
2500 // already a zero (otherwise, infinite loop).
2501 auto *YConst = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Y);
2502 if (YConst && YConst->isNullValue())
2503 return SDValue();
2504
2505 // Transform this into: ~X & Y == 0.
2506 SDValue NotX = DAG.getNOT(SDLoc(X), X, OpVT);
2507 SDValue NewAnd = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, SDLoc(N0), OpVT, NotX, Y);
2508 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, VT, NewAnd, Zero, Cond);
2509 }
2510
2511 return SDValue();
2512}
2513
2514/// There are multiple IR patterns that could be checking whether certain
2515/// truncation of a signed number would be lossy or not. The pattern which is
2516/// best at IR level, may not lower optimally. Thus, we want to unfold it.
2517/// We are looking for the following pattern: (KeptBits is a constant)
2518/// (add %x, (1 << (KeptBits-1))) srccond (1 << KeptBits)
2519/// KeptBits won't be bitwidth(x), that will be constant-folded to true/false.
2520/// KeptBits also can't be 1, that would have been folded to %x dstcond 0
2521/// We will unfold it into the natural trunc+sext pattern:
2522/// ((%x << C) a>> C) dstcond %x
2523/// Where C = bitwidth(x) - KeptBits and C u< bitwidth(x)
2524SDValue TargetLowering::optimizeSetCCOfSignedTruncationCheck(
2525 EVT SCCVT, SDValue N0, SDValue N1, ISD::CondCode Cond, DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
2526 const SDLoc &DL) const {
2527 // We must be comparing with a constant.
2528 ConstantSDNode *C1;
2529 if (!(C1 = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N1)))
2530 return SDValue();
2531
2532 // N0 should be: add %x, (1 << (KeptBits-1))
2533 if (N0->getOpcode() != ISD::ADD)
2534 return SDValue();
2535
2536 // And we must be 'add'ing a constant.
2537 ConstantSDNode *C01;
2538 if (!(C01 = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N0->getOperand(1))))
2539 return SDValue();
2540
2541 SDValue X = N0->getOperand(0);
2542 EVT XVT = X.getValueType();
2543
2544 // Validate constants ...
2545
2546 APInt I1 = C1->getAPIntValue();
2547
2548 ISD::CondCode NewCond;
2549 if (Cond == ISD::CondCode::SETULT) {
2550 NewCond = ISD::CondCode::SETEQ;
2551 } else if (Cond == ISD::CondCode::SETULE) {
2552 NewCond = ISD::CondCode::SETEQ;
2553 // But need to 'canonicalize' the constant.
2554 I1 += 1;
2555 } else if (Cond == ISD::CondCode::SETUGT) {
2556 NewCond = ISD::CondCode::SETNE;
2557 // But need to 'canonicalize' the constant.
2558 I1 += 1;
2559 } else if (Cond == ISD::CondCode::SETUGE) {
2560 NewCond = ISD::CondCode::SETNE;
2561 } else
2562 return SDValue();
2563
2564 APInt I01 = C01->getAPIntValue();
2565
2566 auto checkConstants = [&I1, &I01]() -> bool {
2567 // Both of them must be power-of-two, and the constant from setcc is bigger.
2568 return I1.ugt(I01) && I1.isPowerOf2() && I01.isPowerOf2();
2569 };
2570
2571 if (checkConstants()) {
2572 // Great, e.g. got icmp ult i16 (add i16 %x, 128), 256
2573 } else {
2574 // What if we invert constants? (and the target predicate)
2575 I1.negate();
2576 I01.negate();
2577 NewCond = getSetCCInverse(NewCond, /*isInteger=*/MVT::i64);
2578 if (!checkConstants())
2579 return SDValue();
2580 // Great, e.g. got icmp uge i16 (add i16 %x, -128), -256
2581 }
2582
2583 // They are power-of-two, so which bit is set?
2584 const unsigned KeptBits = I1.logBase2();
2585 const unsigned KeptBitsMinusOne = I01.logBase2();
2586
2587 // Magic!
2588 if (KeptBits != (KeptBitsMinusOne + 1))
2589 return SDValue();
2590 assert(KeptBits > 0 && KeptBits < XVT.getSizeInBits() && "unreachable");
2591
2592 // We don't want to do this in every single case.
2593 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
2594 if (!DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo().shouldTransformSignedTruncationCheck(
2595 XVT, KeptBits))
2596 return SDValue();
2597
2598 const unsigned MaskedBits = XVT.getSizeInBits() - KeptBits;
2599 assert(MaskedBits > 0 && MaskedBits < XVT.getSizeInBits() && "unreachable");
2600
2601 // Unfold into: ((%x << C) a>> C) cond %x
2602 // Where 'cond' will be either 'eq' or 'ne'.
2603 SDValue ShiftAmt = DAG.getConstant(MaskedBits, DL, XVT);
2604 SDValue T0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, XVT, X, ShiftAmt);
2605 SDValue T1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, DL, XVT, T0, ShiftAmt);
2606 SDValue T2 = DAG.getSetCC(DL, SCCVT, T1, X, NewCond);
2607
2608 return T2;
2609}
2610
2611/// Try to fold an equality comparison with a {add/sub/xor} binary operation as
2612/// the 1st operand (N0). Callers are expected to swap the N0/N1 parameters to
2613/// handle the commuted versions of these patterns.
2614SDValue TargetLowering::foldSetCCWithBinOp(EVT VT, SDValue N0, SDValue N1,
2615 ISD::CondCode Cond, const SDLoc &DL,
2616 DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
2617 unsigned BOpcode = N0.getOpcode();
2618 assert((BOpcode == ISD::ADD || BOpcode == ISD::SUB || BOpcode == ISD::XOR) &&
2619 "Unexpected binop");
2620 assert((Cond == ISD::SETEQ || Cond == ISD::SETNE) && "Unexpected condcode");
2621
2622 // (X + Y) == X --> Y == 0
2623 // (X - Y) == X --> Y == 0
2624 // (X ^ Y) == X --> Y == 0
2625 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
2626 EVT OpVT = N0.getValueType();
2627 SDValue X = N0.getOperand(0);
2628 SDValue Y = N0.getOperand(1);
2629 if (X == N1)
2630 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, VT, Y, DAG.getConstant(0, DL, OpVT), Cond);
2631
2632 if (Y != N1)
2633 return SDValue();
2634
2635 // (X + Y) == Y --> X == 0
2636 // (X ^ Y) == Y --> X == 0
2637 if (BOpcode == ISD::ADD || BOpcode == ISD::XOR)
2638 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, VT, X, DAG.getConstant(0, DL, OpVT), Cond);
2639
2640 // The shift would not be valid if the operands are boolean (i1).
2641 if (!N0.hasOneUse() || OpVT.getScalarSizeInBits() == 1)
2642 return SDValue();
2643
2644 // (X - Y) == Y --> X == Y << 1
2645 EVT ShiftVT = getShiftAmountTy(OpVT, DAG.getDataLayout(),
2646 !DCI.isBeforeLegalize());
2647 SDValue One = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, ShiftVT);
2648 SDValue YShl1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, N1.getValueType(), Y, One);
2649 if (!DCI.isCalledByLegalizer())
2650 DCI.AddToWorklist(YShl1.getNode());
2651 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, VT, X, YShl1, Cond);
2652}
2653
2654/// Try to simplify a setcc built with the specified operands and cc. If it is
2655/// unable to simplify it, return a null SDValue.
2656SDValue TargetLowering::SimplifySetCC(EVT VT, SDValue N0, SDValue N1,
2657 ISD::CondCode Cond, bool foldBooleans,
2658 DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
2659 const SDLoc &dl) const {
2660 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
2661 EVT OpVT = N0.getValueType();
2662
2663 // Constant fold or commute setcc.
2664 if (SDValue Fold = DAG.FoldSetCC(VT, N0, N1, Cond, dl))
2665 return Fold;
2666
2667 // Ensure that the constant occurs on the RHS and fold constant comparisons.
2668 // TODO: Handle non-splat vector constants. All undef causes trouble.
2669 ISD::CondCode SwappedCC = ISD::getSetCCSwappedOperands(Cond);
2670 if (isConstOrConstSplat(N0) &&
2671 (DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps() ||
2672 isCondCodeLegal(SwappedCC, N0.getSimpleValueType())))
2673 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N1, N0, SwappedCC);
2674
2675 if (auto *N1C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N1.getNode())) {
2676 const APInt &C1 = N1C->getAPIntValue();
2677
2678 // If the LHS is '(srl (ctlz x), 5)', the RHS is 0/1, and this is an
2679 // equality comparison, then we're just comparing whether X itself is
2680 // zero.
2681 if (N0.getOpcode() == ISD::SRL && (C1.isNullValue() || C1.isOneValue()) &&
2682 N0.getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::CTLZ &&
2683 N0.getOperand(1).getOpcode() == ISD::Constant) {
2684 const APInt &ShAmt = N0.getConstantOperandAPInt(1);
2685 if ((Cond == ISD::SETEQ || Cond == ISD::SETNE) &&
2686 ShAmt == Log2_32(N0.getValueSizeInBits())) {
2687 if ((C1 == 0) == (Cond == ISD::SETEQ)) {
2688 // (srl (ctlz x), 5) == 0 -> X != 0
2689 // (srl (ctlz x), 5) != 1 -> X != 0
2690 Cond = ISD::SETNE;
2691 } else {
2692 // (srl (ctlz x), 5) != 0 -> X == 0
2693 // (srl (ctlz x), 5) == 1 -> X == 0
2694 Cond = ISD::SETEQ;
2695 }
2696 SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, N0.getValueType());
2697 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0.getOperand(0).getOperand(0),
2698 Zero, Cond);
2699 }
2700 }
2701
2702 SDValue CTPOP = N0;
2703 // Look through truncs that don't change the value of a ctpop.
2704 if (N0.hasOneUse() && N0.getOpcode() == ISD::TRUNCATE)
2705 CTPOP = N0.getOperand(0);
2706
2707 if (CTPOP.hasOneUse() && CTPOP.getOpcode() == ISD::CTPOP &&
2708 (N0 == CTPOP ||
2709 N0.getValueSizeInBits() > Log2_32_Ceil(CTPOP.getValueSizeInBits()))) {
2710 EVT CTVT = CTPOP.getValueType();
2711 SDValue CTOp = CTPOP.getOperand(0);
2712
2713 // (ctpop x) u< 2 -> (x & x-1) == 0
2714 // (ctpop x) u> 1 -> (x & x-1) != 0
2715 if ((Cond == ISD::SETULT && C1 == 2) || (Cond == ISD::SETUGT && C1 == 1)){
2716 SDValue Sub = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, CTVT, CTOp,
2717 DAG.getConstant(1, dl, CTVT));
2718 SDValue And = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, CTVT, CTOp, Sub);
2719 ISD::CondCode CC = Cond == ISD::SETULT ? ISD::SETEQ : ISD::SETNE;
2720 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, And, DAG.getConstant(0, dl, CTVT), CC);
2721 }
2722
2723 // (ctpop x) == 1 -> x && (x & x-1) == 0 iff ctpop is illegal.
2724 if (Cond == ISD::SETEQ && C1 == 1 &&
2725 !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::CTPOP, CTVT)) {
2726 SDValue Sub =
2727 DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, CTVT, CTOp, DAG.getConstant(1, dl, CTVT));
2728 SDValue And = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, CTVT, CTOp, Sub);
2729 SDValue LHS = DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, CTOp, DAG.getConstant(0, dl, CTVT),
2730 ISD::SETUGT);
2731 SDValue RHS =
2732 DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, And, DAG.getConstant(0, dl, CTVT), ISD::SETEQ);
2733 return DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, LHS, RHS);
2734 }
2735 }
2736
2737 // (zext x) == C --> x == (trunc C)
2738 // (sext x) == C --> x == (trunc C)
2739 if ((Cond == ISD::SETEQ || Cond == ISD::SETNE) &&
2740 DCI.isBeforeLegalize() && N0->hasOneUse()) {
2741 unsigned MinBits = N0.getValueSizeInBits();
2742 SDValue PreExt;
2743 bool Signed = false;
2744 if (N0->getOpcode() == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND) {
2745 // ZExt
2746 MinBits = N0->getOperand(0).getValueSizeInBits();
2747 PreExt = N0->getOperand(0);
2748 } else if (N0->getOpcode() == ISD::AND) {
2749 // DAGCombine turns costly ZExts into ANDs
2750 if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N0->getOperand(1)))
2751 if ((C->getAPIntValue()+1).isPowerOf2()) {
2752 MinBits = C->getAPIntValue().countTrailingOnes();
2753 PreExt = N0->getOperand(0);
2754 }
2755 } else if (N0->getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND) {
2756 // SExt
2757 MinBits = N0->getOperand(0).getValueSizeInBits();
2758 PreExt = N0->getOperand(0);
2759 Signed = true;
2760 } else if (auto *LN0 = dyn_cast<LoadSDNode>(N0)) {
2761 // ZEXTLOAD / SEXTLOAD
2762 if (LN0->getExtensionType() == ISD::ZEXTLOAD) {
2763 MinBits = LN0->getMemoryVT().getSizeInBits();
2764 PreExt = N0;
2765 } else if (LN0->getExtensionType() == ISD::SEXTLOAD) {
2766 Signed = true;
2767 MinBits = LN0->getMemoryVT().getSizeInBits();
2768 PreExt = N0;
2769 }
2770 }
2771
2772 // Figure out how many bits we need to preserve this constant.
2773 unsigned ReqdBits = Signed ?
2774 C1.getBitWidth() - C1.getNumSignBits() + 1 :
2775 C1.getActiveBits();
2776
2777 // Make sure we're not losing bits from the constant.
2778 if (MinBits > 0 &&
2779 MinBits < C1.getBitWidth() &&
2780 MinBits >= ReqdBits) {
2781 EVT MinVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), MinBits);
2782 if (isTypeDesirableForOp(ISD::SETCC, MinVT)) {
2783 // Will get folded away.
2784 SDValue Trunc = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, MinVT, PreExt);
2785 if (MinBits == 1 && C1 == 1)
2786 // Invert the condition.
2787 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, Trunc, DAG.getConstant(0, dl, MVT::i1),
2788 Cond == ISD::SETEQ ? ISD::SETNE : ISD::SETEQ);
2789 SDValue C = DAG.getConstant(C1.trunc(MinBits), dl, MinVT);
2790 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, Trunc, C, Cond);
2791 }
2792
2793 // If truncating the setcc operands is not desirable, we can still
2794 // simplify the expression in some cases:
2795 // setcc ([sz]ext (setcc x, y, cc)), 0, setne) -> setcc (x, y, cc)
2796 // setcc ([sz]ext (setcc x, y, cc)), 0, seteq) -> setcc (x, y, inv(cc))
2797 // setcc (zext (setcc x, y, cc)), 1, setne) -> setcc (x, y, inv(cc))
2798 // setcc (zext (setcc x, y, cc)), 1, seteq) -> setcc (x, y, cc)
2799 // setcc (sext (setcc x, y, cc)), -1, setne) -> setcc (x, y, inv(cc))
2800 // setcc (sext (setcc x, y, cc)), -1, seteq) -> setcc (x, y, cc)
2801 SDValue TopSetCC = N0->getOperand(0);
2802 unsigned N0Opc = N0->getOpcode();
2803 bool SExt = (N0Opc == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND);
2804 if (TopSetCC.getValueType() == MVT::i1 && VT == MVT::i1 &&
2805 TopSetCC.getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC &&
2806 (N0Opc == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND || N0Opc == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND) &&
2807 (isConstFalseVal(N1C) ||
2808 isExtendedTrueVal(N1C, N0->getValueType(0), SExt))) {
2809
2810 bool Inverse = (N1C->isNullValue() && Cond == ISD::SETEQ) ||
2811 (!N1C->isNullValue() && Cond == ISD::SETNE);
2812
2813 if (!Inverse)
2814 return TopSetCC;
2815
2816 ISD::CondCode InvCond = ISD::getSetCCInverse(
2817 cast<CondCodeSDNode>(TopSetCC.getOperand(2))->get(),
2818 TopSetCC.getOperand(0).getValueType());
2819 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, TopSetCC.getOperand(0),
2820 TopSetCC.getOperand(1),
2821 InvCond);
2822 }
2823 }
2824 }
2825
2826 // If the LHS is '(and load, const)', the RHS is 0, the test is for
2827 // equality or unsigned, and all 1 bits of the const are in the same
2828 // partial word, see if we can shorten the load.
2829 if (DCI.isBeforeLegalize() &&
2830 !ISD::isSignedIntSetCC(Cond) &&
2831 N0.getOpcode() == ISD::AND && C1 == 0 &&
2832 N0.getNode()->hasOneUse() &&
2833 isa<LoadSDNode>(N0.getOperand(0)) &&
2834 N0.getOperand(0).getNode()->hasOneUse() &&
2835 isa<ConstantSDNode>(N0.getOperand(1))) {
2836 LoadSDNode *Lod = cast<LoadSDNode>(N0.getOperand(0));
2837 APInt bestMask;
2838 unsigned bestWidth = 0, bestOffset = 0;
2839 if (!Lod->isVolatile() && Lod->isUnindexed()) {
2840 unsigned origWidth = N0.getValueSizeInBits();
2841 unsigned maskWidth = origWidth;
2842 // We can narrow (e.g.) 16-bit extending loads on 32-bit target to
2843 // 8 bits, but have to be careful...
2844 if (Lod->getExtensionType() != ISD::NON_EXTLOAD)
2845 origWidth = Lod->getMemoryVT().getSizeInBits();
2846 const APInt &Mask = N0.getConstantOperandAPInt(1);
2847 for (unsigned width = origWidth / 2; width>=8; width /= 2) {
2848 APInt newMask = APInt::getLowBitsSet(maskWidth, width);
2849 for (unsigned offset=0; offset<origWidth/width; offset++) {
2850 if (Mask.isSubsetOf(newMask)) {
2851 if (DAG.getDataLayout().isLittleEndian())
2852 bestOffset = (uint64_t)offset * (width/8);
2853 else
2854 bestOffset = (origWidth/width - offset - 1) * (width/8);
2855 bestMask = Mask.lshr(offset * (width/8) * 8);
2856 bestWidth = width;
2857 break;
2858 }
2859 newMask <<= width;
2860 }
2861 }
2862 }
2863 if (bestWidth) {
2864 EVT newVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), bestWidth);
2865 if (newVT.isRound() &&
2866 shouldReduceLoadWidth(Lod, ISD::NON_EXTLOAD, newVT)) {
2867 SDValue Ptr = Lod->getBasePtr();
2868 if (bestOffset != 0)
2869 Ptr = DAG.getPointerAdd(dl, Ptr, bestOffset);
2870 unsigned NewAlign = MinAlign(Lod->getAlignment(), bestOffset);
2871 SDValue NewLoad = DAG.getLoad(
2872 newVT, dl, Lod->getChain(), Ptr,
2873 Lod->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(bestOffset), NewAlign);
2874 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT,
2875 DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, newVT, NewLoad,
2876 DAG.getConstant(bestMask.trunc(bestWidth),
2877 dl, newVT)),
2878 DAG.getConstant(0LL, dl, newVT), Cond);
2879 }
2880 }
2881 }
2882
2883 // If the LHS is a ZERO_EXTEND, perform the comparison on the input.
2884 if (N0.getOpcode() == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND) {
2885 unsigned InSize = N0.getOperand(0).getValueSizeInBits();
2886
2887 // If the comparison constant has bits in the upper part, the
2888 // zero-extended value could never match.
2889 if (C1.intersects(APInt::getHighBitsSet(C1.getBitWidth(),
2890 C1.getBitWidth() - InSize))) {
2891 switch (Cond) {
2892 case ISD::SETUGT:
2893 case ISD::SETUGE:
2894 case ISD::SETEQ:
2895 return DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT);
2896 case ISD::SETULT:
2897 case ISD::SETULE:
2898 case ISD::SETNE:
2899 return DAG.getConstant(1, dl, VT);
2900 case ISD::SETGT:
2901 case ISD::SETGE:
2902 // True if the sign bit of C1 is set.
2903 return DAG.getConstant(C1.isNegative(), dl, VT);
2904 case ISD::SETLT:
2905 case ISD::SETLE:
2906 // True if the sign bit of C1 isn't set.
2907 return DAG.getConstant(C1.isNonNegative(), dl, VT);
2908 default:
2909 break;
2910 }
2911 }
2912
2913 // Otherwise, we can perform the comparison with the low bits.
2914 switch (Cond) {
2915 case ISD::SETEQ:
2916 case ISD::SETNE:
2917 case ISD::SETUGT:
2918 case ISD::SETUGE:
2919 case ISD::SETULT:
2920 case ISD::SETULE: {
2921 EVT newVT = N0.getOperand(0).getValueType();
2922 if (DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps() ||
2923 (isOperationLegal(ISD::SETCC, newVT) &&
2924 isCondCodeLegal(Cond, newVT.getSimpleVT()))) {
2925 EVT NewSetCCVT =
2926 getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), newVT);
2927 SDValue NewConst = DAG.getConstant(C1.trunc(InSize), dl, newVT);
2928
2929 SDValue NewSetCC = DAG.getSetCC(dl, NewSetCCVT, N0.getOperand(0),
2930 NewConst, Cond);
2931 return DAG.getBoolExtOrTrunc(NewSetCC, dl, VT, N0.getValueType());
2932 }
2933 break;
2934 }
2935 default:
2936 break; // todo, be more careful with signed comparisons
2937 }
2938 } else if (N0.getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG &&
2939 (Cond == ISD::SETEQ || Cond == ISD::SETNE)) {
2940 EVT ExtSrcTy = cast<VTSDNode>(N0.getOperand(1))->getVT();
2941 unsigned ExtSrcTyBits = ExtSrcTy.getSizeInBits();
2942 EVT ExtDstTy = N0.getValueType();
2943 unsigned ExtDstTyBits = ExtDstTy.getSizeInBits();
2944
2945 // If the constant doesn't fit into the number of bits for the source of
2946 // the sign extension, it is impossible for both sides to be equal.
2947 if (C1.getMinSignedBits() > ExtSrcTyBits)
2948 return DAG.getConstant(Cond == ISD::SETNE, dl, VT);
2949
2950 SDValue ZextOp;
2951 EVT Op0Ty = N0.getOperand(0).getValueType();
2952 if (Op0Ty == ExtSrcTy) {
2953 ZextOp = N0.getOperand(0);
2954 } else {
2955 APInt Imm = APInt::getLowBitsSet(ExtDstTyBits, ExtSrcTyBits);
2956 ZextOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, Op0Ty, N0.getOperand(0),
2957 DAG.getConstant(Imm, dl, Op0Ty));
2958 }
2959 if (!DCI.isCalledByLegalizer())
2960 DCI.AddToWorklist(ZextOp.getNode());
2961 // Otherwise, make this a use of a zext.
2962 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, ZextOp,
2963 DAG.getConstant(C1 & APInt::getLowBitsSet(
2964 ExtDstTyBits,
2965 ExtSrcTyBits),
2966 dl, ExtDstTy),
2967 Cond);
2968 } else if ((N1C->isNullValue() || N1C->isOne()) &&
2969 (Cond == ISD::SETEQ || Cond == ISD::SETNE)) {
2970 // SETCC (SETCC), [0|1], [EQ|NE] -> SETCC
2971 if (N0.getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC &&
2972 isTypeLegal(VT) && VT.bitsLE(N0.getValueType())) {
2973 bool TrueWhenTrue = (Cond == ISD::SETEQ) ^ (!N1C->isOne());
2974 if (TrueWhenTrue)
2975 return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, VT, N0);
2976 // Invert the condition.
2977 ISD::CondCode CC = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(N0.getOperand(2))->get();
2978 CC = ISD::getSetCCInverse(CC, N0.getOperand(0).getValueType());
2979 if (DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps() ||
2980 isCondCodeLegal(CC, N0.getOperand(0).getSimpleValueType()))
2981 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0.getOperand(0), N0.getOperand(1), CC);
2982 }
2983
2984 if ((N0.getOpcode() == ISD::XOR ||
2985 (N0.getOpcode() == ISD::AND &&
2986 N0.getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::XOR &&
2987 N0.getOperand(1) == N0.getOperand(0).getOperand(1))) &&
2988 isa<ConstantSDNode>(N0.getOperand(1)) &&
2989 cast<ConstantSDNode>(N0.getOperand(1))->isOne()) {
2990 // If this is (X^1) == 0/1, swap the RHS and eliminate the xor. We
2991 // can only do this if the top bits are known zero.
2992 unsigned BitWidth = N0.getValueSizeInBits();
2993 if (DAG.MaskedValueIsZero(N0,
2994 APInt::getHighBitsSet(BitWidth,
2995 BitWidth-1))) {
2996 // Okay, get the un-inverted input value.
2997 SDValue Val;
2998 if (N0.getOpcode() == ISD::XOR) {
2999 Val = N0.getOperand(0);
3000 } else {
3001 assert(N0.getOpcode() == ISD::AND &&
3002 N0.getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::XOR);
3003 // ((X^1)&1)^1 -> X & 1
3004 Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, N0.getValueType(),
3005 N0.getOperand(0).getOperand(0),
3006 N0.getOperand(1));
3007 }
3008
3009 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, Val, N1,
3010 Cond == ISD::SETEQ ? ISD::SETNE : ISD::SETEQ);
3011 }
3012 } else if (N1C->isOne() &&
3013 (VT == MVT::i1 ||
3014 getBooleanContents(N0->getValueType(0)) ==
3015 ZeroOrOneBooleanContent)) {
3016 SDValue Op0 = N0;
3017 if (Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::TRUNCATE)
3018 Op0 = Op0.getOperand(0);
3019
3020 if ((Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::XOR) &&
3021 Op0.getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC &&
3022 Op0.getOperand(1).getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC) {
3023 // (xor (setcc), (setcc)) == / != 1 -> (setcc) != / == (setcc)
3024 Cond = (Cond == ISD::SETEQ) ? ISD::SETNE : ISD::SETEQ;
3025 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, Op0.getOperand(0), Op0.getOperand(1),
3026 Cond);
3027 }
3028 if (Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::AND &&
3029 isa<ConstantSDNode>(Op0.getOperand(1)) &&
3030 cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op0.getOperand(1))->isOne()) {
3031 // If this is (X&1) == / != 1, normalize it to (X&1) != / == 0.
3032 if (Op0.getValueType().bitsGT(VT))
3033 Op0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT,
3034 DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, VT, Op0.getOperand(0)),
3035 DAG.getConstant(1, dl, VT));
3036 else if (Op0.getValueType().bitsLT(VT))
3037 Op0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT,
3038 DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, VT, Op0.getOperand(0)),
3039 DAG.getConstant(1, dl, VT));
3040
3041 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, Op0,
3042 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, Op0.getValueType()),
3043 Cond == ISD::SETEQ ? ISD::SETNE : ISD::SETEQ);
3044 }
3045 if (Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::AssertZext &&
3046 cast<VTSDNode>(Op0.getOperand(1))->getVT() == MVT::i1)
3047 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, Op0,
3048 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, Op0.getValueType()),
3049 Cond == ISD::SETEQ ? ISD::SETNE : ISD::SETEQ);
3050 }
3051 }
3052
3053 if (SDValue V =
3054 optimizeSetCCOfSignedTruncationCheck(VT, N0, N1, Cond, DCI, dl))
3055 return V;
3056 }
3057
3058 // These simplifications apply to splat vectors as well.
3059 // TODO: Handle more splat vector cases.
3060 if (auto *N1C = isConstOrConstSplat(N1)) {
3061 const APInt &C1 = N1C->getAPIntValue();
3062
3063 APInt MinVal, MaxVal;
3064 unsigned OperandBitSize = N1C->getValueType(0).getScalarSizeInBits();
3065 if (ISD::isSignedIntSetCC(Cond)) {
3066 MinVal = APInt::getSignedMinValue(OperandBitSize);
3067 MaxVal = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(OperandBitSize);
3068 } else {
3069 MinVal = APInt::getMinValue(OperandBitSize);
3070 MaxVal = APInt::getMaxValue(OperandBitSize);
3071 }
3072
3073 // Canonicalize GE/LE comparisons to use GT/LT comparisons.
3074 if (Cond == ISD::SETGE || Cond == ISD::SETUGE) {
3075 // X >= MIN --> true
3076 if (C1 == MinVal)
3077 return DAG.getBoolConstant(true, dl, VT, OpVT);
3078
3079 if (!VT.isVector()) { // TODO: Support this for vectors.
3080 // X >= C0 --> X > (C0 - 1)
3081 APInt C = C1 - 1;
3082 ISD::CondCode NewCC = (Cond == ISD::SETGE) ? ISD::SETGT : ISD::SETUGT;
3083 if ((DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps() ||
3084 isCondCodeLegal(NewCC, VT.getSimpleVT())) &&
3085 (!N1C->isOpaque() || (C.getBitWidth() <= 64 &&
3086 isLegalICmpImmediate(C.getSExtValue())))) {
3087 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0,
3088 DAG.getConstant(C, dl, N1.getValueType()),
3089 NewCC);
3090 }
3091 }
3092 }
3093
3094 if (Cond == ISD::SETLE || Cond == ISD::SETULE) {
3095 // X <= MAX --> true
3096 if (C1 == MaxVal)
3097 return DAG.getBoolConstant(true, dl, VT, OpVT);
3098
3099 // X <= C0 --> X < (C0 + 1)
3100 if (!VT.isVector()) { // TODO: Support this for vectors.
3101 APInt C = C1 + 1;
3102 ISD::CondCode NewCC = (Cond == ISD::SETLE) ? ISD::SETLT : ISD::SETULT;
3103 if ((DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps() ||
3104 isCondCodeLegal(NewCC, VT.getSimpleVT())) &&
3105 (!N1C->isOpaque() || (C.getBitWidth() <= 64 &&
3106 isLegalICmpImmediate(C.getSExtValue())))) {
3107 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0,
3108 DAG.getConstant(C, dl, N1.getValueType()),
3109 NewCC);
3110 }
3111 }
3112 }
3113
3114 if (Cond == ISD::SETLT || Cond == ISD::SETULT) {
3115 if (C1 == MinVal)
3116 return DAG.getBoolConstant(false, dl, VT, OpVT); // X < MIN --> false
3117
3118 // TODO: Support this for vectors after legalize ops.
3119 if (!VT.isVector() || DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps()) {
3120 // Canonicalize setlt X, Max --> setne X, Max
3121 if (C1 == MaxVal)
3122 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0, N1, ISD::SETNE);
3123
3124 // If we have setult X, 1, turn it into seteq X, 0
3125 if (C1 == MinVal+1)
3126 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0,
3127 DAG.getConstant(MinVal, dl, N0.getValueType()),
3128 ISD::SETEQ);
3129 }
3130 }
3131
3132 if (Cond == ISD::SETGT || Cond == ISD::SETUGT) {
3133 if (C1 == MaxVal)
3134 return DAG.getBoolConstant(false, dl, VT, OpVT); // X > MAX --> false
3135
3136 // TODO: Support this for vectors after legalize ops.
3137 if (!VT.isVector() || DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps()) {
3138 // Canonicalize setgt X, Min --> setne X, Min
3139 if (C1 == MinVal)
3140 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0, N1, ISD::SETNE);
3141
3142 // If we have setugt X, Max-1, turn it into seteq X, Max
3143 if (C1 == MaxVal-1)
3144 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0,
3145 DAG.getConstant(MaxVal, dl, N0.getValueType()),
3146 ISD::SETEQ);
3147 }
3148 }
3149
3150 // If we have "setcc X, C0", check to see if we can shrink the immediate
3151 // by changing cc.
3152 // TODO: Support this for vectors after legalize ops.
3153 if (!VT.isVector() || DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps()) {
3154 // SETUGT X, SINTMAX -> SETLT X, 0
3155 if (Cond == ISD::SETUGT &&
3156 C1 == APInt::getSignedMaxValue(OperandBitSize))
3157 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0,
3158 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, N1.getValueType()),
3159 ISD::SETLT);
3160
3161 // SETULT X, SINTMIN -> SETGT X, -1
3162 if (Cond == ISD::SETULT &&
3163 C1 == APInt::getSignedMinValue(OperandBitSize)) {
3164 SDValue ConstMinusOne =
3165 DAG.getConstant(APInt::getAllOnesValue(OperandBitSize), dl,
3166 N1.getValueType());
3167 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0, ConstMinusOne, ISD::SETGT);
3168 }
3169 }
3170 }
3171
3172 // Back to non-vector simplifications.
3173 // TODO: Can we do these for vector splats?
3174 if (auto *N1C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N1.getNode())) {
3175 const APInt &C1 = N1C->getAPIntValue();
3176
3177 // Fold bit comparisons when we can.
3178 if ((Cond == ISD::SETEQ || Cond == ISD::SETNE) &&
3179 (VT == N0.getValueType() ||
3180 (isTypeLegal(VT) && VT.bitsLE(N0.getValueType()))) &&
3181 N0.getOpcode() == ISD::AND) {
3182 auto &DL = DAG.getDataLayout();
3183 if (auto *AndRHS = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N0.getOperand(1))) {
3184 EVT ShiftTy = getShiftAmountTy(N0.getValueType(), DL,
3185 !DCI.isBeforeLegalize());
3186 if (Cond == ISD::SETNE && C1 == 0) {// (X & 8) != 0 --> (X & 8) >> 3
3187 // Perform the xform if the AND RHS is a single bit.
3188 if (AndRHS->getAPIntValue().isPowerOf2()) {
3189 return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, VT,
3190 DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, N0.getValueType(), N0,
3191 DAG.getConstant(AndRHS->getAPIntValue().logBase2(), dl,
3192 ShiftTy)));
3193 }
3194 } else if (Cond == ISD::SETEQ && C1 == AndRHS->getAPIntValue()) {
3195 // (X & 8) == 8 --> (X & 8) >> 3
3196 // Perform the xform if C1 is a single bit.
3197 if (C1.isPowerOf2()) {
3198 return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, VT,
3199 DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, N0.getValueType(), N0,
3200 DAG.getConstant(C1.logBase2(), dl,
3201 ShiftTy)));
3202 }
3203 }
3204 }
3205 }
3206
3207 if (C1.getMinSignedBits() <= 64 &&
3208 !isLegalICmpImmediate(C1.getSExtValue())) {
3209 // (X & -256) == 256 -> (X >> 8) == 1
3210 if ((Cond == ISD::SETEQ || Cond == ISD::SETNE) &&
3211 N0.getOpcode() == ISD::AND && N0.hasOneUse()) {
3212 if (auto *AndRHS = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N0.getOperand(1))) {
3213 const APInt &AndRHSC = AndRHS->getAPIntValue();
3214 if ((-AndRHSC).isPowerOf2() && (AndRHSC & C1) == C1) {
3215 unsigned ShiftBits = AndRHSC.countTrailingZeros();
3216 auto &DL = DAG.getDataLayout();
3217 EVT ShiftTy = getShiftAmountTy(N0.getValueType(), DL,
3218 !DCI.isBeforeLegalize());
3219 EVT CmpTy = N0.getValueType();
3220 SDValue Shift = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, CmpTy, N0.getOperand(0),
3221 DAG.getConstant(ShiftBits, dl,
3222 ShiftTy));
3223 SDValue CmpRHS = DAG.getConstant(C1.lshr(ShiftBits), dl, CmpTy);
3224 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, Shift, CmpRHS, Cond);
3225 }
3226 }
3227 } else if (Cond == ISD::SETULT || Cond == ISD::SETUGE ||
3228 Cond == ISD::SETULE || Cond == ISD::SETUGT) {
3229 bool AdjOne = (Cond == ISD::SETULE || Cond == ISD::SETUGT);
3230 // X < 0x100000000 -> (X >> 32) < 1
3231 // X >= 0x100000000 -> (X >> 32) >= 1
3232 // X <= 0x0ffffffff -> (X >> 32) < 1
3233 // X > 0x0ffffffff -> (X >> 32) >= 1
3234 unsigned ShiftBits;
3235 APInt NewC = C1;
3236 ISD::CondCode NewCond = Cond;
3237 if (AdjOne) {
3238 ShiftBits = C1.countTrailingOnes();
3239 NewC = NewC + 1;
3240 NewCond = (Cond == ISD::SETULE) ? ISD::SETULT : ISD::SETUGE;
3241 } else {
3242 ShiftBits = C1.countTrailingZeros();
3243 }
3244 NewC.lshrInPlace(ShiftBits);
3245 if (ShiftBits && NewC.getMinSignedBits() <= 64 &&
3246 isLegalICmpImmediate(NewC.getSExtValue())) {
3247 auto &DL = DAG.getDataLayout();
3248 EVT ShiftTy = getShiftAmountTy(N0.getValueType(), DL,
3249 !DCI.isBeforeLegalize());
3250 EVT CmpTy = N0.getValueType();
3251 SDValue Shift = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, CmpTy, N0,
3252 DAG.getConstant(ShiftBits, dl, ShiftTy));
3253 SDValue CmpRHS = DAG.getConstant(NewC, dl, CmpTy);
3254 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, Shift, CmpRHS, NewCond);
3255 }
3256 }
3257 }
3258 }
3259
3260 if (!isa<ConstantFPSDNode>(N0) && isa<ConstantFPSDNode>(N1)) {
3261 auto *CFP = cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(N1);
3262 assert(!CFP->getValueAPF().isNaN() && "Unexpected NaN value");
3263
3264 // Otherwise, we know the RHS is not a NaN. Simplify the node to drop the
3265 // constant if knowing that the operand is non-nan is enough. We prefer to
3266 // have SETO(x,x) instead of SETO(x, 0.0) because this avoids having to
3267 // materialize 0.0.
3268 if (Cond == ISD::SETO || Cond == ISD::SETUO)
3269 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0, N0, Cond);
3270
3271 // setcc (fneg x), C -> setcc swap(pred) x, -C
3272 if (N0.getOpcode() == ISD::FNEG) {
3273 ISD::CondCode SwapCond = ISD::getSetCCSwappedOperands(Cond);
3274 if (DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps() ||
3275 isCondCodeLegal(SwapCond, N0.getSimpleValueType())) {
3276 SDValue NegN1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FNEG, dl, N0.getValueType(), N1);
3277 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0.getOperand(0), NegN1, SwapCond);
3278 }
3279 }
3280
3281 // If the condition is not legal, see if we can find an equivalent one
3282 // which is legal.
3283 if (!isCondCodeLegal(Cond, N0.getSimpleValueType())) {
3284 // If the comparison was an awkward floating-point == or != and one of
3285 // the comparison operands is infinity or negative infinity, convert the
3286 // condition to a less-awkward <= or >=.
3287 if (CFP->getValueAPF().isInfinity()) {
3288 if (CFP->getValueAPF().isNegative()) {
3289 if (Cond == ISD::SETOEQ &&
3290 isCondCodeLegal(ISD::SETOLE, N0.getSimpleValueType()))
3291 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0, N1, ISD::SETOLE);
3292 if (Cond == ISD::SETUEQ &&
3293 isCondCodeLegal(ISD::SETOLE, N0.getSimpleValueType()))
3294 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0, N1, ISD::SETULE);
3295 if (Cond == ISD::SETUNE &&
3296 isCondCodeLegal(ISD::SETUGT, N0.getSimpleValueType()))
3297 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0, N1, ISD::SETUGT);
3298 if (Cond == ISD::SETONE &&
3299 isCondCodeLegal(ISD::SETUGT, N0.getSimpleValueType()))
3300 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0, N1, ISD::SETOGT);
3301 } else {
3302 if (Cond == ISD::SETOEQ &&
3303 isCondCodeLegal(ISD::SETOGE, N0.getSimpleValueType()))
3304 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0, N1, ISD::SETOGE);
3305 if (Cond == ISD::SETUEQ &&
3306 isCondCodeLegal(ISD::SETOGE, N0.getSimpleValueType()))
3307 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0, N1, ISD::SETUGE);
3308 if (Cond == ISD::SETUNE &&
3309 isCondCodeLegal(ISD::SETULT, N0.getSimpleValueType()))
3310 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0, N1, ISD::SETULT);
3311 if (Cond == ISD::SETONE &&
3312 isCondCodeLegal(ISD::SETULT, N0.getSimpleValueType()))
3313 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0, N1, ISD::SETOLT);
3314 }
3315 }
3316 }
3317 }
3318
3319 if (N0 == N1) {
3320 // The sext(setcc()) => setcc() optimization relies on the appropriate
3321 // constant being emitted.
3322 assert(!N0.getValueType().isInteger() &&
3323 "Integer types should be handled by FoldSetCC");
3324
3325 bool EqTrue = ISD::isTrueWhenEqual(Cond);
3326 unsigned UOF = ISD::getUnorderedFlavor(Cond);
3327 if (UOF == 2) // FP operators that are undefined on NaNs.
3328 return DAG.getBoolConstant(EqTrue, dl, VT, OpVT);
3329 if (UOF == unsigned(EqTrue))
3330 return DAG.getBoolConstant(EqTrue, dl, VT, OpVT);
3331 // Otherwise, we can't fold it. However, we can simplify it to SETUO/SETO
3332 // if it is not already.
3333 ISD::CondCode NewCond = UOF == 0 ? ISD::SETO : ISD::SETUO;
3334 if (NewCond != Cond &&
3335 (DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps() ||
3336 isCondCodeLegal(NewCond, N0.getSimpleValueType())))
3337 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0, N1, NewCond);
3338 }
3339
3340 if ((Cond == ISD::SETEQ || Cond == ISD::SETNE) &&
3341 N0.getValueType().isInteger()) {
3342 if (N0.getOpcode() == ISD::ADD || N0.getOpcode() == ISD::SUB ||
3343 N0.getOpcode() == ISD::XOR) {
3344 // Simplify (X+Y) == (X+Z) --> Y == Z
3345 if (N0.getOpcode() == N1.getOpcode()) {
3346 if (N0.getOperand(0) == N1.getOperand(0))
3347 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0.getOperand(1), N1.getOperand(1), Cond);
3348 if (N0.getOperand(1) == N1.getOperand(1))
3349 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0.getOperand(0), N1.getOperand(0), Cond);
3350 if (isCommutativeBinOp(N0.getOpcode())) {
3351 // If X op Y == Y op X, try other combinations.
3352 if (N0.getOperand(0) == N1.getOperand(1))
3353 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0.getOperand(1), N1.getOperand(0),
3354 Cond);
3355 if (N0.getOperand(1) == N1.getOperand(0))
3356 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0.getOperand(0), N1.getOperand(1),
3357 Cond);
3358 }
3359 }
3360
3361 // If RHS is a legal immediate value for a compare instruction, we need
3362 // to be careful about increasing register pressure needlessly.
3363 bool LegalRHSImm = false;
3364
3365 if (auto *RHSC = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N1)) {
3366 if (auto *LHSR = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N0.getOperand(1))) {
3367 // Turn (X+C1) == C2 --> X == C2-C1
3368 if (N0.getOpcode() == ISD::ADD && N0.getNode()->hasOneUse()) {
3369 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0.getOperand(0),
3370 DAG.getConstant(RHSC->getAPIntValue()-
3371 LHSR->getAPIntValue(),
3372 dl, N0.getValueType()), Cond);
3373 }
3374
3375 // Turn (X^C1) == C2 into X == C1^C2 iff X&~C1 = 0.
3376 if (N0.getOpcode() == ISD::XOR)
3377 // If we know that all of the inverted bits are zero, don't bother
3378 // performing the inversion.
3379 if (DAG.MaskedValueIsZero(N0.getOperand(0), ~LHSR->getAPIntValue()))
3380 return
3381 DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0.getOperand(0),
3382 DAG.getConstant(LHSR->getAPIntValue() ^
3383 RHSC->getAPIntValue(),
3384 dl, N0.getValueType()),
3385 Cond);
3386 }
3387
3388 // Turn (C1-X) == C2 --> X == C1-C2
3389 if (auto *SUBC = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N0.getOperand(0))) {
3390 if (N0.getOpcode() == ISD::SUB && N0.getNode()->hasOneUse()) {
3391 return
3392 DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N0.getOperand(1),
3393 DAG.getConstant(SUBC->getAPIntValue() -
3394 RHSC->getAPIntValue(),
3395 dl, N0.getValueType()),
3396 Cond);
3397 }
3398 }
3399
3400 // Could RHSC fold directly into a compare?
3401 if (RHSC->getValueType(0).getSizeInBits() <= 64)
3402 LegalRHSImm = isLegalICmpImmediate(RHSC->getSExtValue());
3403 }
3404
3405 // (X+Y) == X --> Y == 0 and similar folds.
3406 // Don't do this if X is an immediate that can fold into a cmp
3407 // instruction and X+Y has other uses. It could be an induction variable
3408 // chain, and the transform would increase register pressure.
3409 if (!LegalRHSImm || N0.hasOneUse())
3410 if (SDValue V = foldSetCCWithBinOp(VT, N0, N1, Cond, dl, DCI))
3411 return V;
3412 }
3413
3414 if (N1.getOpcode() == ISD::ADD || N1.getOpcode() == ISD::SUB ||
3415 N1.getOpcode() == ISD::XOR)
3416 if (SDValue V = foldSetCCWithBinOp(VT, N1, N0, Cond, dl, DCI))
3417 return V;
3418
3419 if (SDValue V = foldSetCCWithAnd(VT, N0, N1, Cond, dl, DCI))
3420 return V;
3421 }
3422
3423 // Fold away ALL boolean setcc's.
3424 if (N0.getValueType().getScalarType() == MVT::i1 && foldBooleans) {
3425 SDValue Temp;
3426 switch (Cond) {
3427 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown integer setcc!");
3428 case ISD::SETEQ: // X == Y -> ~(X^Y)
3429 Temp = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, dl, OpVT, N0, N1);
3430 N0 = DAG.getNOT(dl, Temp, OpVT);
3431 if (!DCI.isCalledByLegalizer())
3432 DCI.AddToWorklist(Temp.getNode());
3433 break;
3434 case ISD::SETNE: // X != Y --> (X^Y)
3435 N0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, dl, OpVT, N0, N1);
3436 break;
3437 case ISD::SETGT: // X >s Y --> X == 0 & Y == 1 --> ~X & Y
3438 case ISD::SETULT: // X <u Y --> X == 0 & Y == 1 --> ~X & Y
3439 Temp = DAG.getNOT(dl, N0, OpVT);
3440 N0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, OpVT, N1, Temp);
3441 if (!DCI.isCalledByLegalizer())
3442 DCI.AddToWorklist(Temp.getNode());
3443 break;
3444 case ISD::SETLT: // X <s Y --> X == 1 & Y == 0 --> ~Y & X
3445 case ISD::SETUGT: // X >u Y --> X == 1 & Y == 0 --> ~Y & X
3446 Temp = DAG.getNOT(dl, N1, OpVT);
3447 N0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, OpVT, N0, Temp);
3448 if (!DCI.isCalledByLegalizer())
3449 DCI.AddToWorklist(Temp.getNode());
3450 break;
3451 case ISD::SETULE: // X <=u Y --> X == 0 | Y == 1 --> ~X | Y
3452 case ISD::SETGE: // X >=s Y --> X == 0 | Y == 1 --> ~X | Y
3453 Temp = DAG.getNOT(dl, N0, OpVT);
3454 N0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, OpVT, N1, Temp);
3455 if (!DCI.isCalledByLegalizer())
3456 DCI.AddToWorklist(Temp.getNode());
3457 break;
3458 case ISD::SETUGE: // X >=u Y --> X == 1 | Y == 0 --> ~Y | X
3459 case ISD::SETLE: // X <=s Y --> X == 1 | Y == 0 --> ~Y | X
3460 Temp = DAG.getNOT(dl, N1, OpVT);
3461 N0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, OpVT, N0, Temp);
3462 break;
3463 }
3464 if (VT.getScalarType() != MVT::i1) {
3465 if (!DCI.isCalledByLegalizer())
3466 DCI.AddToWorklist(N0.getNode());
3467 // FIXME: If running after legalize, we probably can't do this.
3468 ISD::NodeType ExtendCode = getExtendForContent(getBooleanContents(OpVT));
3469 N0 = DAG.getNode(ExtendCode, dl, VT, N0);
3470 }
3471 return N0;
3472 }
3473
3474 // Could not fold it.
3475 return SDValue();
3476}
3477
3478/// Returns true (and the GlobalValue and the offset) if the node is a
3479/// GlobalAddress + offset.
3480bool TargetLowering::isGAPlusOffset(SDNode *WN, const GlobalValue *&GA,
3481 int64_t &Offset) const {
3482
3483 SDNode *N = unwrapAddress(SDValue(WN, 0)).getNode();
3484
3485 if (auto *GASD = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(N)) {
3486 GA = GASD->getGlobal();
3487 Offset += GASD->getOffset();
3488 return true;
3489 }
3490
3491 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::ADD) {
3492 SDValue N1 = N->getOperand(0);
3493 SDValue N2 = N->getOperand(1);
3494 if (isGAPlusOffset(N1.getNode(), GA, Offset)) {
3495 if (auto *V = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N2)) {
3496 Offset += V->getSExtValue();
3497 return true;
3498 }
3499 } else if (isGAPlusOffset(N2.getNode(), GA, Offset)) {
3500 if (auto *V = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N1)) {
3501 Offset += V->getSExtValue();
3502 return true;
3503 }
3504 }
3505 }
3506
3507 return false;
3508}
3509
3510SDValue TargetLowering::PerformDAGCombine(SDNode *N,
3511 DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
3512 // Default implementation: no optimization.
3513 return SDValue();
3514}

3516//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3517// Inline Assembler Implementation Methods
3518//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3519
3520TargetLowering::ConstraintType
3521TargetLowering::getConstraintType(StringRef Constraint) const {
3522 unsigned S = Constraint.size();
3523
3524 if (S == 1) {
3525 switch (Constraint[0]) {
3526 default: break;
3527 case 'r': return C_RegisterClass;
3528 case 'm': // memory
3529 case 'o': // offsetable
3530 case 'V': // not offsetable
3531 return C_Memory;
3532 case 'i': // Simple Integer or Relocatable Constant
3533 case 'n': // Simple Integer
3534 case 'E': // Floating Point Constant
3535 case 'F': // Floating Point Constant
3536 case 's': // Relocatable Constant
3537 case 'p': // Address.
3538 case 'X': // Allow ANY value.
3539 case 'I': // Target registers.
3540 case 'J':
3541 case 'K':
3542 case 'L':
3543 case 'M':
3544 case 'N':
3545 case 'O':
3546 case 'P':
3547 case '<':
3548 case '>':
3549 return C_Other;
3550 }
3551 }
3552
3553 if (S > 1 && Constraint[0] == '{' && Constraint[S - 1] == '}') {
3554 if (S == 8 && Constraint.substr(1, 6) == "memory") // "{memory}"
3555 return C_Memory;
3556 return C_Register;
3557 }
3558 return C_Unknown;
3559}
3560
3561/// Try to replace an X constraint, which matches anything, with another that
3562/// has more specific requirements based on the type of the corresponding
3563/// operand.
3564const char *TargetLowering::LowerXConstraint(EVT ConstraintVT) const {
3565 if (ConstraintVT.isInteger())
3566 return "r";
3567 if (ConstraintVT.isFloatingPoint())
3568 return "f"; // works for many targets
3569 return nullptr;
3570}
3571
3572SDValue TargetLowering::LowerAsmOutputForConstraint(
3573 SDValue &Chain, SDValue &Flag, SDLoc DL, const AsmOperandInfo &OpInfo,
3574 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
3575 return SDValue();
3576}
3577
3578/// Lower the specified operand into the Ops vector.
3579/// If it is invalid, don't add anything to Ops.
3580void TargetLowering::LowerAsmOperandForConstraint(SDValue Op,
3581 std::string &Constraint,
3582 std::vector<SDValue> &Ops,
3583 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
3584
3585 if (Constraint.length() > 1) return;
3586
3587 char ConstraintLetter = Constraint[0];
3588 switch (ConstraintLetter) {
3589 default: break;
3590 case 'X': // Allows any operand; labels (basic block) use this.
3591 if (Op.getOpcode() == ISD::BasicBlock ||
3592 Op.getOpcode() == ISD::TargetBlockAddress) {
3593 Ops.push_back(Op);
3594 return;
3595 }
3596 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
3597 case 'i': // Simple Integer or Relocatable Constant
3598 case 'n': // Simple Integer
3599 case 's': { // Relocatable Constant
3600
3601 GlobalAddressSDNode *GA;
3602 ConstantSDNode *C;
3603 uint64_t Offset = 0;
3604
3605 // Match (GA) or (C) or (GA+C) or (GA-C) or ((GA+C)+C) or (((GA+C)+C)+C),
3606 // etc., since getelementpointer is variadic. We can't use
3607 // SelectionDAG::FoldSymbolOffset because it expects the GA to be accessible
3608 // while in this case the GA may be furthest from the root node which is
3609 // likely an ISD::ADD.
3610 while (1) {
3611 if ((GA = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Op)) && ConstraintLetter != 'n') {
3612 Ops.push_back(DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GA->getGlobal(), SDLoc(Op),
3613 GA->getValueType(0),
3614 Offset + GA->getOffset()));
3615 return;
3616 } else if ((C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op)) &&
3617 ConstraintLetter != 's') {
3618 // gcc prints these as sign extended. Sign extend value to 64 bits
3619 // now; without this it would get ZExt'd later in
3620 // ScheduleDAGSDNodes::EmitNode, which is very generic.
3621 bool IsBool = C->getConstantIntValue()->getBitWidth() == 1;
3622 BooleanContent BCont = getBooleanContents(MVT::i64);
3623 ISD::NodeType ExtOpc = IsBool ? getExtendForContent(BCont)
3624 : ISD::SIGN_EXTEND;
3625 int64_t ExtVal = ExtOpc == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND ? C->getZExtValue()
3626 : C->getSExtValue();
3627 Ops.push_back(DAG.getTargetConstant(Offset + ExtVal,
3628 SDLoc(C), MVT::i64));
3629 return;
3630 } else {
3631 const unsigned OpCode = Op.getOpcode();
3632 if (OpCode == ISD::ADD || OpCode == ISD::SUB) {
3633 if ((C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(0))))
3634 Op = Op.getOperand(1);
3635 // Subtraction is not commutative.
3636 else if (OpCode == ISD::ADD &&
3637 (C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))))
3638 Op = Op.getOperand(0);
3639 else
3640 return;
3641 Offset += (OpCode == ISD::ADD ? 1 : -1) * C->getSExtValue();
3642 continue;
3643 }
3644 }
3645 return;
3646 }
3647 break;
3648 }
3649 }
3650}
3651
3652std::pair<unsigned, const TargetRegisterClass *>
3653TargetLowering::getRegForInlineAsmConstraint(const TargetRegisterInfo *RI,
3654 StringRef Constraint,
3655 MVT VT) const {
3656 if (Constraint.empty() || Constraint[0] != '{')
3657 return std::make_pair(0u, static_cast<TargetRegisterClass *>(nullptr));
3658 assert(*(Constraint.end() - 1) == '}' && "Not a brace enclosed constraint?");
3659
3660 // Remove the braces from around the name.
3661 StringRef RegName(Constraint.data() + 1, Constraint.size() - 2);
3662
3663 std::pair<unsigned, const TargetRegisterClass *> R =
3664 std::make_pair(0u, static_cast<const TargetRegisterClass *>(nullptr));
3665
3666 // Figure out which register class contains this reg.
3667 for (const TargetRegisterClass *RC : RI->regclasses()) {
3668 // If none of the value types for this register class are valid, we
3669 // can't use it. For example, 64-bit reg classes on 32-bit targets.
3670 if (!isLegalRC(*RI, *RC))
3671 continue;
3672
3673 for (TargetRegisterClass::iterator I = RC->begin(), E = RC->end();
3674 I != E; ++I) {
3675 if (RegName.equals_lower(RI->getRegAsmName(*I))) {
3676 std::pair<unsigned, const TargetRegisterClass *> S =
3677 std::make_pair(*I, RC);
3678
3679 // If this register class has the requested value type, return it,
3680 // otherwise keep searching and return the first class found
3681 // if no other is found which explicitly has the requested type.
3682 if (RI->isTypeLegalForClass(*RC, VT))
3683 return S;
3684 if (!R.second)
3685 R = S;
3686 }
3687 }
3688 }
3689
3690 return R;
3691}
3692
3693//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3694// Constraint Selection.
3695
3696/// Return true of this is an input operand that is a matching constraint like
3697/// "4".
3698bool TargetLowering::AsmOperandInfo::isMatchingInputConstraint() const {
3699 assert(!ConstraintCode.empty() && "No known constraint!");
3700 return isdigit(static_cast<unsigned char>(ConstraintCode[0]));
3701}
3702
3703/// If this is an input matching constraint, this method returns the output
3704/// operand it matches.
3705unsigned TargetLowering::AsmOperandInfo::getMatchedOperand() const {
3706 assert(!ConstraintCode.empty() && "No known constraint!");
3707 return atoi(ConstraintCode.c_str());
3708}
3709
3710/// Split up the constraint string from the inline assembly value into the
3711/// specific constraints and their prefixes, and also tie in the associated
3712/// operand values.
3713/// If this returns an empty vector, and if the constraint string itself
3714/// isn't empty, there was an error parsing.
3715TargetLowering::AsmOperandInfoVector
3716TargetLowering::ParseConstraints(const DataLayout &DL,
3717 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI,
3718 ImmutableCallSite CS) const {
3719 /// Information about all of the constraints.
3720 AsmOperandInfoVector ConstraintOperands;
3721 const InlineAsm *IA = cast<InlineAsm>(CS.getCalledValue());
3722 unsigned maCount = 0; // Largest number of multiple alternative constraints.
3723
3724 // Do a prepass over the constraints, canonicalizing them, and building up the
3725 // ConstraintOperands list.
3726 unsigned ArgNo = 0; // ArgNo - The argument of the CallInst.
3727 unsigned ResNo = 0; // ResNo - The result number of the next output.
3728
3729 for (InlineAsm::ConstraintInfo &CI : IA->ParseConstraints()) {
3730 ConstraintOperands.emplace_back(std::move(CI));
3731 AsmOperandInfo &OpInfo = ConstraintOperands.back();
3732
3733 // Update multiple alternative constraint count.
3734 if (OpInfo.multipleAlternatives.size() > maCount)
3735 maCount = OpInfo.multipleAlternatives.size();
3736
3737 OpInfo.ConstraintVT = MVT::Other;
3738
3739 // Compute the value type for each operand.
3740 switch (OpInfo.Type) {
3741 case InlineAsm::isOutput:
3742 // Indirect outputs just consume an argument.
3743 if (OpInfo.isIndirect) {
3744 OpInfo.CallOperandVal = const_cast<Value *>(CS.getArgument(ArgNo++));
3745 break;
3746 }
3747
3748 // The return value of the call is this value. As such, there is no
3749 // corresponding argument.
3750 assert(!CS.getType()->isVoidTy() &&
3751 "Bad inline asm!");
3752 if (StructType *STy = dyn_cast<StructType>(CS.getType())) {
3753 OpInfo.ConstraintVT =
3754 getSimpleValueType(DL, STy->getElementType(ResNo));
3755 } else {
3756 assert(ResNo == 0 && "Asm only has one result!");
3757 OpInfo.ConstraintVT = getSimpleValueType(DL, CS.getType());
3758 }
3759 ++ResNo;
3760 break;
3761 case InlineAsm::isInput:
3762 OpInfo.CallOperandVal = const_cast<Value *>(CS.getArgument(ArgNo++));
3763 break;
3764 case InlineAsm::isClobber:
3765 // Nothing to do.
3766 break;
3767 }
3768
3769 if (OpInfo.CallOperandVal) {
3770 llvm::Type *OpTy = OpInfo.CallOperandVal->getType();
3771 if (OpInfo.isIndirect) {
3772 llvm::PointerType *PtrTy = dyn_cast<PointerType>(OpTy);
3773 if (!PtrTy)
3774 report_fatal_error("Indirect operand for inline asm not a pointer!");
3775 OpTy = PtrTy->getElementType();
3776 }
3777
3778 // Look for vector wrapped in a struct. e.g. { <16 x i8> }.
3779 if (StructType *STy = dyn_cast<StructType>(OpTy))
3780 if (STy->getNumElements() == 1)
3781 OpTy = STy->getElementType(0);
3782
3783 // If OpTy is not a single value, it may be a struct/union that we
3784 // can tile with integers.
3785 if (!OpTy->isSingleValueType() && OpTy->isSized()) {
3786 unsigned BitSize = DL.getTypeSizeInBits(OpTy);
3787 switch (BitSize) {
3788 default: break;
3789 case 1:
3790 case 8:
3791 case 16:
3792 case 32:
3793 case 64:
3794 case 128:
3795 OpInfo.ConstraintVT =
3796 MVT::getVT(IntegerType::get(OpTy->getContext(), BitSize), true);
3797 break;
3798 }
3799 } else if (PointerType *PT = dyn_cast<PointerType>(OpTy)) {
3800 unsigned AS = PT->getAddressSpace();
3801 unsigned PtrSize = DL.getPointerSizeInBits(AS);
3802 if (DL.isFatPointer(AS))
3803 OpInfo.ConstraintVT = MVT::getFatPointerVT(PtrSize);
3804 else
3805 OpInfo.ConstraintVT = MVT::getIntegerVT(PtrSize);
3806 } else {
3807 OpInfo.ConstraintVT = MVT::getVT(OpTy, true);
3808 }
3809 }
3810 }
3811
3812 // If we have multiple alternative constraints, select the best alternative.
3813 if (!ConstraintOperands.empty()) {
3814 if (maCount) {
3815 unsigned bestMAIndex = 0;
3816 int bestWeight = -1;
3817 // weight: -1 = invalid match, and 0 = so-so match to 5 = good match.
3818 int weight = -1;
3819 unsigned maIndex;
3820 // Compute the sums of the weights for each alternative, keeping track
3821 // of the best (highest weight) one so far.
3822 for (maIndex = 0; maIndex < maCount; ++maIndex) {
3823 int weightSum = 0;
3824 for (unsigned cIndex = 0, eIndex = ConstraintOperands.size();
3825 cIndex != eIndex; ++cIndex) {
3826 AsmOperandInfo &OpInfo = ConstraintOperands[cIndex];
3827 if (OpInfo.Type == InlineAsm::isClobber)
3828 continue;
3829
3830 // If this is an output operand with a matching input operand,
3831 // look up the matching input. If their types mismatch, e.g. one
3832 // is an integer, the other is floating point, or their sizes are
3833 // different, flag it as an maCantMatch.
3834 if (OpInfo.hasMatchingInput()) {
3835 AsmOperandInfo &Input = ConstraintOperands[OpInfo.MatchingInput];
3836 if (OpInfo.ConstraintVT != Input.ConstraintVT) {
3837 if ((OpInfo.ConstraintVT.isInteger() !=
3838 Input.ConstraintVT.isInteger()) ||
3839 (OpInfo.ConstraintVT.getSizeInBits() !=
3840 Input.ConstraintVT.getSizeInBits())) {
3841 weightSum = -1; // Can't match.
3842 break;
3843 }
3844 }
3845 }
3846 weight = getMultipleConstraintMatchWeight(OpInfo, maIndex);
3847 if (weight == -1) {
3848 weightSum = -1;
3849 break;
3850 }
3851 weightSum += weight;
3852 }
3853 // Update best.
3854 if (weightSum > bestWeight) {
3855 bestWeight = weightSum;
3856 bestMAIndex = maIndex;
3857 }
3858 }
3859
3860 // Now select chosen alternative in each constraint.
3861 for (unsigned cIndex = 0, eIndex = ConstraintOperands.size();
3862 cIndex != eIndex; ++cIndex) {
3863 AsmOperandInfo &cInfo = ConstraintOperands[cIndex];
3864 if (cInfo.Type == InlineAsm::isClobber)
3865 continue;
3866 cInfo.selectAlternative(bestMAIndex);
3867 }
3868 }
3869 }
3870
3871 // Check and hook up tied operands, choose constraint code to use.
3872 for (unsigned cIndex = 0, eIndex = ConstraintOperands.size();
3873 cIndex != eIndex; ++cIndex) {
3874 AsmOperandInfo &OpInfo = ConstraintOperands[cIndex];
3875
3876 // If this is an output operand with a matching input operand, look up the
3877 // matching input. If their types mismatch, e.g. one is an integer, the
3878 // other is floating point, or their sizes are different, flag it as an
3879 // error.
3880 if (OpInfo.hasMatchingInput()) {
3881 AsmOperandInfo &Input = ConstraintOperands[OpInfo.MatchingInput];
3882
3883 if (OpInfo.ConstraintVT != Input.ConstraintVT) {
3884 std::pair<unsigned, const TargetRegisterClass *> MatchRC =
3885 getRegForInlineAsmConstraint(TRI, OpInfo.ConstraintCode,
3886 OpInfo.ConstraintVT);
3887 std::pair<unsigned, const TargetRegisterClass *> InputRC =
3888 getRegForInlineAsmConstraint(TRI, Input.ConstraintCode,
3889 Input.ConstraintVT);
3890 if ((OpInfo.ConstraintVT.isInteger() !=
3891 Input.ConstraintVT.isInteger()) ||
3892 (MatchRC.second != InputRC.second)) {
3893 report_fatal_error("Unsupported asm: input constraint"
3894 " with a matching output constraint of"
3895 " incompatible type!");
3896 }
3897 }
3898 }
3899 }
3900
3901 return ConstraintOperands;
3902}
3903
3904/// Return an integer indicating how general CT is.
3905static unsigned getConstraintGenerality(TargetLowering::ConstraintType CT) {
3906 switch (CT) {
3907 case TargetLowering::C_Other:
3908 case TargetLowering::C_Unknown:
3909 return 0;
3910 case TargetLowering::C_Register:
3911 return 1;
3912 case TargetLowering::C_RegisterClass:
3913 return 2;
3914 case TargetLowering::C_Memory:
3915 return 3;
3916 }
3917 llvm_unreachable("Invalid constraint type");
3918}
3919
3920/// Examine constraint type and operand type and determine a weight value.
3921/// This object must already have been set up with the operand type
3922/// and the current alternative constraint selected.
3923TargetLowering::ConstraintWeight
3924 TargetLowering::getMultipleConstraintMatchWeight(
3925 AsmOperandInfo &info, int maIndex) const {
3926 InlineAsm::ConstraintCodeVector *rCodes;
3927 if (maIndex >= (int)info.multipleAlternatives.size())
3928 rCodes = &info.Codes;
3929 else
3930 rCodes = &info.multipleAlternatives[maIndex].Codes;
3931 ConstraintWeight BestWeight = CW_Invalid;
3932
3933 // Loop over the options, keeping track of the most general one.
3934 for (unsigned i = 0, e = rCodes->size(); i != e; ++i) {
3935 ConstraintWeight weight =
3936 getSingleConstraintMatchWeight(info, (*rCodes)[i].c_str());
3937 if (weight > BestWeight)
3938 BestWeight = weight;
3939 }
3940
3941 return BestWeight;
3942}
3943
3944/// Examine constraint type and operand type and determine a weight value.
3945/// This object must already have been set up with the operand type
3946/// and the current alternative constraint selected.
3947TargetLowering::ConstraintWeight
3948 TargetLowering::getSingleConstraintMatchWeight(
3949 AsmOperandInfo &info, const char *constraint) const {
3950 ConstraintWeight weight = CW_Invalid;
3951 Value *CallOperandVal = info.CallOperandVal;
3952 // If we don't have a value, we can't do a match,
3953 // but allow it at the lowest weight.
3954 if (!CallOperandVal)
3955 return CW_Default;
3956 // Look at the constraint type.
3957 switch (*constraint) {
3958 case 'i': // immediate integer.
3959 case 'n': // immediate integer with a known value.
3960 if (isa<ConstantInt>(CallOperandVal))
3961 weight = CW_Constant;
3962 break;
3963 case 's': // non-explicit intregal immediate.
3964 if (isa<GlobalValue>(CallOperandVal))
3965 weight = CW_Constant;
3966 break;
3967 case 'E': // immediate float if host format.
3968 case 'F': // immediate float.
3969 if (isa<ConstantFP>(CallOperandVal))
3970 weight = CW_Constant;
3971 break;
3972 case '<': // memory operand with autodecrement.
3973 case '>': // memory operand with autoincrement.
3974 case 'm': // memory operand.
3975 case 'o': // offsettable memory operand
3976 case 'V': // non-offsettable memory operand
3977 weight = CW_Memory;
3978 break;
3979 case 'r': // general register.
3980 case 'g': // general register, memory operand or immediate integer.
3981 // note: Clang converts "g" to "imr".
3982 if (CallOperandVal->getType()->isIntegerTy())
3983 weight = CW_Register;
3984 break;
3985 case 'X': // any operand.
3986 default:
3987 weight = CW_Default;
3988 break;
3989 }
3990 return weight;
3991}
3992
3993/// If there are multiple different constraints that we could pick for this
3994/// operand (e.g. "imr") try to pick the 'best' one.
3995/// This is somewhat tricky: constraints fall into four classes:
3996/// Other -> immediates and magic values
3997/// Register -> one specific register
3998/// RegisterClass -> a group of regs
3999/// Memory -> memory
4000/// Ideally, we would pick the most specific constraint possible: if we have
4001/// something that fits into a register, we would pick it. The problem here
4002/// is that if we have something that could either be in a register or in
4003/// memory that use of the register could cause selection of *other*
4004/// operands to fail: they might only succeed if we pick memory. Because of
4005/// this the heuristic we use is:
4006///
4007/// 1) If there is an 'other' constraint, and if the operand is valid for
4008/// that constraint, use it. This makes us take advantage of 'i'
4009/// constraints when available.
4010/// 2) Otherwise, pick the most general constraint present. This prefers
4011/// 'm' over 'r', for example.
4012///
4013static void ChooseConstraint(TargetLowering::AsmOperandInfo &OpInfo,
4014 const TargetLowering &TLI,
4015 SDValue Op, SelectionDAG *DAG) {
4016 assert(OpInfo.Codes.size() > 1 && "Doesn't have multiple constraint options");
4017 unsigned BestIdx = 0;
4018 TargetLowering::ConstraintType BestType = TargetLowering::C_Unknown;
4019 int BestGenerality = -1;
4020
4021 // Loop over the options, keeping track of the most general one.
4022 for (unsigned i = 0, e = OpInfo.Codes.size(); i != e; ++i) {
4023 TargetLowering::ConstraintType CType =
4024 TLI.getConstraintType(OpInfo.Codes[i]);
4025
4026 // If this is an 'other' constraint, see if the operand is valid for it.
4027 // For example, on X86 we might have an 'rI' constraint. If the operand
4028 // is an integer in the range [0..31] we want to use I (saving a load
4029 // of a register), otherwise we must use 'r'.
4030 if (CType == TargetLowering::C_Other && Op.getNode()) {
4031 assert(OpInfo.Codes[i].size() == 1 &&
4032 "Unhandled multi-letter 'other' constraint");
4033 std::vector<SDValue> ResultOps;
4034 TLI.LowerAsmOperandForConstraint(Op, OpInfo.Codes[i],
4035 ResultOps, *DAG);
4036 if (!ResultOps.empty()) {
4037 BestType = CType;
4038 BestIdx = i;
4039 break;
4040 }
4041 }
4042
4043 // Things with matching constraints can only be registers, per gcc
4044 // documentation. This mainly affects "g" constraints.
4045 if (CType == TargetLowering::C_Memory && OpInfo.hasMatchingInput())
4046 continue;
4047
4048 // This constraint letter is more general than the previous one, use it.
4049 int Generality = getConstraintGenerality(CType);
4050 if (Generality > BestGenerality) {
4051 BestType = CType;
4052 BestIdx = i;
4053 BestGenerality = Generality;
4054 }
4055 }
4056
4057 OpInfo.ConstraintCode = OpInfo.Codes[BestIdx];
4058 OpInfo.ConstraintType = BestType;
4059}
4060
4061/// Determines the constraint code and constraint type to use for the specific
4062/// AsmOperandInfo, setting OpInfo.ConstraintCode and OpInfo.ConstraintType.
4063void TargetLowering::ComputeConstraintToUse(AsmOperandInfo &OpInfo,
4064 SDValue Op,
4065 SelectionDAG *DAG) const {
4066 assert(!OpInfo.Codes.empty() && "Must have at least one constraint");
4067
4068 // Single-letter constraints ('r') are very common.
4069 if (OpInfo.Codes.size() == 1) {
4070 OpInfo.ConstraintCode = OpInfo.Codes[0];
4071 OpInfo.ConstraintType = getConstraintType(OpInfo.ConstraintCode);
4072 } else {
4073 ChooseConstraint(OpInfo, *this, Op, DAG);
4074 }
4075
4076 // 'X' matches anything.
4077 if (OpInfo.ConstraintCode == "X" && OpInfo.CallOperandVal) {
4078 // Labels and constants are handled elsewhere ('X' is the only thing
4079 // that matches labels). For Functions, the type here is the type of
4080 // the result, which is not what we want to look at; leave them alone.
4081 Value *v = OpInfo.CallOperandVal;
4082 if (isa<BasicBlock>(v) || isa<ConstantInt>(v) || isa<Function>(v)) {
4083 OpInfo.CallOperandVal = v;
4084 return;
4085 }
4086
4087 if (Op.getNode() && Op.getOpcode() == ISD::TargetBlockAddress)
4088 return;
4089
4090 // Otherwise, try to resolve it to something we know about by looking at
4091 // the actual operand type.
4092 if (const char *Repl = LowerXConstraint(OpInfo.ConstraintVT)) {
4093 OpInfo.ConstraintCode = Repl;
4094 OpInfo.ConstraintType = getConstraintType(OpInfo.ConstraintCode);
4095 }
4096 }
4097}
4098
4099/// Given an exact SDIV by a constant, create a multiplication
4100/// with the multiplicative inverse of the constant.
4101static SDValue BuildExactSDIV(const TargetLowering &TLI, SDNode *N,
4102 const SDLoc &dl, SelectionDAG &DAG,
4103 SmallVectorImpl<SDNode *> &Created) {
4104 SDValue Op0 = N->getOperand(0);
4105 SDValue Op1 = N->getOperand(1);
4106 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
4107 EVT SVT = VT.getScalarType();
4108 EVT ShVT = TLI.getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout());
4109 EVT ShSVT = ShVT.getScalarType();
4110
4111 bool UseSRA = false;
4112 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Shifts, Factors;
4113
4114 auto BuildSDIVPattern = [&](ConstantSDNode *C) {
4115 if (C->isNullValue())
4116 return false;
4117 APInt Divisor = C->getAPIntValue();
4118 unsigned Shift = Divisor.countTrailingZeros();
4119 if (Shift) {
4120 Divisor.ashrInPlace(Shift);
4121 UseSRA = true;
4122 }
4123 // Calculate the multiplicative inverse, using Newton's method.
4124 APInt t;
4125 APInt Factor = Divisor;
4126 while ((t = Divisor * Factor) != 1)
4127 Factor *= APInt(Divisor.getBitWidth(), 2) - t;
4128 Shifts.push_back(DAG.getConstant(Shift, dl, ShSVT));
4129 Factors.push_back(DAG.getConstant(Factor, dl, SVT));
4130 return true;
4131 };
4132
4133 // Collect all magic values from the build vector.
4134 if (!ISD::matchUnaryPredicate(Op1, BuildSDIVPattern))
4135 return SDValue();
4136
4137 SDValue Shift, Factor;
4138 if (VT.isVector()) {
4139 Shift = DAG.getBuildVector(ShVT, dl, Shifts);
4140 Factor = DAG.getBuildVector(VT, dl, Factors);
4141 } else {
4142 Shift = Shifts[0];
4143 Factor = Factors[0];
4144 }
4145
4146 SDValue Res = Op0;
4147
4148 // Shift the value upfront if it is even, so the LSB is one.
4149 if (UseSRA) {
4150 // TODO: For UDIV use SRL instead of SRA.
4151 SDNodeFlags Flags;
4152 Flags.setExact(true);
4153 Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, dl, VT, Res, Shift, Flags);
4154 Created.push_back(Res.getNode());
4155 }
4156
4157 return DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, VT, Res, Factor);
4158}
4159
4160SDValue TargetLowering::BuildSDIVPow2(SDNode *N, const APInt &Divisor,
4161 SelectionDAG &DAG,
4162 SmallVectorImpl<SDNode *> &Created) const {
4163 AttributeList Attr = DAG.getMachineFunction().getFunction().getAttributes();
4164 const TargetLowering &TLI = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo();
4165 if (TLI.isIntDivCheap(N->getValueType(0), Attr))
4166 return SDValue(N, 0); // Lower SDIV as SDIV
4167 return SDValue();
4168}
4169
4170/// Given an ISD::SDIV node expressing a divide by constant,
4171/// return a DAG expression to select that will generate the same value by
4172/// multiplying by a magic number.
4173/// Ref: "Hacker's Delight" or "The PowerPC Compiler Writer's Guide".
4174SDValue TargetLowering::BuildSDIV(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
4175 bool IsAfterLegalization,
4176 SmallVectorImpl<SDNode *> &Created) const {
4177 SDLoc dl(N);
4178 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
4179 EVT SVT = VT.getScalarType();
4180 EVT ShVT = getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout());
4181 EVT ShSVT = ShVT.getScalarType();
4182 unsigned EltBits = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
4183
4184 // Check to see if we can do this.
4185 // FIXME: We should be more aggressive here.
4186 if (!isTypeLegal(VT))
4187 return SDValue();
4188
4189 // If the sdiv has an 'exact' bit we can use a simpler lowering.
4190 if (N->getFlags().hasExact())
4191 return BuildExactSDIV(*this, N, dl, DAG, Created);
4192
4193 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> MagicFactors, Factors, Shifts, ShiftMasks;
4194
4195 auto BuildSDIVPattern = [&](ConstantSDNode *C) {
4196 if (C->isNullValue())
4197 return false;
4198
4199 const APInt &Divisor = C->getAPIntValue();
4200 APInt::ms magics = Divisor.magic();
4201 int NumeratorFactor = 0;
4202 int ShiftMask = -1;
4203
4204 if (Divisor.isOneValue() || Divisor.isAllOnesValue()) {
4205 // If d is +1/-1, we just multiply the numerator by +1/-1.
4206 NumeratorFactor = Divisor.getSExtValue();
4207 magics.m = 0;
4208 magics.s = 0;
4209 ShiftMask = 0;
4210 } else if (Divisor.isStrictlyPositive() && magics.m.isNegative()) {
4211 // If d > 0 and m < 0, add the numerator.
4212 NumeratorFactor = 1;
4213 } else if (Divisor.isNegative() && magics.m.isStrictlyPositive()) {
4214 // If d < 0 and m > 0, subtract the numerator.
4215 NumeratorFactor = -1;
4216 }
4217
4218 MagicFactors.push_back(DAG.getConstant(magics.m, dl, SVT));
4219 Factors.push_back(DAG.getConstant(NumeratorFactor, dl, SVT));
4220 Shifts.push_back(DAG.getConstant(magics.s, dl, ShSVT));
4221 ShiftMasks.push_back(DAG.getConstant(ShiftMask, dl, SVT));
4222 return true;
4223 };
4224
4225 SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0);
4226 SDValue N1 = N->getOperand(1);
4227
4228 // Collect the shifts / magic values from each element.
4229 if (!ISD::matchUnaryPredicate(N1, BuildSDIVPattern))
4230 return SDValue();
4231
4232 SDValue MagicFactor, Factor, Shift, ShiftMask;
4233 if (VT.isVector()) {
4234 MagicFactor = DAG.getBuildVector(VT, dl, MagicFactors);
4235 Factor = DAG.getBuildVector(VT, dl, Factors);
4236 Shift = DAG.getBuildVector(ShVT, dl, Shifts);
4237 ShiftMask = DAG.getBuildVector(VT, dl, ShiftMasks);
4238 } else {
4239 MagicFactor = MagicFactors[0];
4240 Factor = Factors[0];
4241 Shift = Shifts[0];
4242 ShiftMask = ShiftMasks[0];
4243 }
4244
4245 // Multiply the numerator (operand 0) by the magic value.
4246 // FIXME: We should support doing a MUL in a wider type.
4247 SDValue Q;
4248 if (IsAfterLegalization ? isOperationLegal(ISD::MULHS, VT)
4249 : isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::MULHS, VT))
4250 Q = DAG.getNode(ISD::MULHS, dl, VT, N0, MagicFactor);
4251 else if (IsAfterLegalization ? isOperationLegal(ISD::SMUL_LOHI, VT)
4252 : isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SMUL_LOHI, VT)) {
4253 SDValue LoHi =
4254 DAG.getNode(ISD::SMUL_LOHI, dl, DAG.getVTList(VT, VT), N0, MagicFactor);
4255 Q = SDValue(LoHi.getNode(), 1);
4256 } else
4257 return SDValue(); // No mulhs or equivalent.
4258 Created.push_back(Q.getNode());
4259
4260 // (Optionally) Add/subtract the numerator using Factor.
4261 Factor = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, VT, N0, Factor);
4262 Created.push_back(Factor.getNode());
4263 Q = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, VT, Q, Factor);
4264 Created.push_back(Q.getNode());
4265
4266 // Shift right algebraic by shift value.
4267 Q = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, dl, VT, Q, Shift);
4268 Created.push_back(Q.getNode());
4269
4270 // Extract the sign bit, mask it and add it to the quotient.
4271 SDValue SignShift = DAG.getConstant(EltBits - 1, dl, ShVT);
4272 SDValue T = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Q, SignShift);
4273 Created.push_back(T.getNode());
4274 T = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, T, ShiftMask);
4275 Created.push_back(T.getNode());
4276 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, VT, Q, T);
4277}
4278
4279/// Given an ISD::UDIV node expressing a divide by constant,
4280/// return a DAG expression to select that will generate the same value by
4281/// multiplying by a magic number.
4282/// Ref: "Hacker's Delight" or "The PowerPC Compiler Writer's Guide".
4283SDValue TargetLowering::BuildUDIV(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
4284 bool IsAfterLegalization,
4285 SmallVectorImpl<SDNode *> &Created) const {
4286 SDLoc dl(N);
4287 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
4288 EVT SVT = VT.getScalarType();
4289 EVT ShVT = getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout());
4290 EVT ShSVT = ShVT.getScalarType();
4291 unsigned EltBits = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
4292
4293 // Check to see if we can do this.
4294 // FIXME: We should be more aggressive here.
4295 if (!isTypeLegal(VT))
4296 return SDValue();
4297
4298 bool UseNPQ = false;
4299 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> PreShifts, PostShifts, MagicFactors, NPQFactors;
4300
4301 auto BuildUDIVPattern = [&](ConstantSDNode *C) {
4302 if (C->isNullValue())
4303 return false;
4304 // FIXME: We should use a narrower constant when the upper
4305 // bits are known to be zero.
4306 APInt Divisor = C->getAPIntValue();
4307 APInt::mu magics = Divisor.magicu();
4308 unsigned PreShift = 0, PostShift = 0;
4309
4310 // If the divisor is even, we can avoid using the expensive fixup by
4311 // shifting the divided value upfront.
4312 if (magics.a != 0 && !Divisor[0]) {
4313 PreShift = Divisor.countTrailingZeros();
4314 // Get magic number for the shifted divisor.
4315 magics = Divisor.lshr(PreShift).magicu(PreShift);
4316 assert(magics.a == 0 && "Should use cheap fixup now");
4317 }
4318
4319 APInt Magic = magics.m;
4320
4321 unsigned SelNPQ;
4322 if (magics.a == 0 || Divisor.isOneValue()) {
4323 assert(magics.s < Divisor.getBitWidth() &&
4324 "We shouldn't generate an undefined shift!");
4325 PostShift = magics.s;
4326 SelNPQ = false;
4327 } else {
4328 PostShift = magics.s - 1;
4329 SelNPQ = true;
4330 }
4331
4332 PreShifts.push_back(DAG.getConstant(PreShift, dl, ShSVT));
4333 MagicFactors.push_back(DAG.getConstant(Magic, dl, SVT));
4334 NPQFactors.push_back(
4335 DAG.getConstant(SelNPQ ? APInt::getOneBitSet(EltBits, EltBits - 1)
4336 : APInt::getNullValue(EltBits),
4337 dl, SVT));
4338 PostShifts.push_back(DAG.getConstant(PostShift, dl, ShSVT));
4339 UseNPQ |= SelNPQ;
4340 return true;
4341 };
4342
4343 SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0);
4344 SDValue N1 = N->getOperand(1);
4345
4346 // Collect the shifts/magic values from each element.
4347 if (!ISD::matchUnaryPredicate(N1, BuildUDIVPattern))
4348 return SDValue();
4349
4350 SDValue PreShift, PostShift, MagicFactor, NPQFactor;
4351 if (VT.isVector()) {
4352 PreShift = DAG.getBuildVector(ShVT, dl, PreShifts);
4353 MagicFactor = DAG.getBuildVector(VT, dl, MagicFactors);
4354 NPQFactor = DAG.getBuildVector(VT, dl, NPQFactors);
4355 PostShift = DAG.getBuildVector(ShVT, dl, PostShifts);
4356 } else {
4357 PreShift = PreShifts[0];
4358 MagicFactor = MagicFactors[0];
4359 PostShift = PostShifts[0];
4360 }
4361
4362 SDValue Q = N0;
4363 Q = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Q, PreShift);
4364 Created.push_back(Q.getNode());
4365
4366 // FIXME: We should support doing a MUL in a wider type.
4367 auto GetMULHU = [&](SDValue X, SDValue Y) {
4368 if (IsAfterLegalization ? isOperationLegal(ISD::MULHU, VT)
4369 : isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::MULHU, VT))
4370 return DAG.getNode(ISD::MULHU, dl, VT, X, Y);
4371 if (IsAfterLegalization ? isOperationLegal(ISD::UMUL_LOHI, VT)
4372 : isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::UMUL_LOHI, VT)) {
4373 SDValue LoHi =
4374 DAG.getNode(ISD::UMUL_LOHI, dl, DAG.getVTList(VT, VT), X, Y);
4375 return SDValue(LoHi.getNode(), 1);
4376 }
4377 return SDValue(); // No mulhu or equivalent
4378 };
4379
4380 // Multiply the numerator (operand 0) by the magic value.
4381 Q = GetMULHU(Q, MagicFactor);
4382 if (!Q)
4383 return SDValue();
4384
4385 Created.push_back(Q.getNode());
4386
4387 if (UseNPQ) {
4388 SDValue NPQ = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, VT, N0, Q);
4389 Created.push_back(NPQ.getNode());
4390
4391 // For vectors we might have a mix of non-NPQ/NPQ paths, so use
4392 // MULHU to act as a SRL-by-1 for NPQ, else multiply by zero.
4393 if (VT.isVector())
4394 NPQ = GetMULHU(NPQ, NPQFactor);
4395 else
4396 NPQ = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, NPQ, DAG.getConstant(1, dl, ShVT));
4397
4398 Created.push_back(NPQ.getNode());
4399
4400 Q = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, VT, NPQ, Q);
4401 Created.push_back(Q.getNode());
4402 }
4403
4404 Q = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Q, PostShift);
4405 Created.push_back(Q.getNode());
4406
4407 SDValue One = DAG.getConstant(1, dl, VT);
4408 SDValue IsOne = DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, N1, One, ISD::SETEQ);
4409 return DAG.getSelect(dl, VT, IsOne, N0, Q);
4410}
4411
4412bool TargetLowering::
4413verifyReturnAddressArgumentIsConstant(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
4414 if (!isa<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(0))) {
4415 DAG.getContext()->emitError("argument to '__builtin_return_address' must "
4416 "be a constant integer");
4417 return true;
4418 }
4419
4420 return false;
4421}
4422
4423//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
4424// Legalization Utilities
4425//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
4426
4427bool TargetLowering::expandMUL_LOHI(unsigned Opcode, EVT VT, SDLoc dl,
4428 SDValue LHS, SDValue RHS,
4429 SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &Result,
4430 EVT HiLoVT, SelectionDAG &DAG,
4431 MulExpansionKind Kind, SDValue LL,
4432 SDValue LH, SDValue RL, SDValue RH) const {
4433 assert(Opcode == ISD::MUL || Opcode == ISD::UMUL_LOHI ||
4434 Opcode == ISD::SMUL_LOHI);
4435
4436 bool HasMULHS = (Kind == MulExpansionKind::Always) ||
4437 isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::MULHS, HiLoVT);
4438 bool HasMULHU = (Kind == MulExpansionKind::Always) ||
4439 isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::MULHU, HiLoVT);
4440 bool HasSMUL_LOHI = (Kind == MulExpansionKind::Always) ||
4441 isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SMUL_LOHI, HiLoVT);
4442 bool HasUMUL_LOHI = (Kind == MulExpansionKind::Always) ||
4443 isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::UMUL_LOHI, HiLoVT);
4444
4445 if (!HasMULHU && !HasMULHS && !HasUMUL_LOHI && !HasSMUL_LOHI)
4446 return false;
4447
4448 unsigned OuterBitSize = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
4449 unsigned InnerBitSize = HiLoVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
4450 unsigned LHSSB = DAG.ComputeNumSignBits(LHS);
4451 unsigned RHSSB = DAG.ComputeNumSignBits(RHS);
4452
4453 // LL, LH, RL, and RH must be either all NULL or all set to a value.
4454 assert((LL.getNode() && LH.getNode() && RL.getNode() && RH.getNode()) ||
4455 (!LL.getNode() && !LH.getNode() && !RL.getNode() && !RH.getNode()));
4456
4457 SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(HiLoVT, HiLoVT);
4458 auto MakeMUL_LOHI = [&](SDValue L, SDValue R, SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi,
4459 bool Signed) -> bool {
4460 if ((Signed && HasSMUL_LOHI) || (!Signed && HasUMUL_LOHI)) {
4461 Lo = DAG.getNode(Signed ? ISD::SMUL_LOHI : ISD::UMUL_LOHI, dl, VTs, L, R);
4462 Hi = SDValue(Lo.getNode(), 1);
4463 return true;
4464 }
4465 if ((Signed && HasMULHS) || (!Signed && HasMULHU)) {
4466 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, HiLoVT, L, R);
4467 Hi = DAG.getNode(Signed ? ISD::MULHS : ISD::MULHU, dl, HiLoVT, L, R);
4468 return true;
4469 }
4470 return false;
4471 };
4472
4473 SDValue Lo, Hi;
4474
4475 if (!LL.getNode() && !RL.getNode() &&
4476 isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::TRUNCATE, HiLoVT)) {
4477 LL = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, HiLoVT, LHS);
4478 RL = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, HiLoVT, RHS);
4479 }
4480
4481 if (!LL.getNode())
4482 return false;
4483
4484 APInt HighMask = APInt::getHighBitsSet(OuterBitSize, InnerBitSize);
4485 if (DAG.MaskedValueIsZero(LHS, HighMask) &&
4486 DAG.MaskedValueIsZero(RHS, HighMask)) {
4487 // The inputs are both zero-extended.
4488 if (MakeMUL_LOHI(LL, RL, Lo, Hi, false)) {
4489 Result.push_back(Lo);
4490 Result.push_back(Hi);
4491 if (Opcode != ISD::MUL) {
4492 SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, HiLoVT);
4493 Result.push_back(Zero);
