4494 Result.push_back(Zero);
4495 }
4496 return true;
4497 }
4498 }
4499
4500 if (!VT.isVector() && Opcode == ISD::MUL && LHSSB > InnerBitSize &&
4501 RHSSB > InnerBitSize) {
4502 // The input values are both sign-extended.
4503 // TODO non-MUL case?
4504 if (MakeMUL_LOHI(LL, RL, Lo, Hi, true)) {
4505 Result.push_back(Lo);
4506 Result.push_back(Hi);
4507 return true;
4508 }
4509 }
4510
4511 unsigned ShiftAmount = OuterBitSize - InnerBitSize;
4512 EVT ShiftAmountTy = getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout());
4513 if (APInt::getMaxValue(ShiftAmountTy.getSizeInBits()).ult(ShiftAmount)) {
4514 // FIXME getShiftAmountTy does not always return a sensible result when VT
4515 // is an illegal type, and so the type may be too small to fit the shift
4516 // amount. Override it with i32. The shift will have to be legalized.
4517 ShiftAmountTy = MVT::i32;
4518 }
4519 SDValue Shift = DAG.getConstant(ShiftAmount, dl, ShiftAmountTy);
4520
4521 if (!LH.getNode() && !RH.getNode() &&
4522 isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SRL, VT) &&
4523 isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::TRUNCATE, HiLoVT)) {
4524 LH = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, LHS, Shift);
4525 LH = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, HiLoVT, LH);
4526 RH = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, RHS, Shift);
4527 RH = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, HiLoVT, RH);
4528 }
4529
4530 if (!LH.getNode())
4531 return false;
4532
4533 if (!MakeMUL_LOHI(LL, RL, Lo, Hi, false))
4534 return false;
4535
4536 Result.push_back(Lo);
4537
4538 if (Opcode == ISD::MUL) {
4539 RH = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, HiLoVT, LL, RH);
4540 LH = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, HiLoVT, LH, RL);
4541 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, HiLoVT, Hi, RH);
4542 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, HiLoVT, Hi, LH);
4543 Result.push_back(Hi);
4544 return true;
4545 }
4546
4547 // Compute the full width result.
4548 auto Merge = [&](SDValue Lo, SDValue Hi) -> SDValue {
4549 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, dl, VT, Lo);
4550 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, dl, VT, Hi);
4551 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Hi, Shift);
4552 return DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Lo, Hi);
4553 };
4554
4555 SDValue Next = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, dl, VT, Hi);
4556 if (!MakeMUL_LOHI(LL, RH, Lo, Hi, false))
4557 return false;
4558
4559 // This is effectively the add part of a multiply-add of half-sized operands,
4560 // so it cannot overflow.
4561 Next = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, VT, Next, Merge(Lo, Hi));
4562
4563 if (!MakeMUL_LOHI(LH, RL, Lo, Hi, false))
4564 return false;
4565
4566 SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, HiLoVT);
4567 EVT BoolType = getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), VT);
4568
4569 bool UseGlue = (isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::ADDC, VT) &&
4570 isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::ADDE, VT));
4571 if (UseGlue)
4572 Next = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADDC, dl, DAG.getVTList(VT, MVT::Glue), Next,
4573 Merge(Lo, Hi));
4574 else
4575 Next = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADDCARRY, dl, DAG.getVTList(VT, BoolType), Next,
4576 Merge(Lo, Hi), DAG.getConstant(0, dl, BoolType));
4577
4578 SDValue Carry = Next.getValue(1);
4579 Result.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, HiLoVT, Next));
4580 Next = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Next, Shift);
4581
4582 if (!MakeMUL_LOHI(LH, RH, Lo, Hi, Opcode == ISD::SMUL_LOHI))
4583 return false;
4584
4585 if (UseGlue)
4586 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADDE, dl, DAG.getVTList(HiLoVT, MVT::Glue), Hi, Zero,
4587 Carry);
4588 else
4589 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADDCARRY, dl, DAG.getVTList(HiLoVT, BoolType), Hi,
4590 Zero, Carry);
4591
4592 Next = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, VT, Next, Merge(Lo, Hi));
4593
4594 if (Opcode == ISD::SMUL_LOHI) {
4595 SDValue NextSub = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, VT, Next,
4596 DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, dl, VT, RL));
4597 Next = DAG.getSelectCC(dl, LH, Zero, NextSub, Next, ISD::SETLT);
4598
4599 NextSub = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, VT, Next,
4600 DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, dl, VT, LL));
4601 Next = DAG.getSelectCC(dl, RH, Zero, NextSub, Next, ISD::SETLT);
4602 }
4603
4604 Result.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, HiLoVT, Next));
4605 Next = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Next, Shift);
4606 Result.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, HiLoVT, Next));
4607 return true;
4608}
4609
4610bool TargetLowering::expandMUL(SDNode *N, SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi, EVT HiLoVT,
4611 SelectionDAG &DAG, MulExpansionKind Kind,
4612 SDValue LL, SDValue LH, SDValue RL,
4613 SDValue RH) const {
4614 SmallVector<SDValue, 2> Result;
4615 bool Ok = expandMUL_LOHI(N->getOpcode(), N->getValueType(0), N,
4616 N->getOperand(0), N->getOperand(1), Result, HiLoVT,
4617 DAG, Kind, LL, LH, RL, RH);
4618 if (Ok) {
4619 assert(Result.size() == 2);
4620 Lo = Result[0];
4621 Hi = Result[1];
4622 }
4623 return Ok;
4624}
4625
4626bool TargetLowering::expandFunnelShift(SDNode *Node, SDValue &Result,
4627 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
4628 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
4629
4630 if (VT.isVector() && (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SHL, VT) ||
4631 !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SRL, VT) ||
4632 !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SUB, VT) ||
4633 !isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::OR, VT)))
4634 return false;
4635
4636 // fshl: (X << (Z % BW)) | (Y >> (BW - (Z % BW)))
4637 // fshr: (X << (BW - (Z % BW))) | (Y >> (Z % BW))
4638 SDValue X = Node->getOperand(0);
4639 SDValue Y = Node->getOperand(1);
4640 SDValue Z = Node->getOperand(2);
4641
4642 unsigned EltSizeInBits = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
4643 bool IsFSHL = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::FSHL;
4644 SDLoc DL(SDValue(Node, 0));
4645
4646 EVT ShVT = Z.getValueType();
4647 SDValue BitWidthC = DAG.getConstant(EltSizeInBits, DL, ShVT);
4648 SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, ShVT);
4649
4650 SDValue ShAmt;
4651 if (isPowerOf2_32(EltSizeInBits)) {
4652 SDValue Mask = DAG.getConstant(EltSizeInBits - 1, DL, ShVT);
4653 ShAmt = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, ShVT, Z, Mask);
4654 } else {
4655 ShAmt = DAG.getNode(ISD::UREM, DL, ShVT, Z, BitWidthC);
4656 }
4657
4658 SDValue InvShAmt = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, ShVT, BitWidthC, ShAmt);
4659 SDValue ShX = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, X, IsFSHL ? ShAmt : InvShAmt);
4660 SDValue ShY = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VT, Y, IsFSHL ? InvShAmt : ShAmt);
4661 SDValue Or = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, VT, ShX, ShY);
4662
4663 // If (Z % BW == 0), then the opposite direction shift is shift-by-bitwidth,
4664 // and that is undefined. We must compare and select to avoid UB.
4665 EVT CCVT = getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), ShVT);
4666
4667 // For fshl, 0-shift returns the 1st arg (X).
4668 // For fshr, 0-shift returns the 2nd arg (Y).
4669 SDValue IsZeroShift = DAG.getSetCC(DL, CCVT, ShAmt, Zero, ISD::SETEQ);
4670 Result = DAG.getSelect(DL, VT, IsZeroShift, IsFSHL ? X : Y, Or);
4671 return true;
4672}
4673
4674// TODO: Merge with expandFunnelShift.
4675bool TargetLowering::expandROT(SDNode *Node, SDValue &Result,
4676 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
4677 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
4678 unsigned EltSizeInBits = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
4679 bool IsLeft = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::ROTL;
4680 SDValue Op0 = Node->getOperand(0);
4681 SDValue Op1 = Node->getOperand(1);
4682 SDLoc DL(SDValue(Node, 0));
4683
4684 EVT ShVT = Op1.getValueType();
4685 SDValue BitWidthC = DAG.getConstant(EltSizeInBits, DL, ShVT);
4686
4687 // If a rotate in the other direction is legal, use it.
4688 unsigned RevRot = IsLeft ? ISD::ROTR : ISD::ROTL;
4689 if (isOperationLegal(RevRot, VT)) {
4690 SDValue Sub = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, ShVT, BitWidthC, Op1);
4691 Result = DAG.getNode(RevRot, DL, VT, Op0, Sub);
4692 return true;
4693 }
4694
4695 if (VT.isVector() && (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SHL, VT) ||
4696 !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SRL, VT) ||
4697 !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SUB, VT) ||
4698 !isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::OR, VT) ||
4699 !isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::AND, VT)))
4700 return false;
4701
4702 // Otherwise,
4703 // (rotl x, c) -> (or (shl x, (and c, w-1)), (srl x, (and w-c, w-1)))
4704 // (rotr x, c) -> (or (srl x, (and c, w-1)), (shl x, (and w-c, w-1)))
4705 //
4706 assert(isPowerOf2_32(EltSizeInBits) && EltSizeInBits > 1 &&
4707 "Expecting the type bitwidth to be a power of 2");
4708 unsigned ShOpc = IsLeft ? ISD::SHL : ISD::SRL;
4709 unsigned HsOpc = IsLeft ? ISD::SRL : ISD::SHL;
4710 SDValue BitWidthMinusOneC = DAG.getConstant(EltSizeInBits - 1, DL, ShVT);
4711 SDValue NegOp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, ShVT, BitWidthC, Op1);
4712 SDValue And0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, ShVT, Op1, BitWidthMinusOneC);
4713 SDValue And1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, ShVT, NegOp1, BitWidthMinusOneC);
4714 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, VT, DAG.getNode(ShOpc, DL, VT, Op0, And0),
4715 DAG.getNode(HsOpc, DL, VT, Op0, And1));
4716 return true;
4717}
4718
4719bool TargetLowering::expandFP_TO_SINT(SDNode *Node, SDValue &Result,
4720 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
4721 SDValue Src = Node->getOperand(0);
4722 EVT SrcVT = Src.getValueType();
4723 EVT DstVT = Node->getValueType(0);
4724 SDLoc dl(SDValue(Node, 0));
4725
4726 // FIXME: Only f32 to i64 conversions are supported.
4727 if (SrcVT != MVT::f32 || DstVT != MVT::i64)
4728 return false;
4729
4730 // Expand f32 -> i64 conversion
4731 // This algorithm comes from compiler-rt's implementation of fixsfdi:
4732 // https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/blob/master/compiler-rt/lib/builtins/fixsfdi.c
4733 unsigned SrcEltBits = SrcVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
4734 EVT IntVT = SrcVT.changeTypeToInteger();
4735 EVT IntShVT = getShiftAmountTy(IntVT, DAG.getDataLayout());
4736
4737 SDValue ExponentMask = DAG.getConstant(0x7F800000, dl, IntVT);
4738 SDValue ExponentLoBit = DAG.getConstant(23, dl, IntVT);
4739 SDValue Bias = DAG.getConstant(127, dl, IntVT);
4740 SDValue SignMask = DAG.getConstant(APInt::getSignMask(SrcEltBits), dl, IntVT);
4741 SDValue SignLowBit = DAG.getConstant(SrcEltBits - 1, dl, IntVT);
4742 SDValue MantissaMask = DAG.getConstant(0x007FFFFF, dl, IntVT);
4743
4744 SDValue Bits = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, IntVT, Src);
4745
4746 SDValue ExponentBits = DAG.getNode(
4747 ISD::SRL, dl, IntVT, DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, IntVT, Bits, ExponentMask),
4748 DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(ExponentLoBit, dl, IntShVT));
4749 SDValue Exponent = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, IntVT, ExponentBits, Bias);
4750
4751 SDValue Sign = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, dl, IntVT,
4752 DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, IntVT, Bits, SignMask),
4753 DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(SignLowBit, dl, IntShVT));
4754 Sign = DAG.getSExtOrTrunc(Sign, dl, DstVT);
4755
4756 SDValue R = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, IntVT,
4757 DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, IntVT, Bits, MantissaMask),
4758 DAG.getConstant(0x00800000, dl, IntVT));
4759
4760 R = DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(R, dl, DstVT);
4761
4762 R = DAG.getSelectCC(
4763 dl, Exponent, ExponentLoBit,
4764 DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, DstVT, R,
4765 DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(
4766 DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, IntVT, Exponent, ExponentLoBit),
4767 dl, IntShVT)),
4768 DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, DstVT, R,
4769 DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(
4770 DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, IntVT, ExponentLoBit, Exponent),
4771 dl, IntShVT)),
4772 ISD::SETGT);
4773
4774 SDValue Ret = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, DstVT,
4775 DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, dl, DstVT, R, Sign), Sign);
4776
4777 Result = DAG.getSelectCC(dl, Exponent, DAG.getConstant(0, dl, IntVT),
4778 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, DstVT), Ret, ISD::SETLT);
4779 return true;
4780}
4781
4782bool TargetLowering::expandFP_TO_UINT(SDNode *Node, SDValue &Result,
4783 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
4784 SDLoc dl(SDValue(Node, 0));
4785 SDValue Src = Node->getOperand(0);
4786
4787 EVT SrcVT = Src.getValueType();
4788 EVT DstVT = Node->getValueType(0);
4789 EVT SetCCVT =
4790 getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), SrcVT);
4791
4792 // Only expand vector types if we have the appropriate vector bit operations.
4793 if (DstVT.isVector() && (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::FP_TO_SINT, DstVT) ||
4794 !isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::XOR, SrcVT)))
4795 return false;
4796
4797 // If the maximum float value is smaller then the signed integer range,
4798 // the destination signmask can't be represented by the float, so we can
4799 // just use FP_TO_SINT directly.
4800 const fltSemantics &APFSem = DAG.EVTToAPFloatSemantics(SrcVT);
4801 APFloat APF(APFSem, APInt::getNullValue(SrcVT.getScalarSizeInBits()));
4802 APInt SignMask = APInt::getSignMask(DstVT.getScalarSizeInBits());
4803 if (APFloat::opOverflow &
4804 APF.convertFromAPInt(SignMask, false, APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven)) {
4805 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_TO_SINT, dl, DstVT, Src);
4806 return true;
4807 }
4808
4809 SDValue Cst = DAG.getConstantFP(APF, dl, SrcVT);
4810 SDValue Sel = DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCVT, Src, Cst, ISD::SETLT);
4811
4812 bool Strict = shouldUseStrictFP_TO_INT(SrcVT, DstVT, /*IsSigned*/ false);
4813 if (Strict) {
4814 // Expand based on maximum range of FP_TO_SINT, if the value exceeds the
4815 // signmask then offset (the result of which should be fully representable).
4816 // Sel = Src < 0x8000000000000000
4817 // Val = select Sel, Src, Src - 0x8000000000000000
4818 // Ofs = select Sel, 0, 0x8000000000000000
4819 // Result = fp_to_sint(Val) ^ Ofs
4820
4821 // TODO: Should any fast-math-flags be set for the FSUB?
4822 SDValue Val = DAG.getSelect(dl, SrcVT, Sel, Src,
4823 DAG.getNode(ISD::FSUB, dl, SrcVT, Src, Cst));
4824 SDValue Ofs = DAG.getSelect(dl, DstVT, Sel, DAG.getConstant(0, dl, DstVT),
4825 DAG.getConstant(SignMask, dl, DstVT));
4826 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, dl, DstVT,
4827 DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_TO_SINT, dl, DstVT, Val), Ofs);
4828 } else {
4829 // Expand based on maximum range of FP_TO_SINT:
4830 // True = fp_to_sint(Src)
4831 // False = 0x8000000000000000 + fp_to_sint(Src - 0x8000000000000000)
4832 // Result = select (Src < 0x8000000000000000), True, False
4833
4834 SDValue True = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_TO_SINT, dl, DstVT, Src);
4835 // TODO: Should any fast-math-flags be set for the FSUB?
4836 SDValue False = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_TO_SINT, dl, DstVT,
4837 DAG.getNode(ISD::FSUB, dl, SrcVT, Src, Cst));
4838 False = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, dl, DstVT, False,
4839 DAG.getConstant(SignMask, dl, DstVT));
4840 Result = DAG.getSelect(dl, DstVT, Sel, True, False);
4841 }
4842 return true;
4843}
4844
4845bool TargetLowering::expandUINT_TO_FP(SDNode *Node, SDValue &Result,
4846 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
4847 SDValue Src = Node->getOperand(0);
4848 EVT SrcVT = Src.getValueType();
4849 EVT DstVT = Node->getValueType(0);
4850
4851 if (SrcVT.getScalarType() != MVT::i64)
4852 return false;
4853
4854 SDLoc dl(SDValue(Node, 0));
4855 EVT ShiftVT = getShiftAmountTy(SrcVT, DAG.getDataLayout());
4856
4857 if (DstVT.getScalarType() == MVT::f32) {
4858 // Only expand vector types if we have the appropriate vector bit
4859 // operations.
4860 if (SrcVT.isVector() &&
4861 (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SRL, SrcVT) ||
4862 !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::FADD, DstVT) ||
4863 !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SINT_TO_FP, SrcVT) ||
4864 !isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::OR, SrcVT) ||
4865 !isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::AND, SrcVT)))
4866 return false;
4867
4868 // For unsigned conversions, convert them to signed conversions using the
4869 // algorithm from the x86_64 __floatundidf in compiler_rt.
4870 SDValue Fast = DAG.getNode(ISD::SINT_TO_FP, dl, DstVT, Src);
4871
4872 SDValue ShiftConst = DAG.getConstant(1, dl, ShiftVT);
4873 SDValue Shr = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, SrcVT, Src, ShiftConst);
4874 SDValue AndConst = DAG.getConstant(1, dl, SrcVT);
4875 SDValue And = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, SrcVT, Src, AndConst);
4876 SDValue Or = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, SrcVT, And, Shr);
4877
4878 SDValue SignCvt = DAG.getNode(ISD::SINT_TO_FP, dl, DstVT, Or);
4879 SDValue Slow = DAG.getNode(ISD::FADD, dl, DstVT, SignCvt, SignCvt);
4880
4881 // TODO: This really should be implemented using a branch rather than a
4882 // select. We happen to get lucky and machinesink does the right
4883 // thing most of the time. This would be a good candidate for a
4884 // pseudo-op, or, even better, for whole-function isel.
4885 EVT SetCCVT =
4886 getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), SrcVT);
4887
4888 SDValue SignBitTest = DAG.getSetCC(
4889 dl, SetCCVT, Src, DAG.getConstant(0, dl, SrcVT), ISD::SETLT);
4890 Result = DAG.getSelect(dl, DstVT, SignBitTest, Slow, Fast);
4891 return true;
4892 }
4893
4894 if (DstVT.getScalarType() == MVT::f64) {
4895 // Only expand vector types if we have the appropriate vector bit
4896 // operations.
4897 if (SrcVT.isVector() &&
4898 (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SRL, SrcVT) ||
4899 !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::FADD, DstVT) ||
4900 !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::FSUB, DstVT) ||
4901 !isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::OR, SrcVT) ||
4902 !isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::AND, SrcVT)))
4903 return false;
4904
4905 // Implementation of unsigned i64 to f64 following the algorithm in
4906 // __floatundidf in compiler_rt. This implementation has the advantage
4907 // of performing rounding correctly, both in the default rounding mode
4908 // and in all alternate rounding modes.
4909 SDValue TwoP52 = DAG.getConstant(UINT64_C(0x4330000000000000), dl, SrcVT);
4910 SDValue TwoP84PlusTwoP52 = DAG.getConstantFP(
4911 BitsToDouble(UINT64_C(0x4530000000100000)), dl, DstVT);
4912 SDValue TwoP84 = DAG.getConstant(UINT64_C(0x4530000000000000), dl, SrcVT);
4913 SDValue LoMask = DAG.getConstant(UINT64_C(0x00000000FFFFFFFF), dl, SrcVT);
4914 SDValue HiShift = DAG.getConstant(32, dl, ShiftVT);
4915
4916 SDValue Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, SrcVT, Src, LoMask);
4917 SDValue Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, SrcVT, Src, HiShift);
4918 SDValue LoOr = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, SrcVT, Lo, TwoP52);
4919 SDValue HiOr = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, SrcVT, Hi, TwoP84);
4920 SDValue LoFlt = DAG.getBitcast(DstVT, LoOr);
4921 SDValue HiFlt = DAG.getBitcast(DstVT, HiOr);
4922 SDValue HiSub = DAG.getNode(ISD::FSUB, dl, DstVT, HiFlt, TwoP84PlusTwoP52);
4923 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::FADD, dl, DstVT, LoFlt, HiSub);
4924 return true;
4925 }
4926
4927 return false;
4928}
4929
4930SDValue TargetLowering::expandFMINNUM_FMAXNUM(SDNode *Node,
4931 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
4932 SDLoc dl(Node);
4933 unsigned NewOp = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::FMINNUM ?
4934 ISD::FMINNUM_IEEE : ISD::FMAXNUM_IEEE;
4935 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
4936 if (isOperationLegalOrCustom(NewOp, VT)) {
4937 SDValue Quiet0 = Node->getOperand(0);
4938 SDValue Quiet1 = Node->getOperand(1);
4939
4940 if (!Node->getFlags().hasNoNaNs()) {
4941 // Insert canonicalizes if it's possible we need to quiet to get correct
4942 // sNaN behavior.
4943 if (!DAG.isKnownNeverSNaN(Quiet0)) {
4944 Quiet0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FCANONICALIZE, dl, VT, Quiet0,
4945 Node->getFlags());
4946 }
4947 if (!DAG.isKnownNeverSNaN(Quiet1)) {
4948 Quiet1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FCANONICALIZE, dl, VT, Quiet1,
4949 Node->getFlags());
4950 }
4951 }
4952
4953 return DAG.getNode(NewOp, dl, VT, Quiet0, Quiet1, Node->getFlags());
4954 }
4955
4956 return SDValue();
4957}
4958
4959bool TargetLowering::expandCTPOP(SDNode *Node, SDValue &Result,
4960 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
4961 SDLoc dl(Node);
4962 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
4963 EVT ShVT = getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout());
4964 SDValue Op = Node->getOperand(0);
4965 unsigned Len = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
4966 assert(VT.isInteger() && "CTPOP not implemented for this type.");
4967
4968 // TODO: Add support for irregular type lengths.
4969 if (!(Len <= 128 && Len % 8 == 0))
4970 return false;
4971
4972 // Only expand vector types if we have the appropriate vector bit operations.
4973 if (VT.isVector() && (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::ADD, VT) ||
4974 !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SUB, VT) ||
4975 !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SRL, VT) ||
4976 (Len != 8 && !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::MUL, VT)) ||
4977 !isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::AND, VT)))
4978 return false;
4979
4980 // This is the "best" algorithm from
4981 // http://graphics.stanford.edu/~seander/bithacks.html#CountBitsSetParallel
4982 SDValue Mask55 =
4983 DAG.getConstant(APInt::getSplat(Len, APInt(8, 0x55)), dl, VT);
4984 SDValue Mask33 =
4985 DAG.getConstant(APInt::getSplat(Len, APInt(8, 0x33)), dl, VT);
4986 SDValue Mask0F =
4987 DAG.getConstant(APInt::getSplat(Len, APInt(8, 0x0F)), dl, VT);
4988 SDValue Mask01 =
4989 DAG.getConstant(APInt::getSplat(Len, APInt(8, 0x01)), dl, VT);
4990
4991 // v = v - ((v >> 1) & 0x55555555...)
4992 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, VT, Op,
4993 DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT,
4994 DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op,
4995 DAG.getConstant(1, dl, ShVT)),
4996 Mask55));
4997 // v = (v & 0x33333333...) + ((v >> 2) & 0x33333333...)
4998 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, VT, DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Op, Mask33),
4999 DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT,
5000 DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op,
5001 DAG.getConstant(2, dl, ShVT)),
5002 Mask33));
5003 // v = (v + (v >> 4)) & 0x0F0F0F0F...
5004 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT,
5005 DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, VT, Op,
5006 DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op,
5007 DAG.getConstant(4, dl, ShVT))),
5008 Mask0F);
5009 // v = (v * 0x01010101...) >> (Len - 8)
5010 if (Len > 8)
5011 Op =
5012 DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, VT, Op, Mask01),
5013 DAG.getConstant(Len - 8, dl, ShVT));
5014
5015 Result = Op;
5016 return true;
5017}
5018
5019bool TargetLowering::expandCTLZ(SDNode *Node, SDValue &Result,
5020 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5021 SDLoc dl(Node);
5022 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
5023 EVT ShVT = getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout());
5024 SDValue Op = Node->getOperand(0);
5025 unsigned NumBitsPerElt = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
5026
5027 // If the non-ZERO_UNDEF version is supported we can use that instead.
5028 if (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF &&
5029 isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::CTLZ, VT)) {
5030 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::CTLZ, dl, VT, Op);
5031 return true;
5032 }
5033
5034 // If the ZERO_UNDEF version is supported use that and handle the zero case.
5035 if (isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF, VT)) {
5036 EVT SetCCVT =
5037 getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), VT);
5038 SDValue CTLZ = DAG.getNode(ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF, dl, VT, Op);
5039 SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT);
5040 SDValue SrcIsZero = DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCVT, Op, Zero, ISD::SETEQ);
5041 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, dl, VT, SrcIsZero,
5042 DAG.getConstant(NumBitsPerElt, dl, VT), CTLZ);
5043 return true;
5044 }
5045
5046 // Only expand vector types if we have the appropriate vector bit operations.
5047 if (VT.isVector() && (!isPowerOf2_32(NumBitsPerElt) ||
5048 !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::CTPOP, VT) ||
5049 !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SRL, VT) ||
5050 !isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::OR, VT)))
5051 return false;
5052
5053 // for now, we do this:
5054 // x = x | (x >> 1);
5055 // x = x | (x >> 2);
5056 // ...
5057 // x = x | (x >>16);
5058 // x = x | (x >>32); // for 64-bit input
5059 // return popcount(~x);
5060 //
5061 // Ref: "Hacker's Delight" by Henry Warren
5062 for (unsigned i = 0; (1U << i) <= (NumBitsPerElt / 2); ++i) {
5063 SDValue Tmp = DAG.getConstant(1ULL << i, dl, ShVT);
5064 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Op,
5065 DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op, Tmp));
5066 }
5067 Op = DAG.getNOT(dl, Op, VT);
5068 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::CTPOP, dl, VT, Op);
5069 return true;
5070}
5071
5072bool TargetLowering::expandCTTZ(SDNode *Node, SDValue &Result,
5073 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5074 SDLoc dl(Node);
5075 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
5076 SDValue Op = Node->getOperand(0);
5077 unsigned NumBitsPerElt = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
5078
5079 // If the non-ZERO_UNDEF version is supported we can use that instead.
5080 if (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF &&
5081 isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::CTTZ, VT)) {
5082 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::CTTZ, dl, VT, Op);
5083 return true;
5084 }
5085
5086 // If the ZERO_UNDEF version is supported use that and handle the zero case.
5087 if (isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF, VT)) {
5088 EVT SetCCVT =
5089 getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), VT);
5090 SDValue CTTZ = DAG.getNode(ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF, dl, VT, Op);
5091 SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT);
5092 SDValue SrcIsZero = DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCVT, Op, Zero, ISD::SETEQ);
5093 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, dl, VT, SrcIsZero,
5094 DAG.getConstant(NumBitsPerElt, dl, VT), CTTZ);
5095 return true;
5096 }
5097
5098 // Only expand vector types if we have the appropriate vector bit operations.
5099 if (VT.isVector() && (!isPowerOf2_32(NumBitsPerElt) ||
5100 (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::CTPOP, VT) &&
5101 !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::CTLZ, VT)) ||
5102 !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SUB, VT) ||
5103 !isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::AND, VT) ||
5104 !isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::XOR, VT)))
5105 return false;
5106
5107 // for now, we use: { return popcount(~x & (x - 1)); }
5108 // unless the target has ctlz but not ctpop, in which case we use:
5109 // { return 32 - nlz(~x & (x-1)); }
5110 // Ref: "Hacker's Delight" by Henry Warren
5111 SDValue Tmp = DAG.getNode(
5112 ISD::AND, dl, VT, DAG.getNOT(dl, Op, VT),
5113 DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(1, dl, VT)));
5114
5115 // If ISD::CTLZ is legal and CTPOP isn't, then do that instead.
5116 if (isOperationLegal(ISD::CTLZ, VT) && !isOperationLegal(ISD::CTPOP, VT)) {
5117 Result =
5118 DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, VT, DAG.getConstant(NumBitsPerElt, dl, VT),
5119 DAG.getNode(ISD::CTLZ, dl, VT, Tmp));
5120 return true;
5121 }
5122
5123 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::CTPOP, dl, VT, Tmp);
5124 return true;
5125}
5126
5127bool TargetLowering::expandABS(SDNode *N, SDValue &Result,
5128 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5129 SDLoc dl(N);
5130 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
5131 EVT ShVT = getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout());
5132 SDValue Op = N->getOperand(0);
5133
5134 // Only expand vector types if we have the appropriate vector operations.
5135 if (VT.isVector() && (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SRA, VT) ||
5136 !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::ADD, VT) ||
5137 !isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::XOR, VT)))
5138 return false;
5139
5140 SDValue Shift =
5141 DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, dl, VT, Op,
5142 DAG.getConstant(VT.getScalarSizeInBits() - 1, dl, ShVT));
5143 SDValue Add = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, VT, Op, Shift);
5144 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, dl, VT, Add, Shift);
5145 return true;
5146}
5147
5148SDValue TargetLowering::scalarizeVectorLoad(LoadSDNode *LD,
5149 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5150 SDLoc SL(LD);
5151 SDValue Chain = LD->getChain();
5152 SDValue BasePTR = LD->getBasePtr();
5153 EVT SrcVT = LD->getMemoryVT();
5154 ISD::LoadExtType ExtType = LD->getExtensionType();
5155
5156 unsigned NumElem = SrcVT.getVectorNumElements();
5157
5158 EVT SrcEltVT = SrcVT.getScalarType();
5159 EVT DstEltVT = LD->getValueType(0).getScalarType();
5160
5161 unsigned Stride = SrcEltVT.getSizeInBits() / 8;
5162 assert(SrcEltVT.isByteSized());
5163
5164 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Vals;
5165 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> LoadChains;
5166
5167 for (unsigned Idx = 0; Idx < NumElem; ++Idx) {
5168 SDValue ScalarLoad =
5169 DAG.getExtLoad(ExtType, SL, DstEltVT, Chain, BasePTR,
5170 LD->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(Idx * Stride),
5171 SrcEltVT, MinAlign(LD->getAlignment(), Idx * Stride),
5172 LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags(), LD->getAAInfo());
5173
5174 BasePTR = DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(SL, BasePTR, Stride);
5175
5176 Vals.push_back(ScalarLoad.getValue(0));
5177 LoadChains.push_back(ScalarLoad.getValue(1));
5178 }
5179
5180 SDValue NewChain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, SL, MVT::Other, LoadChains);
5181 SDValue Value = DAG.getBuildVector(LD->getValueType(0), SL, Vals);
5182
5183 return DAG.getMergeValues({Value, NewChain}, SL);
5184}
5185
5186SDValue TargetLowering::scalarizeVectorStore(StoreSDNode *ST,
5187 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5188 SDLoc SL(ST);
5189
5190 SDValue Chain = ST->getChain();
5191 SDValue BasePtr = ST->getBasePtr();
5192 SDValue Value = ST->getValue();
5193 EVT StVT = ST->getMemoryVT();
5194
5195 // The type of the data we want to save
5196 EVT RegVT = Value.getValueType();
5197 EVT RegSclVT = RegVT.getScalarType();
5198
5199 // The type of data as saved in memory.
5200 EVT MemSclVT = StVT.getScalarType();
5201
5202 EVT IdxVT = getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
5203 unsigned NumElem = StVT.getVectorNumElements();
5204
5205 // A vector must always be stored in memory as-is, i.e. without any padding
5206 // between the elements, since various code depend on it, e.g. in the
5207 // handling of a bitcast of a vector type to int, which may be done with a
5208 // vector store followed by an integer load. A vector that does not have
5209 // elements that are byte-sized must therefore be stored as an integer
5210 // built out of the extracted vector elements.
5211 if (!MemSclVT.isByteSized()) {
5212 unsigned NumBits = StVT.getSizeInBits();
5213 EVT IntVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), NumBits);
5214
5215 SDValue CurrVal = DAG.getConstant(0, SL, IntVT);
5216
5217 for (unsigned Idx = 0; Idx < NumElem; ++Idx) {
5218 SDValue Elt = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, RegSclVT, Value,
5219 DAG.getConstant(Idx, SL, IdxVT));
5220 SDValue Trunc = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, SL, MemSclVT, Elt);
5221 SDValue ExtElt = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, SL, IntVT, Trunc);
5222 unsigned ShiftIntoIdx =
5223 (DAG.getDataLayout().isBigEndian() ? (NumElem - 1) - Idx : Idx);
5224 SDValue ShiftAmount =
5225 DAG.getConstant(ShiftIntoIdx * MemSclVT.getSizeInBits(), SL, IntVT);
5226 SDValue ShiftedElt =
5227 DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, SL, IntVT, ExtElt, ShiftAmount);
5228 CurrVal = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, SL, IntVT, CurrVal, ShiftedElt);
5229 }
5230
5231 return DAG.getStore(Chain, SL, CurrVal, BasePtr, ST->getPointerInfo(),
5232 ST->getAlignment(), ST->getMemOperand()->getFlags(),
5233 ST->getAAInfo());
5234 }
5235
5236 // Store Stride in bytes
5237 unsigned Stride = MemSclVT.getSizeInBits() / 8;
5238 assert(Stride && "Zero stride!");
5239 // Extract each of the elements from the original vector and save them into
5240 // memory individually.
5241 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Stores;
5242 for (unsigned Idx = 0; Idx < NumElem; ++Idx) {
5243 SDValue Elt = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, RegSclVT, Value,
5244 DAG.getConstant(Idx, SL, IdxVT));
5245
5246 SDValue Ptr = DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(SL, BasePtr, Idx * Stride);
5247
5248 // This scalar TruncStore may be illegal, but we legalize it later.
5249 SDValue Store = DAG.getTruncStore(
5250 Chain, SL, Elt, Ptr, ST->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(Idx * Stride),
5251 MemSclVT, MinAlign(ST->getAlignment(), Idx * Stride),
5252 ST->getMemOperand()->getFlags(), ST->getAAInfo());
5253
5254 Stores.push_back(Store);
5255 }
5256
5257 return DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, SL, MVT::Other, Stores);
5258}
5259
5260SDValue TargetLowering::unalignedLoadStoreCSetbounds(const char *loadOrStore,
5261 SDValue Ptr,
5262 const SDLoc &DL,
5263 unsigned CapSize,
5264 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5265 // Only set bounds if the pointer was actually a CHERI capability (i.e. skip
5266 // setting bounds in hybrid mode)
5267 if (!Ptr->getValueType(0).isFatPointer())
5268 return Ptr;
5269 if (cheri::ShouldCollectCSetBoundsStats) {
5270 cheri::CSetBoundsStats->add(
5271 CapSize, CapSize, "expanding unaligned capability load/store",
5272 cheri::SetBoundsPointerSource::Stack,
5273 StringRef("expanding unaligned capability ") + loadOrStore,
5274 cheri::inferSourceLocation(DL.getDebugLoc(),
5275 DAG.getMachineFunction().getName()));
5276 }
5277 return DAG.getCSetBounds(Ptr, CapSize, /*CSetBoundsStatsAlreadyLogged=*/true);
5278}
5279
5280std::pair<SDValue, SDValue>
5281TargetLowering::expandUnalignedLoad(LoadSDNode *LD, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5282 assert(LD->getAddressingMode() == ISD::UNINDEXED &&
5283 "unaligned indexed loads not implemented!");
5284 SDValue Chain = LD->getChain();
5285 SDValue Ptr = LD->getBasePtr();
5286 EVT VT = LD->getValueType(0);
5287 EVT LoadedVT = LD->getMemoryVT();
5288 SDLoc dl(LD);
5289 auto &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
5290
5291 if (VT.isFatPointer() && !supportsUnalignedCapabilityMemOps()) {
5292 auto CapAlign = VT.getStoreSize();
5293 DiagnosticInfoCheriInefficient Warning(
5294 MF.getFunction(), dl.getDebugLoc(),
5295 "found underaligned load of capability type (aligned to " +
5296 Twine(LD->getAlignment()) + " bytes instead of " + Twine(CapAlign) +
5297 "). Will use memcpy() instead of capability load to preserve tags "
5298 "if it is aligned correctly at runtime");
5299 DAG.getContext()->diagnose(Warning);
5300
5301 SDValue TmpPtr = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(VT);
5302 int SPFI = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(TmpPtr.getNode())->getIndex();
5303 auto TmpPtrInfo =
5304 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(DAG.getMachineFunction(), SPFI);
5305 // Also bound the arguments for the memcpy call
5306 SDValue BoundedTmpPtr = unalignedLoadStoreCSetbounds("load stack destination", TmpPtr, dl,
5307 CapAlign, DAG);
5308 SDValue BoundedPtr = unalignedLoadStoreCSetbounds("load memcpy source", Ptr, dl, CapAlign,
5309 DAG);
5310 SDValue Ch = DAG.getMemcpy(Chain, dl, BoundedTmpPtr, BoundedPtr,
5311 DAG.getConstant(CapAlign, dl, MVT::i64),
5312 LD->getAlignment(),
5313 /*isVolatile=*/false,
5314 /*AlwaysInline=*/false,
5315 /*isTailCall=*/false,
5316 /*MustPreserveCheriCapabilities=*/true,
5317 TmpPtrInfo, LD->getPointerInfo(),
5318 "!!<CHERI-NODIAG>!!");
5319 // Load the updated value (does not need to be bounded!)
5320 auto Result = DAG.getLoad(VT, dl, Ch, TmpPtr, TmpPtrInfo);
5321 return std::make_pair(Result, Result.getValue(1));
5322 }
5323
5324 if (VT.isFloatingPoint() || VT.isVector()) {
5325 EVT intVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), LoadedVT.getSizeInBits());
5326 if (isTypeLegal(intVT) && isTypeLegal(LoadedVT)) {
5327 if (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::LOAD, intVT) &&
5328 LoadedVT.isVector()) {
5329 // Scalarize the load and let the individual components be handled.
5330 SDValue Scalarized = scalarizeVectorLoad(LD, DAG);
5331 if (Scalarized->getOpcode() == ISD::MERGE_VALUES)
5332 return std::make_pair(Scalarized.getOperand(0), Scalarized.getOperand(1));
5333 return std::make_pair(Scalarized.getValue(0), Scalarized.getValue(1));
5334 }
5335
5336 // Expand to a (misaligned) integer load of the same size,
5337 // then bitconvert to floating point or vector.
5338 SDValue newLoad = DAG.getLoad(intVT, dl, Chain, Ptr,
5339 LD->getMemOperand());
5340 SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, LoadedVT, newLoad);
5341 if (LoadedVT != VT)
5342 Result = DAG.getNode(VT.isFloatingPoint() ? ISD::FP_EXTEND :
5343 ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, VT, Result);
5344
5345 return std::make_pair(Result, newLoad.getValue(1));
5346 }
5347
5348 // Copy the value to a (aligned) stack slot using (unaligned) integer
5349 // loads and stores, then do a (aligned) load from the stack slot.
5350 MVT RegVT = getRegisterType(*DAG.getContext(), intVT);
5351 unsigned LoadedBytes = LoadedVT.getStoreSize();
5352 unsigned RegBytes = RegVT.getSizeInBits() / 8;
5353 unsigned NumRegs = (LoadedBytes + RegBytes - 1) / RegBytes;
5354
5355 // Make sure the stack slot is also aligned for the register type.
5356 SDValue StackBase = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(LoadedVT, RegVT);
5357 auto FrameIndex = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(StackBase.getNode())->getIndex();
5358 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Stores;
5359 SDValue StackPtr = StackBase;
5360 unsigned Offset = 0;
5361
5362 EVT PtrVT = Ptr.getValueType();
5363 EVT StackPtrVT = StackPtr.getValueType();
5364
5365 SDValue PtrIncrement = DAG.getConstant(RegBytes, dl, PtrVT);
5366 SDValue StackPtrIncrement = DAG.getConstant(RegBytes, dl, StackPtrVT);
5367
5368 // Do all but one copies using the full register width.
5369 for (unsigned i = 1; i < NumRegs; i++) {
5370 // Load one integer register's worth from the original location.
5371 SDValue Load = DAG.getLoad(
5372 RegVT, dl, Chain, Ptr, LD->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(Offset),
5373 MinAlign(LD->getAlignment(), Offset), LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags(),
5374 LD->getAAInfo());
5375 // Follow the load with a store to the stack slot. Remember the store.
5376 Stores.push_back(DAG.getStore(
5377 Load.getValue(1), dl, Load, StackPtr,
5378 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FrameIndex, Offset)));
5379 // Increment the pointers.
5380 Offset += RegBytes;
5381
5382 Ptr = DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(dl, Ptr, PtrIncrement);
5383 StackPtr = DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(dl, StackPtr, StackPtrIncrement);
5384 }
5385
5386 // The last copy may be partial. Do an extending load.
5387 EVT MemVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(),
5388 8 * (LoadedBytes - Offset));
5389 SDValue Load =
5390 DAG.getExtLoad(ISD::EXTLOAD, dl, RegVT, Chain, Ptr,
5391 LD->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(Offset), MemVT,
5392 MinAlign(LD->getAlignment(), Offset),
5393 LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags(), LD->getAAInfo());
5394 // Follow the load with a store to the stack slot. Remember the store.
5395 // On big-endian machines this requires a truncating store to ensure
5396 // that the bits end up in the right place.
5397 Stores.push_back(DAG.getTruncStore(
5398 Load.getValue(1), dl, Load, StackPtr,
5399 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FrameIndex, Offset), MemVT));
5400
5401 // The order of the stores doesn't matter - say it with a TokenFactor.
5402 SDValue TF = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Stores);
5403
5404 // Finally, perform the original load only redirected to the stack slot.
5405 Load = DAG.getExtLoad(LD->getExtensionType(), dl, VT, TF, StackBase,
5406 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FrameIndex, 0),
5407 LoadedVT);
5408
5409 // Callers expect a MERGE_VALUES node.
5410 return std::make_pair(Load, TF);
5411 }
5412
5413 assert(LoadedVT.isInteger() && !LoadedVT.isVector() &&
5414 "Unaligned load of unsupported type.");
5415
5416 // Compute the new VT that is half the size of the old one. This is an
5417 // integer MVT.
5418 unsigned NumBits = LoadedVT.getSizeInBits();
5419 EVT NewLoadedVT;
5420 NewLoadedVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), NumBits/2);
5421 NumBits >>= 1;
5422
5423 unsigned Alignment = LD->getAlignment();
5424 unsigned IncrementSize = NumBits / 8;
5425 ISD::LoadExtType HiExtType = LD->getExtensionType();
5426
5427 // If the original load is NON_EXTLOAD, the hi part load must be ZEXTLOAD.
5428 if (HiExtType == ISD::NON_EXTLOAD)
5429 HiExtType = ISD::ZEXTLOAD;
5430
5431 // Load the value in two parts
5432 SDValue Lo, Hi;
5433 if (DAG.getDataLayout().isLittleEndian()) {
5434 Lo = DAG.getExtLoad(ISD::ZEXTLOAD, dl, VT, Chain, Ptr, LD->getPointerInfo(),
5435 NewLoadedVT, Alignment, LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags(),
5436 LD->getAAInfo());
5437
5438 Ptr = DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(dl, Ptr, IncrementSize);
5439 Hi = DAG.getExtLoad(HiExtType, dl, VT, Chain, Ptr,
5440 LD->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(IncrementSize),
5441 NewLoadedVT, MinAlign(Alignment, IncrementSize),
5442 LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags(), LD->getAAInfo());
5443 } else {
5444 Hi = DAG.getExtLoad(HiExtType, dl, VT, Chain, Ptr, LD->getPointerInfo(),
5445 NewLoadedVT, Alignment, LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags(),
5446 LD->getAAInfo());
5447
5448 Ptr = DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(dl, Ptr, IncrementSize);
5449 Lo = DAG.getExtLoad(ISD::ZEXTLOAD, dl, VT, Chain, Ptr,
5450 LD->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(IncrementSize),
5451 NewLoadedVT, MinAlign(Alignment, IncrementSize),
5452 LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags(), LD->getAAInfo());
5453 }
5454
5455 // aggregate the two parts
5456 SDValue ShiftAmount =
5457 DAG.getConstant(NumBits, dl, getShiftAmountTy(Hi.getValueType(),
5458 DAG.getDataLayout()));
5459 SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Hi, ShiftAmount);
5460 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Result, Lo);
5461
5462 SDValue TF = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Lo.getValue(1),
5463 Hi.getValue(1));
5464
5465 return std::make_pair(Result, TF);
5466}
5467
5468SDValue TargetLowering::expandUnalignedStore(StoreSDNode *ST,
5469 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5470 assert(ST->getAddressingMode() == ISD::UNINDEXED &&
5471 "unaligned indexed stores not implemented!");
5472 SDValue Chain = ST->getChain();
5473 SDValue Ptr = ST->getBasePtr();
5474 SDValue Val = ST->getValue();
5475 EVT VT = Val.getValueType();
5476 int Alignment = ST->getAlignment();
5477 auto &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
5478 EVT StoreMemVT = ST->getMemoryVT();
5479
5480 if (VT.isFatPointer() && !supportsUnalignedCapabilityMemOps()) {
5481 auto CapAlign = VT.getStoreSize();
5482 SDLoc dl(ST);
5483 DiagnosticInfoCheriInefficient Warning(
5484 MF.getFunction(), dl.getDebugLoc(),
5485 "found underaligned store of capability type (aligned to " +
5486 Twine(ST->getAlignment()) + " bytes instead of " + Twine(CapAlign) +
5487 "). Will use memcpy() instead of capability load to preserve tags "
5488 "if it is aligned correctly at runtime");
5489 DAG.getContext()->diagnose(Warning);
5490
5491 SDValue TmpPtr = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(VT);
5492 int SPFI = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(TmpPtr.getNode())->getIndex();
5493 auto TmpPtrInfo =
5494 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(DAG.getMachineFunction(), SPFI);
5495 SDValue Ch = DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, Val, TmpPtr, TmpPtrInfo);
5496 // Add bounds on the arguments to memcpy:
5497 TmpPtr = unalignedLoadStoreCSetbounds("store stack source", TmpPtr, dl,
5498 CapAlign, DAG);
5499 Ptr = unalignedLoadStoreCSetbounds("store memcpy destination", Ptr, dl,
5500 CapAlign, DAG);
5501 auto Result = DAG.getMemcpy(Ch, dl, Ptr, TmpPtr,
5502 DAG.getConstant(CapAlign, dl, MVT::i64),
5503 ST->getAlignment(),
5504 /*isVolatile=*/false,
5505 /*AlwaysInline=*/false,
5506 /*isTailCall=*/false,
5507 /*MustPreserveCheriCapabilities=*/true,
5508 ST->getPointerInfo(), TmpPtrInfo,
5509 "!!<CHERI-NODIAG>!!");
5510 return Result;
5511 }
5512
5513 SDLoc dl(ST);
5514 if (StoreMemVT.isFloatingPoint() || StoreMemVT.isVector()) {
5515 EVT intVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), VT.getSizeInBits());
5516 if (isTypeLegal(intVT)) {
5517 if (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::STORE, intVT) &&
5518 StoreMemVT.isVector()) {
5519 // Scalarize the store and let the individual components be handled.
5520 SDValue Result = scalarizeVectorStore(ST, DAG);
5521 return Result;
5522 }
5523 // Expand to a bitconvert of the value to the integer type of the
5524 // same size, then a (misaligned) int store.
5525 // FIXME: Does not handle truncating floating point stores!
5526 SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, intVT, Val);
5527 Result = DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, Result, Ptr, ST->getPointerInfo(),
5528 Alignment, ST->getMemOperand()->getFlags());
5529 return Result;
5530 }
5531 // Do a (aligned) store to a stack slot, then copy from the stack slot
5532 // to the final destination using (unaligned) integer loads and stores.
5533 MVT RegVT = getRegisterType(
5534 *DAG.getContext(),
5535 EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), StoreMemVT.getSizeInBits()));
5536 EVT PtrVT = Ptr.getValueType();
5537 unsigned StoredBytes = StoreMemVT.getStoreSize();
5538 unsigned RegBytes = RegVT.getSizeInBits() / 8;
5539 unsigned NumRegs = (StoredBytes + RegBytes - 1) / RegBytes;
5540
5541 // Make sure the stack slot is also aligned for the register type.
5542 SDValue StackPtr = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(StoreMemVT, RegVT);
5543 auto FrameIndex = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(StackPtr.getNode())->getIndex();
5544
5545 // Perform the original store, only redirected to the stack slot.
5546 SDValue Store = DAG.getTruncStore(
5547 Chain, dl, Val, StackPtr,
5548 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FrameIndex, 0), StoreMemVT);
5549
5550 EVT StackPtrVT = StackPtr.getValueType();
5551
5552 SDValue PtrIncrement = DAG.getConstant(RegBytes, dl, PtrVT);
5553 SDValue StackPtrIncrement = DAG.getConstant(RegBytes, dl, StackPtrVT);
5554 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Stores;
5555 unsigned Offset = 0;
5556
5557 // Do all but one copies using the full register width.
5558 for (unsigned i = 1; i < NumRegs; i++) {
5559 // Load one integer register's worth from the stack slot.
5560 SDValue Load = DAG.getLoad(
5561 RegVT, dl, Store, StackPtr,
5562 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FrameIndex, Offset));
5563 // Store it to the final location. Remember the store.
5564 Stores.push_back(DAG.getStore(Load.getValue(1), dl, Load, Ptr,
5565 ST->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(Offset),
5566 MinAlign(ST->getAlignment(), Offset),
5567 ST->getMemOperand()->getFlags()));
5568 // Increment the pointers.
5569 Offset += RegBytes;
5570 StackPtr = DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(dl, StackPtr, StackPtrIncrement);
5571 Ptr = DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(dl, Ptr, PtrIncrement);
5572 }
5573
5574 // The last store may be partial. Do a truncating store. On big-endian
5575 // machines this requires an extending load from the stack slot to ensure
5576 // that the bits are in the right place.
5577 EVT LoadMemVT =
5578 EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), 8 * (StoredBytes - Offset));
5579
5580 // Load from the stack slot.
5581 SDValue Load = DAG.getExtLoad(
5582 ISD::EXTLOAD, dl, RegVT, Store, StackPtr,
5583 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FrameIndex, Offset), LoadMemVT);
5584
5585 Stores.push_back(
5586 DAG.getTruncStore(Load.getValue(1), dl, Load, Ptr,
5587 ST->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(Offset), LoadMemVT,
5588 MinAlign(ST->getAlignment(), Offset),
5589 ST->getMemOperand()->getFlags(), ST->getAAInfo()));
5590 // The order of the stores doesn't matter - say it with a TokenFactor.
5591 SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Stores);
5592 return Result;
5593 }
5594
5595 assert(StoreMemVT.isInteger() && !StoreMemVT.isVector() &&
5596 "Unaligned store of unknown type.");
5597 // Get the half-size VT
5598 EVT NewStoredVT = StoreMemVT.getHalfSizedIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext());
5599 int NumBits = NewStoredVT.getSizeInBits();
5600 int IncrementSize = NumBits / 8;
5601
5602 // Divide the stored value in two parts.
5603 SDValue ShiftAmount = DAG.getConstant(
5604 NumBits, dl, getShiftAmountTy(Val.getValueType(), DAG.getDataLayout()));
5605 SDValue Lo = Val;
5606 SDValue Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Val, ShiftAmount);
5607
5608 // Store the two parts
5609 SDValue Store1, Store2;
5610 Store1 = DAG.getTruncStore(Chain, dl,
5611 DAG.getDataLayout().isLittleEndian() ? Lo : Hi,
5612 Ptr, ST->getPointerInfo(), NewStoredVT, Alignment,
5613 ST->getMemOperand()->getFlags());
5614
5615 Ptr = DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(dl, Ptr, IncrementSize);
5616 Alignment = MinAlign(Alignment, IncrementSize);
5617 Store2 = DAG.getTruncStore(
5618 Chain, dl, DAG.getDataLayout().isLittleEndian() ? Hi : Lo, Ptr,
5619 ST->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(IncrementSize), NewStoredVT, Alignment,
5620 ST->getMemOperand()->getFlags(), ST->getAAInfo());
5621
5622 SDValue Result =
5623 DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Store1, Store2);
5624 return Result;
5625}
5626
5627SDValue
5628TargetLowering::IncrementMemoryAddress(SDValue Addr, SDValue Mask,
5629 const SDLoc &DL, EVT DataVT,
5630 SelectionDAG &DAG,
5631 bool IsCompressedMemory) const {
5632 SDValue Increment;
5633 EVT AddrVT = Addr.getValueType();
5634 EVT MaskVT = Mask.getValueType();
5635 assert(DataVT.getVectorNumElements() == MaskVT.getVectorNumElements() &&
5636 "Incompatible types of Data and Mask");
5637 if (IsCompressedMemory) {
5638 // Incrementing the pointer according to number of '1's in the mask.
5639 EVT MaskIntVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), MaskVT.getSizeInBits());
5640 SDValue MaskInIntReg = DAG.getBitcast(MaskIntVT, Mask);
5641 if (MaskIntVT.getSizeInBits() < 32) {
5642 MaskInIntReg = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i32, MaskInIntReg);
5643 MaskIntVT = MVT::i32;
5644 }
5645
5646 // Count '1's with POPCNT.
5647 Increment = DAG.getNode(ISD::CTPOP, DL, MaskIntVT, MaskInIntReg);
5648 Increment = DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(Increment, DL, AddrVT);
5649 // Scale is an element size in bytes.
5650 SDValue Scale = DAG.getConstant(DataVT.getScalarSizeInBits() / 8, DL,
5651 AddrVT);
5652 Increment = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, DL, AddrVT, Increment, Scale);
5653 } else
5654 Increment = DAG.getConstant(DataVT.getStoreSize(), DL, AddrVT);
5655
5656 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, AddrVT, Addr, Increment);
5657}
5658
5659static SDValue clampDynamicVectorIndex(SelectionDAG &DAG,
5660 SDValue Idx,
5661 EVT VecVT,
5662 const SDLoc &dl) {
5663 if (isa<ConstantSDNode>(Idx))
5664 return Idx;
5665
5666 EVT IdxVT = Idx.getValueType();
5667 unsigned NElts = VecVT.getVectorNumElements();
5668 if (isPowerOf2_32(NElts)) {
5669 APInt Imm = APInt::getLowBitsSet(IdxVT.getSizeInBits(),
5670 Log2_32(NElts));
5671 return DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, IdxVT, Idx,
5672 DAG.getConstant(Imm, dl, IdxVT));
5673 }
5674
5675 return DAG.getNode(ISD::UMIN, dl, IdxVT, Idx,
5676 DAG.getConstant(NElts - 1, dl, IdxVT));
5677}
5678
5679SDValue TargetLowering::getVectorElementPointer(SelectionDAG &DAG,
5680 SDValue VecPtr, EVT VecVT,
5681 SDValue Index) const {
5682 SDLoc dl(Index);
5683 // Make sure the index type is big enough to compute in.
5684 Index = DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(Index, dl, VecPtr.getValueType());
5685
5686 EVT EltVT = VecVT.getVectorElementType();
5687
5688 // Calculate the element offset and add it to the pointer.
5689 unsigned EltSize = EltVT.getSizeInBits() / 8; // FIXME: should be ABI size.
5690 assert(EltSize * 8 == EltVT.getSizeInBits() &&
5691 "Converting bits to bytes lost precision");
5692
5693 Index = clampDynamicVectorIndex(DAG, Index, VecVT, dl);
5694
5695 EVT IdxVT = Index.getValueType();
5696
5697 Index = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, IdxVT, Index,
5698 DAG.getConstant(EltSize, dl, IdxVT));
5699 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, IdxVT, VecPtr, Index);
5700}
5701
5702//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5703// Implementation of Emulated TLS Model
5704//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5705
5706SDValue TargetLowering::LowerToTLSEmulatedModel(const GlobalAddressSDNode *GA,
5707 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5708 // Access to address of TLS varialbe xyz is lowered to a function call:
5709 // __emutls_get_address( address of global variable named "__emutls_v.xyz" )
5710 EVT DataPtrVT = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout(),
5711 DAG.getDataLayout().getGlobalsAddressSpace());
5712 PointerType *VoidPtrType = Type::getInt8PtrTy(*DAG.getContext());
5713 SDLoc dl(GA);
5714
5715 ArgListTy Args;
5716 ArgListEntry Entry;
5717 std::string NameString = ("__emutls_v." + GA->getGlobal()->getName()).str();
5718 Module *VariableModule = const_cast<Module*>(GA->getGlobal()->getParent());
5719 StringRef EmuTlsVarName(NameString);
5720 GlobalVariable *EmuTlsVar = VariableModule->getNamedGlobal(EmuTlsVarName);
5721 assert(EmuTlsVar && "Cannot find EmuTlsVar ");
5722 Entry.Node = DAG.getGlobalAddress(EmuTlsVar, dl, DataPtrVT);
5723 Entry.Ty = VoidPtrType;
5724 Args.push_back(Entry);
5725
5726 SDValue EmuTlsGetAddr = DAG.getExternalFunctionSymbol("__emutls_get_address");
5727
5728 TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo CLI(DAG);
5729 CLI.setDebugLoc(dl).setChain(DAG.getEntryNode());
5730 CLI.setLibCallee(CallingConv::C, VoidPtrType, EmuTlsGetAddr, std::move(Args));
5731 std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> CallResult = LowerCallTo(CLI);
5732
5733 // TLSADDR will be codegen'ed as call. Inform MFI that function has calls.
5734 // At last for X86 targets, maybe good for other targets too?
5735 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = DAG.getMachineFunction().getFrameInfo();
5736 MFI.setAdjustsStack(true); // Is this only for X86 target?
5737 MFI.setHasCalls(true);
5738
5739 assert((GA->getOffset() == 0) &&
5740 "Emulated TLS must have zero offset in GlobalAddressSDNode");
5741 return CallResult.first;
5742}
5743
5744SDValue TargetLowering::lowerCmpEqZeroToCtlzSrl(SDValue Op,
5745 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5746 assert((Op->getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC) && "Input has to be a SETCC node.");
5747 if (!isCtlzFast())
5748 return SDValue();
5749 ISD::CondCode CC = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(Op.getOperand(2))->get();
5750 SDLoc dl(Op);
5751 if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))) {
5752 if (C->isNullValue() && CC == ISD::SETEQ) {
5753 EVT VT = Op.getOperand(0).getValueType();
5754 SDValue Zext = Op.getOperand(0);
5755 if (VT.bitsLT(MVT::i32)) {
5756 VT = MVT::i32;
5757 Zext = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, dl, VT, Op.getOperand(0));
5758 }
5759 unsigned Log2b = Log2_32(VT.getSizeInBits());
5760 SDValue Clz = DAG.getNode(ISD::CTLZ, dl, VT, Zext);
5761 SDValue Scc = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Clz,
5762 DAG.getConstant(Log2b, dl, MVT::i32));
5763 return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, MVT::i32, Scc);
5764 }
5765 }
5766 return SDValue();
5767}
5768
5769SDValue TargetLowering::expandAddSubSat(SDNode *Node, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5770 unsigned Opcode = Node->getOpcode();
5771 SDValue LHS = Node->getOperand(0);
5772 SDValue RHS = Node->getOperand(1);
5773 EVT VT = LHS.getValueType();
5774 SDLoc dl(Node);
5775
5776 assert(VT == RHS.getValueType() && "Expected operands to be the same type");
5777 assert(VT.isInteger() && "Expected operands to be integers");
5778
5779 // usub.sat(a, b) -> umax(a, b) - b
5780 if (Opcode == ISD::USUBSAT && isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::UMAX, VT)) {
5781 SDValue Max = DAG.getNode(ISD::UMAX, dl, VT, LHS, RHS);
5782 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, VT, Max, RHS);
5783 }
5784
5785 if (Opcode == ISD::UADDSAT && isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::UMIN, VT)) {
5786 SDValue InvRHS = DAG.getNOT(dl, RHS, VT);
5787 SDValue Min = DAG.getNode(ISD::UMIN, dl, VT, LHS, InvRHS);
5788 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, VT, Min, RHS);
5789 }
5790
5791 unsigned OverflowOp;
5792 switch (Opcode) {
5793 case ISD::SADDSAT:
5794 OverflowOp = ISD::SADDO;
5795 break;
5796 case ISD::UADDSAT:
5797 OverflowOp = ISD::UADDO;
5798 break;
5799 case ISD::SSUBSAT:
5800 OverflowOp = ISD::SSUBO;
5801 break;
5802 case ISD::USUBSAT:
5803 OverflowOp = ISD::USUBO;
5804 break;
5805 default:
5806 llvm_unreachable("Expected method to receive signed or unsigned saturation "
5807 "addition or subtraction node.");
5808 }
5809
5810 unsigned BitWidth = LHS.getScalarValueSizeInBits();
5811 EVT BoolVT = getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), VT);
5812 SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(OverflowOp, dl, DAG.getVTList(VT, BoolVT),
5813 LHS, RHS);
5814 SDValue SumDiff = Result.getValue(0);
5815 SDValue Overflow = Result.getValue(1);
5816 SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT);
5817 SDValue AllOnes = DAG.getAllOnesConstant(dl, VT);
5818
5819 if (Opcode == ISD::UADDSAT) {
5820 if (getBooleanContents(VT) == ZeroOrNegativeOneBooleanContent) {
5821 // (LHS + RHS) | OverflowMask
5822 SDValue OverflowMask = DAG.getSExtOrTrunc(Overflow, dl, VT);
5823 return DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, SumDiff, OverflowMask);
5824 }
5825 // Overflow ? 0xffff.... : (LHS + RHS)
5826 return DAG.getSelect(dl, VT, Overflow, AllOnes, SumDiff);
5827 } else if (Opcode == ISD::USUBSAT) {
5828 if (getBooleanContents(VT) == ZeroOrNegativeOneBooleanContent) {
5829 // (LHS - RHS) & ~OverflowMask
5830 SDValue OverflowMask = DAG.getSExtOrTrunc(Overflow, dl, VT);
5831 SDValue Not = DAG.getNOT(dl, OverflowMask, VT);
5832 return DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, SumDiff, Not);
5833 }
5834 // Overflow ? 0 : (LHS - RHS)
5835 return DAG.getSelect(dl, VT, Overflow, Zero, SumDiff);
5836 } else {
5837 // SatMax -> Overflow && SumDiff < 0
5838 // SatMin -> Overflow && SumDiff >= 0
5839 APInt MinVal = APInt::getSignedMinValue(BitWidth);
5840 APInt MaxVal = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(BitWidth);
5841 SDValue SatMin = DAG.getConstant(MinVal, dl, VT);
5842 SDValue SatMax = DAG.getConstant(MaxVal, dl, VT);
5843 SDValue SumNeg = DAG.getSetCC(dl, BoolVT, SumDiff, Zero, ISD::SETLT);
5844 Result = DAG.getSelect(dl, VT, SumNeg, SatMax, SatMin);
5845 return DAG.getSelect(dl, VT, Overflow, Result, SumDiff);
5846 }
5847}
5848
5849SDValue
5850TargetLowering::expandFixedPointMul(SDNode *Node, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5851 assert((Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SMULFIX ||
5852 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::UMULFIX ||
5853 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SMULFIXSAT) &&
5854 "Expected a fixed point multiplication opcode");
5855
5856 SDLoc dl(Node);
5857 SDValue LHS = Node->getOperand(0);
5858 SDValue RHS = Node->getOperand(1);
5859 EVT VT = LHS.getValueType();
5860 unsigned Scale = Node->getConstantOperandVal(2);
5861 bool Saturating = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SMULFIXSAT;
5862 EVT BoolVT = getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), VT);
5863 unsigned VTSize = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
5864
5865 if (!Scale) {
5866 // [us]mul.fix(a, b, 0) -> mul(a, b)
5867 if (!Saturating && isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::MUL, VT)) {
5868 return DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, VT, LHS, RHS);
5869 } else if (Saturating && isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SMULO, VT)) {
5870 SDValue Result =
5871 DAG.getNode(ISD::SMULO, dl, DAG.getVTList(VT, BoolVT), LHS, RHS);
5872 SDValue Product = Result.getValue(0);
5873 SDValue Overflow = Result.getValue(1);
5874 SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT);
5875
5876 APInt MinVal = APInt::getSignedMinValue(VTSize);
5877 APInt MaxVal = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(VTSize);
5878 SDValue SatMin = DAG.getConstant(MinVal, dl, VT);
5879 SDValue SatMax = DAG.getConstant(MaxVal, dl, VT);
5880 SDValue ProdNeg = DAG.getSetCC(dl, BoolVT, Product, Zero, ISD::SETLT);
5881 Result = DAG.getSelect(dl, VT, ProdNeg, SatMax, SatMin);
5882 return DAG.getSelect(dl, VT, Overflow, Result, Product);
5883 }
5884 }
5885
5886 bool Signed =
5887 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SMULFIX || Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SMULFIXSAT;
5888 assert(((Signed && Scale < VTSize) || (!Signed && Scale <= VTSize)) &&
5889 "Expected scale to be less than the number of bits if signed or at "
5890 "most the number of bits if unsigned.");
5891 assert(LHS.getValueType() == RHS.getValueType() &&
5892 "Expected both operands to be the same type");
5893
5894 // Get the upper and lower bits of the result.
5895 SDValue Lo, Hi;
5896 unsigned LoHiOp = Signed ? ISD::SMUL_LOHI : ISD::UMUL_LOHI;
5897 unsigned HiOp = Signed ? ISD::MULHS : ISD::MULHU;
5898 if (isOperationLegalOrCustom(LoHiOp, VT)) {
5899 SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(LoHiOp, dl, DAG.getVTList(VT, VT), LHS, RHS);
5900 Lo = Result.getValue(0);
5901 Hi = Result.getValue(1);
5902 } else if (isOperationLegalOrCustom(HiOp, VT)) {
5903 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, VT, LHS, RHS);
5904 Hi = DAG.getNode(HiOp, dl, VT, LHS, RHS);
5905 } else if (VT.isVector()) {
5906 return SDValue();
5907 } else {
5908 report_fatal_error("Unable to expand fixed point multiplication.");
5909 }
5910
5911 if (Scale == VTSize)
5912 // Result is just the top half since we'd be shifting by the width of the
5913 // operand.
5914 return Hi;
5915
5916 // The result will need to be shifted right by the scale since both operands
5917 // are scaled. The result is given to us in 2 halves, so we only want part of
5918 // both in the result.
5919 EVT ShiftTy = getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout());
5920 SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::FSHR, dl, VT, Hi, Lo,
5921 DAG.getConstant(Scale, dl, ShiftTy));
5922 if (!Saturating)
5923 return Result;
5924
5925 unsigned OverflowBits = VTSize - Scale + 1; // +1 for the sign
5926 SDValue HiMask =
5927 DAG.getConstant(APInt::getHighBitsSet(VTSize, OverflowBits), dl, VT);
5928 SDValue LoMask = DAG.getConstant(
5929 APInt::getLowBitsSet(VTSize, VTSize - OverflowBits), dl, VT);
5930 APInt MaxVal = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(VTSize);
5931 APInt MinVal = APInt::getSignedMinValue(VTSize);
5932
5933 Result = DAG.getSelectCC(dl, Hi, LoMask,
5934 DAG.getConstant(MaxVal, dl, VT), Result,
5935 ISD::SETGT);
5936 return DAG.getSelectCC(dl, Hi, HiMask,
5937 DAG.getConstant(MinVal, dl, VT), Result,
5938 ISD::SETLT);
5939}
5940
5941void TargetLowering::expandUADDSUBO(
5942 SDNode *Node, SDValue &Result, SDValue &Overflow, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5943 SDLoc dl(Node);
5944 SDValue LHS = Node->getOperand(0);
5945 SDValue RHS = Node->getOperand(1);
5946 bool IsAdd = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::UADDO;
5947
5948 // If ADD/SUBCARRY is legal, use that instead.
5949 unsigned OpcCarry = IsAdd ? ISD::ADDCARRY : ISD::SUBCARRY;
5950 if (isOperationLegalOrCustom(OpcCarry, Node->getValueType(0))) {
5951 SDValue CarryIn = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, Node->getValueType(1));
5952 SDValue NodeCarry = DAG.getNode(OpcCarry, dl, Node->getVTList(),
5953 { LHS, RHS, CarryIn });
5954 Result = SDValue(NodeCarry.getNode(), 0);
5955 Overflow = SDValue(NodeCarry.getNode(), 1);
5956 return;
5957 }
5958
5959 Result = DAG.getNode(IsAdd ? ISD::ADD : ISD::SUB, dl,
5960 LHS.getValueType(), LHS, RHS);
5961
5962 EVT ResultType = Node->getValueType(1);
5963 EVT SetCCType = getSetCCResultType(
5964 DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), Node->getValueType(0));
5965 ISD::CondCode CC = IsAdd ? ISD::SETULT : ISD::SETUGT;
5966 SDValue SetCC = DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCType, Result, LHS, CC);
5967 Overflow = DAG.getBoolExtOrTrunc(SetCC, dl, ResultType, ResultType);
5968}
5969
5970void TargetLowering::expandSADDSUBO(
5971 SDNode *Node, SDValue &Result, SDValue &Overflow, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5972 SDLoc dl(Node);
5973 SDValue LHS = Node->getOperand(0);
5974 SDValue RHS = Node->getOperand(1);
5975 bool IsAdd = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SADDO;
5976
5977 Result = DAG.getNode(IsAdd ? ISD::ADD : ISD::SUB, dl,
5978 LHS.getValueType(), LHS, RHS);
5979
5980 EVT ResultType = Node->getValueType(1);
5981 EVT OType = getSetCCResultType(
5982 DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), Node->getValueType(0));
5983
5984 // If SADDSAT/SSUBSAT is legal, compare results to detect overflow.
5985 unsigned OpcSat = IsAdd ? ISD::SADDSAT : ISD::SSUBSAT;
5986 if (isOperationLegalOrCustom(OpcSat, LHS.getValueType())) {
5987 SDValue Sat = DAG.getNode(OpcSat, dl, LHS.getValueType(), LHS, RHS);
5988 SDValue SetCC = DAG.getSetCC(dl, OType, Result, Sat, ISD::SETNE);
5989 Overflow = DAG.getBoolExtOrTrunc(SetCC, dl, ResultType, ResultType);
5990 return;
5991 }
5992
5993 SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, LHS.getValueType());
5994
5995 // LHSSign -> LHS >= 0
5996 // RHSSign -> RHS >= 0
5997 // SumSign -> Result >= 0
5998 //
5999 // Add:
6000 // Overflow -> (LHSSign == RHSSign) && (LHSSign != SumSign)
6001 // Sub:
6002 // Overflow -> (LHSSign != RHSSign) && (LHSSign != SumSign)
6003 SDValue LHSSign = DAG.getSetCC(dl, OType, LHS, Zero, ISD::SETGE);
6004 SDValue RHSSign = DAG.getSetCC(dl, OType, RHS, Zero, ISD::SETGE);
6005 SDValue SignsMatch = DAG.getSetCC(dl, OType, LHSSign, RHSSign,
6006 IsAdd ? ISD::SETEQ : ISD::SETNE);
6007
6008 SDValue SumSign = DAG.getSetCC(dl, OType, Result, Zero, ISD::SETGE);
6009 SDValue SumSignNE = DAG.getSetCC(dl, OType, LHSSign, SumSign, ISD::SETNE);
6010
6011 SDValue Cmp = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, OType, SignsMatch, SumSignNE);
6012 Overflow = DAG.getBoolExtOrTrunc(Cmp, dl, ResultType, ResultType);
6013}
6014
6015bool TargetLowering::expandMULO(SDNode *Node, SDValue &Result,
6016 SDValue &Overflow, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
6017 SDLoc dl(Node);
6018 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
6019 EVT SetCCVT = getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), VT);
6020 SDValue LHS = Node->getOperand(0);
6021 SDValue RHS = Node->getOperand(1);
6022 bool isSigned = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SMULO;
6023
6024 // For power-of-two multiplications we can use a simpler shift expansion.
6025 if (ConstantSDNode *RHSC = isConstOrConstSplat(RHS)) {
6026 const APInt &C = RHSC->getAPIntValue();
6027 // mulo(X, 1 << S) -> { X << S, (X << S) >> S != X }
6028 if (C.isPowerOf2()) {
6029 // smulo(x, signed_min) is same as umulo(x, signed_min).
6030 bool UseArithShift = isSigned && !C.isMinSignedValue();
6031 EVT ShiftAmtTy = getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout());
6032 SDValue ShiftAmt = DAG.getConstant(C.logBase2(), dl, ShiftAmtTy);
6033 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, LHS, ShiftAmt);
6034 Overflow = DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCVT,
6035 DAG.getNode(UseArithShift ? ISD::SRA : ISD::SRL,
6036 dl, VT, Result, ShiftAmt),
6037 LHS, ISD::SETNE);
6038 return true;
6039 }
6040 }
6041
6042 EVT WideVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), VT.getScalarSizeInBits() * 2);
6043 if (VT.isVector())
6044 WideVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), WideVT,
6045 VT.getVectorNumElements());
6046
6047 SDValue BottomHalf;
6048 SDValue TopHalf;
6049 static const unsigned Ops[2][3] =
6050 { { ISD::MULHU, ISD::UMUL_LOHI, ISD::ZERO_EXTEND },
6051 { ISD::MULHS, ISD::SMUL_LOHI, ISD::SIGN_EXTEND }};
6052 if (isOperationLegalOrCustom(Ops[isSigned][0], VT)) {
6053 BottomHalf = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, VT, LHS, RHS);
6054 TopHalf = DAG.getNode(Ops[isSigned][0], dl, VT, LHS, RHS);
6055 } else if (isOperationLegalOrCustom(Ops[isSigned][1], VT)) {
6056 BottomHalf = DAG.getNode(Ops[isSigned][1], dl, DAG.getVTList(VT, VT), LHS,
6057 RHS);
6058 TopHalf = BottomHalf.getValue(1);
6059 } else if (isTypeLegal(WideVT)) {
6060 LHS = DAG.getNode(Ops[isSigned][2], dl, WideVT, LHS);
6061 RHS = DAG.getNode(Ops[isSigned][2], dl, WideVT, RHS);
6062 SDValue Mul = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, WideVT, LHS, RHS);
6063 BottomHalf = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, VT, Mul);
6064 SDValue ShiftAmt = DAG.getConstant(VT.getScalarSizeInBits(), dl,
6065 getShiftAmountTy(WideVT, DAG.getDataLayout()));
6066 TopHalf = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, VT,
6067 DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, WideVT, Mul, ShiftAmt));
6068 } else {
6069 if (VT.isVector())
6070 return false;
6071
6072 // We can fall back to a libcall with an illegal type for the MUL if we
6073 // have a libcall big enough.
6074 // Also, we can fall back to a division in some cases, but that's a big
6075 // performance hit in the general case.
6076 RTLIB::Libcall LC = RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL;
6077 if (WideVT == MVT::i16)
6078 LC = RTLIB::MUL_I16;
6079 else if (WideVT == MVT::i32)
6080 LC = RTLIB::MUL_I32;
6081 else if (WideVT == MVT::i64)
6082 LC = RTLIB::MUL_I64;
6083 else if (WideVT == MVT::i128)
6084 LC = RTLIB::MUL_I128;
6085 assert(LC != RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL && "Cannot expand this operation!");
6086
6087 SDValue HiLHS;
6088 SDValue HiRHS;
6089 if (isSigned) {
6090 // The high part is obtained by SRA'ing all but one of the bits of low
6091 // part.
6092 unsigned LoSize = VT.getSizeInBits();
6093 HiLHS =
6094 DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, dl, VT, LHS,
6095 DAG.getConstant(LoSize - 1, dl,
6096 getPointerRangeTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
6097 HiRHS =
6098 DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, dl, VT, RHS,
6099 DAG.getConstant(LoSize - 1, dl,
6100 getPointerRangeTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
6101 } else {
6102 HiLHS = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT);
6103 HiRHS = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT);
6104 }
6105
6106 // Here we're passing the 2 arguments explicitly as 4 arguments that are
6107 // pre-lowered to the correct types. This all depends upon WideVT not
6108 // being a legal type for the architecture and thus has to be split to
6109 // two arguments.
6110 SDValue Ret;
6111 if (shouldSplitFunctionArgumentsAsLittleEndian(DAG.getDataLayout())) {
6112 // Halves of WideVT are packed into registers in different order
6113 // depending on platform endianness. This is usually handled by
6114 // the C calling convention, but we can't defer to it in
6115 // the legalizer.
6116 SDValue Args[] = { LHS, HiLHS, RHS, HiRHS };
6117 Ret = makeLibCall(DAG, LC, WideVT, Args, isSigned, dl,
6118 /* doesNotReturn */ false, /* isReturnValueUsed */ true,
6119 /* isPostTypeLegalization */ true).first;
6120 } else {
6121 SDValue Args[] = { HiLHS, LHS, HiRHS, RHS };
6122 Ret = makeLibCall(DAG, LC, WideVT, Args, isSigned, dl,
6123 /* doesNotReturn */ false, /* isReturnValueUsed */ true,
6124 /* isPostTypeLegalization */ true).first;
6125 }
6126 assert(Ret.getOpcode() == ISD::MERGE_VALUES &&
6127 "Ret value is a collection of constituent nodes holding result.");
6128 if (DAG.getDataLayout().isLittleEndian()) {
6129 // Same as above.
6130 BottomHalf = Ret.getOperand(0);
6131 TopHalf = Ret.getOperand(1);
6132 } else {
6133 BottomHalf = Ret.getOperand(1);
6134 TopHalf = Ret.getOperand(0);
6135 }
6136 }
6137
6138 Result = BottomHalf;
6139 if (isSigned) {
6140 SDValue ShiftAmt = DAG.getConstant(
6141 VT.getScalarSizeInBits() - 1, dl,
6142 getShiftAmountTy(BottomHalf.getValueType(), DAG.getDataLayout()));
6143 SDValue Sign = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, dl, VT, BottomHalf, ShiftAmt);
6144 Overflow = DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCVT, TopHalf, Sign, ISD::SETNE);
6145 } else {
6146 Overflow = DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCVT, TopHalf,
6147 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT), ISD::SETNE);
6148 }
6149
6150 // Truncate the result if SetCC returns a larger type than needed.
6151 EVT RType = Node->getValueType(1);
6152 if (RType.getSizeInBits() < Overflow.getValueSizeInBits())
6153 Overflow = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, RType, Overflow);
6154
6155 assert(RType.getSizeInBits() == Overflow.getValueSizeInBits() &&
6156 "Unexpected result type for S/UMULO legalization");
6157 return true;
6158}
6159
6160SDValue TargetLowering::expandVecReduce(SDNode *Node, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
6161 SDLoc dl(Node);
6162 bool NoNaN = Node->getFlags().hasNoNaNs();
6163 unsigned BaseOpcode = 0;
6164 switch (Node->getOpcode()) {
6165 default: llvm_unreachable("Expected VECREDUCE opcode");
6166 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FADD: BaseOpcode = ISD::FADD; break;
6167 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMUL: BaseOpcode = ISD::FMUL; break;
6168 case ISD::VECREDUCE_ADD: BaseOpcode = ISD::ADD; break;
6169 case ISD::VECREDUCE_MUL: BaseOpcode = ISD::MUL; break;
6170 case ISD::VECREDUCE_AND: BaseOpcode = ISD::AND; break;
6171 case ISD::VECREDUCE_OR: BaseOpcode = ISD::OR; break;
6172 case ISD::VECREDUCE_XOR: BaseOpcode = ISD::XOR; break;
6173 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMAX: BaseOpcode = ISD::SMAX; break;
6174 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMIN: BaseOpcode = ISD::SMIN; break;
6175 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMAX: BaseOpcode = ISD::UMAX; break;
6176 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMIN: BaseOpcode = ISD::UMIN; break;
6177 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMAX:
6178 BaseOpcode = NoNaN ? ISD::FMAXNUM : ISD::FMAXIMUM;
6179 break;
6180 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMIN:
6181 BaseOpcode = NoNaN ? ISD::FMINNUM : ISD::FMINIMUM;
6182 break;
6183 }
6184
6185 SDValue Op = Node->getOperand(0);
6186 EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
6187
6188 // Try to use a shuffle reduction for power of two vectors.
6189 if (VT.isPow2VectorType()) {
6190 while (VT.getVectorNumElements() > 1) {
6191 EVT HalfVT = VT.getHalfNumVectorElementsVT(*DAG.getContext());
6192 if (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(BaseOpcode, HalfVT))
6193 break;
6194
6195 SDValue Lo, Hi;
6196 std::tie(Lo, Hi) = DAG.SplitVector(Op, dl);
6197 Op = DAG.getNode(BaseOpcode, dl, HalfVT, Lo, Hi);
6198 VT = HalfVT;
6199 }
6200 }
6201
6202 EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
6203 unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
6204
6205 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops;
6206 DAG.ExtractVectorElements(Op, Ops, 0, NumElts);
6207
6208 SDValue Res = Ops[0];
6209 for (unsigned i = 1; i < NumElts; i++)
6210 Res = DAG.getNode(BaseOpcode, dl, EltVT, Res, Ops[i], Node->getFlags());
6211
6212 // Result type may be wider than element type.
6213 if (EltVT != Node->getValueType(0))
6214 Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, Node->getValueType(0), Res);
6215 return Res;
6216}
